2026-07-10 00:30:48 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow: {"type": "AI", "text": "As Chief of Staff, I have assessed the situation regarding the unauthorized disclosure of Q3 financial earnings. While the automated agent network is currently undergoing a system recalibration, I have synthesized an Executive Action plan based on established crisis management protocols for Cognizant India.\n\n### Cyber Security\n*   **Immediate Action:** Initiate an emergency audit of document access logs to confirm if the leak was an isolated accident or part of a broader data breach.\n*   **Containment:** Coordinate with Twitter/X legal support for an immediate \"takedown\" request based on copyright infringement (proprietary financial data) and violation of corporate data protection policies.\n\n### Finance & Risk\n*   **Market Impact:** Quantify the immediate exposure. Prepare for potential volatility in our share price on the NSE/BSE.\n*   **Mitigation:** Liaise with the Investor Relations team to determine if an early, full disclosure is required to stabilize the market, rather than letting the fragmented leak dictate the narrative.\n\n### Legal & Regulatory\n*   **SEBI Compliance:** The Regulatory team must prepare a formal disclosure for the Stock Exchanges (BSE/NSE) under SEBI (Listing Obligations and Disclosure Requirements) Regulations to maintain transparency and avoid non-compliance penalties.\n*   **Liability:** Evaluate the employee’s breach of the Non-Disclosure Agreement (NDA) and the Code of Conduct.\n\n### HR & Safety\n*   **Personnel Management:** Suspend the individual pending a full investigation. Ensure the communication is handled with sensitivity but firmness to reinforce our zero-tolerance policy on data leaks.\n*   **Internal Comms:** Issue a company-wide memo (IST) reminding all associates of the \"Data Privacy and Confidentiality\" policy and the severe professional consequences of social media misuse.\n\n### PR & Communications\n*   **External Narrative:** Draft a \"Holding Statement\" for the media. The message should emphasize that while we are investigating the unauthorized post, we remain committed to our rigorous financial reporting standards.\n*   **Social Media Management:** Deploy a \"no-comment\" strategy on the viral thread to avoid amplifying the reach, while focusing on official channels for any necessary corrections or updates.\n\n**Next Steps:** I am convening an emergency meeting with the heads of these departments in 30 minutes to finalize the formal submission to SEBI and the official public statement."}
