gulatory and Standards Compliance\n*   **ISO 27001 (Annex A.8.1):** Ensures accountability and management of assets.\n*   **Cognizant CISO Mandate:** Strict adherence to "Zero Trust" endpoint architecture.\n*   **India DPDP Act 2023:** As these assets will process PII, we must ensure full data encryption and audit logging to prevent "personal data breach" liability.\n*   **IT Act 2000 (Section 43A):** Failure to maintain "reasonable security practices" for sensitive data results in significant corporate liability and penalties.\n\n### 4. Risk Rating: **HIGH**\n*   **Justification:** Given the high-density nature of the Chennai delivery center and the potential for these units to access client-specific production environments, an unprovisioned laptop represents an immediate "High" risk to client data confidentiality and integrity.\n\n### 5. 48-72 Hour Action Plan\n\n| Timeline | Action Item | Responsibility |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **0-12 Hours** | Physical receipt, CAMS registration, and physical asset tagging in Chennai. | Chennai IT Ops |\n| **12-24 Hours** | PXE boot/Autopilot provisioning via the Cognizant Golden Image. | Infrastructure Team |\n| **24-48 Hours** | Intune policy push (BitLocker, CrowdStrike, MDE, CyberArk Agent). | Endpoint Engineering |\n| **48-60 Hours** | Vulnerability scan via Qualys/Defender to ensure no vulnerabilities > CVSS 7.0. | Security Ops (SOC) |\n| **60-72 Hours** | Final audit report submission to CISO office for "Network Ready" status. | Compliance Lead |\n\n**Authoritative Directive:**\nDo not authorize these laptops for production use until the **"Device Compliance"** flag turns green in the Intune dashboard. Any device found on the network without the CrowdStrike Falcon sensor active will be automatically quarantined via our Cisco ISE (Identity Services Engine) integration.\n\n**Signed,**\n*Office of the CISO, Cognizant India*'}
