2026-07-10 00:54:12 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 00:54:12 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from HR_Safety_Agent\nAs the Head of HR for Cognizant India, I have reviewed your request regarding the allocation of 20 Dell Latitude 5540 laptops for the upcoming project kick-off in Chennai.\n\nGiven the **3-day timeline**, we are currently operating outside the standard SLA, which requires a **5-day lead time**. Below is the assessment and the mandatory path forward to ensure our new joiners are onboarded effectively under the \'CognizantOne\' framework.\n\n### 1. Impact Assessment\n*   **Affected Headcount:** 20 new associates.\n*   **Grade Levels:** Typically C1–C2 (Entry-level/Associate) for project-specific deployments.\n*   **Communication:** We must immediately notify the onboarding cohort that while laptops are being processed, their initial orientation will be conducted via BYOD (Bring Your Own Device) or a temporary VDI session if their machine is not ready by Day 1.\n\n### 2. Asset Allocation & Process (The \'New Hire IT Setup\')\nSince the request is for 20 units, we must adhere to the **ServiceNow \'New Hire IT Setup\' catalog item**. \n\n*   **The Constraint:** Our standard policy requires the ticket to be raised **5 days prior** to the joining date. \n*   **Action Plan:** \n    1.  **Immediate Escalation:** You must raise the ServiceNow request **today**. Once the ticket is generated, please share the Ticket ID with the Chennai Facilities/IT Desk.\n    2.  **Manager Approval:** Ensure the hiring manager has completed the \'Asset Provisioning\' workflow in **Workday**. Without the Workday status as "Ready for Onboarding," IT will not release the inventory.\n    3.  **NHOK (New Hire Onboarding Kit):** The laptops are part of the standard NHOK. If inventory at the Chennai delivery center is depleted, we will need to request a trans-location from the nearest hub (e.g., Bangalore or Hyderabad), which may impact the 3-day timeline.\n\n### 3. Internal Communication Template\nPlease use the following template to manage expectations with the project stakeholders:\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** URGENT: IT Asset Provisioning for [Project Name] New Joiners – Chennai DC\n\n**Dear Team,**\n\nWe are excited to welcome the 20 new associates to the [Project Name] team in Chennai. \n\nTo ensure a seamless transition, we are currently processing the allocation of 20 Dell Latitude 5540 laptops. Please note that while we are fast-tracking this request via the ServiceNow \'New Hire IT Setup\' portal, our standard lead time is 5 days. We are working closely with the IT infrastructure team to minimize any potential delays.\n\n**Action Items:**\n*   **Hiring Managers:** Please ensure the Workday onboarding checklist is marked as \'Complete\' for all 20 associates by EOD today.\n*   **Associates:** You will receive an automated notification from ServiceNow once your asset is tagged. Please report to the designated \'Onboarding Zone\' at the Chennai DC on your start date. \n\nWe appreciate your patience as we equip our team for success. Please reach out to the iHR portal (via CognizantOne) if you have any questions regarding your specific onboarding status.\n\nRegards,\n\n**[Your Name/HRBP Name]**\nHuman Resources – Cognizant India\n\n***\n\n### 4. Next Steps\n*   **Workday Check:** Confirm that all 20 associates have been moved to the "Onboarding" stage in Workday.\n*   **iHR Support:** If the ServiceNow ticket is blocked, please raise a high-priority query via the **iHR portal** under "IT/Infrastructure Support" and reference this as a "Project Critical" requirement. \n\n**Note:** Please ensure that all asset handovers are recorded in the Asset Management System (AMS) to maintain compliance with our internal audit policies.'}
2026-07-10 00:54:12 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 00:54:12 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff', 'Cyber_Security_Agent'], 'text': None}
2026-07-10 00:54:12 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 00:54:12 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff', 'Cyber_Security_Agent'], 'text': ''}
2026-07-10 00:54:12 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 00:54:12 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Cyber_Security_Agent\nAs the CISO representative for Cognizant India, I am defining the mandatory security and asset provisioning protocols for the 20 incoming Dell Latitude 5540 units at our Chennai facility. These assets must be "Security-Ready" before they touch the internal production network.\n\n### 1. Security Risk Assessment\nThe primary risks involve **Unauthorized Access, Data Exfiltration, and Insider Threat**. Unprovisioned hardware lacks full-disk encryption, endpoint detection, and identity-bound access controls. If deployed without these controls, these assets present a significant vulnerability to Cognizant’s corporate network, potentially leading to unauthorized data exposure and non-compliance with client-specific security requirements.\n\n### 2. Mandatory Security Controls\n*   **Hardware/Firmware:** Ensure Secure Boot is enabled in BIOS; set a BIOS password to prevent unauthorized modification.\n*   **OS/Image:** Deployment of the **Cognizant Golden Image** (Windows 11 Enterprise) via PXE boot or USB-C imaging server.\n*   **Encryption:** Mandatory **BitLocker** enforcement with XTS-AES 256-bit encryption. Recovery keys must be escrowed to Azure AD/Intune.\n*   **Endpoint Protection:** Silent installation of **CrowdStrike Falcon** (Sensor must be active and communicating with the console).\n*   **Identity & Access:** Registration via **Microsoft Intune (MDM/MAM)** for policy enforcement and **CyberArk** for Privileged Access Management (PAM) if the device is assigned to a developer/admin.\n*   **Asset Tagging:** Physical asset tags (Barcode/QR) must be affixed to the chassis and mapped to the asset ID in the **Cognizant Asset Management System (CAMS)**.\n\n### 3. Standards & Regulatory Compliance\n*   **ISO 27001 (A.8.1.1):** Mandatory inventory of assets.\n*   **Cognizant CISO Mandate:** Strict adherence to the "Zero Trust" hardware provisioning policy.\n*   **India DPDP Act 2023:** Ensures that any device containing PII/SPI is encrypted and monitored to prevent unauthorized data processing.\n*   **IT Act 2000 (Section 43A):** Cognizant as a Body Corporate is liable for damages if reasonable security practices (encryption, access control) are not implemented.\n\n### 4. Risk Rating\n*   **Risk Rating: HIGH**\n*   **Justification:** These are unhardened assets entering a high-security delivery center. Failure to properly tag and secure these laptops before they connect to the corporate network could lead to unauthorized network entry, potential data breaches, and audit failures against client security SLAs.\n\n### 5. 72-Hour Action Plan\n\n| Timeframe | Action Item | Responsibility |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **0-12 Hours** | Physical inspection, BIOS hardening, and tagging in CAMS. | Chennai IT Ops |\n| **12-24 Hours** | PXE/USB deployment of the Golden Image; BitLocker encryption trigger. | Desktop Engineering |\n| **24-48 Hours** | Intune enrollment and CrowdStrike Falcon sensor verification. | Security Operations |\n| **48-60 Hours** | Compliance scan (checking for vulnerabilities/missing patches via Defender). | IT Security Team |\n| **60-72 Hours** | Final audit review; issuance of "Clean Bill of Health" and device hand-over. | CISO Compliance Office |\n\n**Instruction to IT Ops:**\nDo not allow these devices to connect to the production VLAN until the CrowdStrike Falcon console confirms the "Active" status and Intune reports "Compliant." Any device failing to report within 72 hours must be quarantined to the "Isolation VLAN" for manual remediation.'}
