2026-07-10 00:54:15 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow: {"type": "AI", "text": "### Executive Action Summary: Procurement Exception for M/s. Rashi Peripherals\n\nThis briefing outlines the cross-functional assessment regarding the urgent procurement of 20 Dell Latitude 5540 laptops (₹2,32,332) for the Chennai delivery center.\n\n#### ### Procurement & Financial Risk\n*   **Status:** **UNDER REVIEW**. The advance payment request is a high-risk deviation from our standard Net-30 credit policy.\n*   **Directives:** \n    *   No payment is to be issued without a formal **Exception to Policy (ETP)** approval registered in the GRC tool.\n    *   The vendor must provide an **unconditional Bank Guarantee (BG)** equal to the advance amount (₹2,32,332) before any funds are released.\n    *   Procurement must link this transaction to a specific milestone in the **iSource** portal to protect Cognizant’s capital.\n    *   Finance has confirmed that this transaction exceeds the ₹2 Lakh threshold, requiring digital sign-off from the VP of Finance.\n\n#### ### Legal & Compliance\n*   **Status:** **MEDIUM RISK**. \n*   **Directives:** Any advance payment must be structured as a \"recoverable deposit\" under a formal contract addendum to mitigate risks under the Indian Contract Act, 1872. The legal team mandates that the contract include a \"Right of Set-off\" and \"Clawback Provision\" to ensure recovery in the event of vendor default.\n\n#### ### Cyber Security & Asset Management\n*   **Status:** **HIGH RISK**. \n*   **Directives:** Assets arriving in Chennai must undergo strict hardening. No laptop may connect to the production VLAN until:\n    1.  Physical asset tagging is completed in the **Cognizant Asset Management System (CAMS)**.\n    2.  The **Cognizant Golden Image** is deployed.\n    3.  **CrowdStrike Falcon** and **BitLocker** encryption are verified active by the Security Operations team.\n    4.  Devices are enrolled and compliant in **Microsoft Intune**.\n\n#### ### HR & Onboarding\n*   **Status:** **ESCALATED**. \n*   **Directives:** \n    *   The 3-day timeline is below the standard 5-day SLA. Hiring managers must ensure Workday onboarding checklists are marked \"Complete\" by EOD today.\n    *   A ServiceNow ticket must be raised immediately. If the request is blocked, it must be escalated via the **iHR Portal** as a \"Project Critical\" requirement.\n\n---\n\n### STATUS: UNDER REVIEW\n**NEXT STEPS:**\n1.  **Procurement:** Request a Bank Guarantee (BG) from M/s. Rashi Peripherals (Owner: Procurement Lead).\n2.  **Finance:** Submit the ETP request in the GRC tool for VP Finance sign-off (Owner: Procurement Finance Controller).\n3.  **IT Ops:** Prepare the Chennai DC intake area for immediate BIOS hardening and asset tagging upon arrival (Owner: Chennai IT Operations Manager).\n4.  **HR:** Verify Workday status for all 20 associates and trigger the ServiceNow ticket (Owner: HR Business Partner).\n5.  **Legal:** Draft the Addendum for the advance payment exception ensuring all recovery clauses are included (Owner: Legal Counsel)."}
