2026-07-10 01:03:55 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow: {"type": "AI", "text": "### Executive Action Summary: Procurement of 20 Dell Latitude 5540 Laptops\n\nThis memorandum outlines the cross-functional assessment regarding the urgent procurement of 20 Dell Latitude 5540 laptops (Total: ₹2,32,332) from M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd. for the Chennai delivery center.\n\n---\n\n### Procurement & Financial Risk\n*   **Status:** **UNDER REVIEW / EXCEPTION REQUIRED**.\n*   **Financial Impact:** The request for advance payment violates Cognizant's standard Net-30 credit policy. This creates a financial risk of unsecured capital outflow.\n*   **Requirements for Approval:**\n    *   **Exception to Policy (ETP):** Must be logged in the procurement system (Ariba/Coupa) with full justification.\n    *   **Bank Guarantee (BG):** The vendor must provide an irrevocable Bank Guarantee for the full amount (₹2,32,332) as per legal and finance mandates.\n    *   **Vendor Validation:** Procurement must confirm vendor status in the iSource portal; if Rashi Peripherals cannot meet Net-30 terms, alternative Tier-1 vendors should be engaged immediately.\n\n### Legal & Regulatory Compliance\n*   **Legal Position:** The shift to advance payment requires a formal **Addendum to the Master Service Agreement (MSA)** to avoid setting a dangerous precedent.\n*   **Regulatory Risk:** Failure to secure the hardware after payment could lead to audit queries regarding \"Prepaid Expenses\" and potential GST Input Tax Credit (ITC) reconciliation issues under the CGST/SGST Act.\n*   **Mandate:** Legal Counsel mandates an indemnity bond or BG to protect Cognizant’s interest under the Indian Contract Act, 1872.\n\n### Cyber Security & Asset Management\n*   **Security Posture:** **CRITICAL**. These assets will handle client data; therefore, standard security hardening is non-negotiable.\n*   **Deployment Protocol:** \n    *   **Physical:** Mandatory tagging via CAMS at the Chennai delivery center upon receipt.\n    *   **Logical:** Full \"Golden Image\" deployment, BitLocker encryption (AES-256), and CrowdStrike Falcon sensor installation are mandatory.\n    *   **Compliance:** No asset shall be issued to an associate until Intune reports \"Compliant\" status and the device heartbeat is confirmed in the SecOps dashboard.\n\n### HR & Onboarding\n*   **Status:** **COORDINATION IN PROGRESS**.\n*   **Workforce Readiness:** The 20 new joiners are scheduled for project kick-off in 3 days. \n*   **Action:** HR has authorized an \"Urgent Fulfillment\" status for the ServiceNow IT requests. Any delay in hardware delivery beyond the 3-day window will require immediate activation of \"Hot-Desking\" and loaner device protocols at the Chennai campus.\n\n---\n\n### STATUS: ESCALATED\nThe request is currently held pending the submission of the Bank Guarantee and the formal ETP approval in the procurement system.\n\n### NEXT STEPS\n1.  **Procurement Team:** Immediately request a Bank Guarantee from M/s. Rashi Peripherals and log the ETP in Ariba. **(Owner: Procurement Lead, Bangalore)**\n2.  **Finance Team:** Review and approve the ETP once the BG is validated by the Treasury department. **(Owner: Finance Controller)**\n3.  **IT/Asset Team (Chennai):** Prepare the Chennai warehouse for receipt and initiate the \"Urgent Fulfillment\" ServiceNow tickets for the 20 associates. **(Owner: Chennai IT Lead)**\n4.  **HR Team:** Communicate the 3-day timeline to new joiners and prepare contingency \"loaner\" devices to ensure no impact on project kick-off. **(Owner: HRBP Chennai)**\n5.  **Legal Team:** Draft and execute the one-time MSA Addendum for the advance payment terms. **(Owner: Legal Counsel)**"}
