2026-07-10 01:19:15 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow: {"type": "AI", "text": "### Executive Action Summary: Procurement & Onboarding Strategy\n\n**To:** Executive Leadership Team, Cognizant India\n**From:** Office of the Chief of Staff\n**Subject:** Urgent Procurement & Asset Provisioning – Chennai Delivery Center\n**Date:** May 22, 2024 (IST)\n\nFollowing a cross-functional review regarding the purchase of 20 Dell Latitude 5540 laptops (₹2,32,332) for the Chennai delivery center, the following directive has been established to ensure compliance with financial policies, legal mandates, and IT security protocols.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Finance & Procurement Directive\n*   **Payment Policy:** The request for advance payment is **DENIED** as it violates standard Net-30 day credit terms.\n*   **Exception Process:** To proceed, the procurement team must secure a **Bank Guarantee (BG)** for the full amount of ₹2,32,332. Alternatively, the vendor must agree to standard Net-30 terms.\n*   **Approval Authority:** As the invoice value exceeds ₹2 Lakh, this transaction requires a formal **Exception to Policy (ETP)** form, signed by the BU Head and the Finance Controller, and uploaded to the Ariba portal.\n*   **Compliance:** Verify the vendor's MSME status via the Udyam portal. If they are an MSME, the 45-day statutory payment limit under the MSME Act, 2006, is legally binding.\n\n### 2. Legal & Regulatory Compliance\n*   **Contractual Integrity:** Any deviation from payment terms requires a formal \"Letter of Variation\" or \"Amendment to MSA\" to avoid breach of contract under the Indian Contract Act, 1872.\n*   **Audit Trail:** All correspondence must be archived in the iSource vendor portal to satisfy internal audit requirements and minimize risk under the DPDP Act 2023.\n\n### 3. IT Security & Asset Management\n*   **Critical Security Baseline:** No laptop may be deployed until it passes the \"Compliant\" check in Intune. This includes mandatory BitLocker (XTS-AES 256) encryption, CrowdStrike Falcon (EDR) installation, and CyberArk (EPM) configuration.\n*   **Asset Tracking:** Units must be registered in the ServiceNow CMDB within 24 hours of GRN. Failure to perform this will trigger an audit flag.\n\n### 4. HR & Onboarding Coordination\n*   **Expedited Provisioning:** The 3-day window is critical. The IT setup request must be submitted via ServiceNow immediately, tagged with Director-level approval, to bypass the standard 5-day SLA.\n*   **Day 1 Readiness:** If delivery is delayed beyond the 3-day window, the Chennai Onboarding Lead is authorized to issue temporary \"loaner\" devices to prevent Day 1 productivity loss.\n\n---\n\n**STATUS: UNDER REVIEW (Pending Financial ETP & Bank Guarantee)**\n\n**NEXT STEPS:**\n1.  **Procurement Team:** Negotiate Net-30 terms or secure a Bank Guarantee from M/s. Rashi Peripherals. (Owner: Procurement Lead)\n2.  **Finance Ops:** Generate the ETP form and route for Finance Controller signature upon receipt of vendor compliance docs. (Owner: Finance Controller)\n3.  **IT/Asset Team:** Initiate the ServiceNow 'New Hire IT Setup' request and prepare for physical imaging upon arrival. (Owner: IT Asset Manager)\n4.  **HR Team:** Notify the 20 new joiners of the provisioning status and ensure they complete the iHR Pre-boarding Checklist. (Owner: HR Onboarding Lead)"}
