allows us to hold critical components in a "ready-to-deploy" state, reducing the risk of global supply chain volatility affecting our project ramp-ups.\n\n### 3. Asset Lifecycle Management (ALM) & Governance\nGovernance is non-negotiable. Every asset must be accounted for within our ecosystem:\n\n*   **Asset Tagging:** Upon receipt, every device is physically affixed with a **Cognizant (CTS) Asset Tag**.\n*   **CMDB Integration:** The asset details (Serial Number, MAC address, Model) must be updated in the **ServiceNow CMDB**. Failure to update the CMDB within 24 hours of receipt results in a procurement audit flag.\n*   **Cost Center Assignment:** Each asset is mapped to a specific **SAP Cost Center**. This ensures that depreciation and maintenance costs are accurately reflected in the P&L of the respective business unit (BU).\n\n### 4. Logistics & Financial Realities\n*   **Logistics Costs:** We negotiate volume-based contracts with our logistics partners. On average, inter-city shipping for a standard laptop unit ranges between **INR 400–800**, inclusive of insurance and transit tracking.\n*   **Performance Monitoring:** We conduct quarterly **Vendor Business Reviews (VBRs)**. Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) include:\n    *   **OTIF (On-Time In-Full) Delivery Rate:** Target > 95%.\n    *   **PO Acknowledgement Time:** Target < 24 hours.\n    *   **Defect Rate:** Target < 1%.\n\n### Summary for Stakeholders\nOur supply chain is designed for scale and speed. By leveraging **SAP S/4HANA** for data integrity and **iSource** for seamless vendor collaboration, we ensure that Cognizant associates have the tools required to deliver for our clients without friction. \n\n**Pro-tip for project leads:** Always ensure your PRs are submitted with the correct Cost Center code at least 10 business days before the required "In-Hand" date to account for potential logistics variances.'}
