2026-07-10 01:35:06 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 01:35:06 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': "result from HR_Safety_Agent\nAs Head of Human Resources for Cognizant India, I am pleased to outline our framework for operational excellence, associate safety, and talent risk mitigation. At Cognizant, our **'CognizantOne'** framework serves as the foundation for the associate experience, ensuring that every policy is accessible, equitable, and data-driven via our **Workday HRMS** and **iHR portal**.\n\nBelow is the overview of our strategic approach:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Workforce Safety & Statutory Compliance\nOur commitment to safety is non-negotiable. We strictly adhere to the **Factories Act, 1948**, and our internal **Occupational Safety and Health (OSH) Policy**.\n\n*   **Policy Enforcement:** All facilities must maintain mandated safety registers, emergency exit protocols, and periodic safety audits.\n*   **Incident Reporting:** Any safety incident or near-miss must be reported immediately via the **iHR 'Safety Incident Report' module**. \n*   **Compliance:** We conduct regular training on fire safety, workstation ergonomics (especially for our Work-from-Anywhere associates), and emergency evacuation procedures to ensure 100% compliance with local labor laws.\n\n### 2. HR Policy & Talent Risk Management\nManaging a workforce of our scale requires a robust risk management framework integrated into **Workday**.\n\n*   **Talent Risk Assessment:** We categorize talent risk by mapping **Grade Levels (C1-C5 for associates; M1-M5 for management)** against performance data and flight-risk indicators (e.g., tenure, skill obsolescence, and compensation benchmarking).\n*   **Mitigation:** We utilize the **'Cognizant Talent Marketplace'** to encourage internal mobility, reducing churn by providing associates with new project opportunities without them having to leave the organization.\n*   **Policy Access:** All associates are expected to review the **'India Employee Handbook'** available on the **iHR portal**, which outlines our Code of Conduct, POSH (Prevention of Sexual Harassment) policies, and our 'Zero Tolerance' stance on non-compliance.\n\n### 3. Asset Allocation & Onboarding (NHOK)\nEfficiency in onboarding is a key KPI for our Talent Acquisition and IT teams. To ensure a seamless Day 1 experience:\n\n*   **NHOK Process:** Managers must initiate the **'New Hire IT Setup'** request via the **ServiceNow catalog** at least **5 days prior** to the associate’s joining date.\n*   **Verification:** This triggers the provisioning of the **New Hire Onboarding Kit (NHOK)**, which includes the workstation, encrypted hardware, and system access rights pre-configured for the associate’s specific grade and project requirements.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Template: Internal Communication Memo\n*When addressing a shift in policy or a major organizational update, we use the following standard: *\n\n**Subject:** [Action Required/Update] Important Policy Update Regarding [Topic]\n\n**Dear Associates,**\n\nAt Cognizant, we continuously evolve our processes to better serve our talent and clients. We are writing to inform you of [Update/Change] effective [Date].\n\n*   **Impact:** This update applies to all associates across grades [C1-M5].\n*   **Why it matters:** This alignment ensures we remain compliant with [Policy/Regulation] and strengthens our operational agility.\n*   **Next Steps:** Please log in to the **iHR portal** to acknowledge the updated policy. Detailed FAQs are available in the 'Policy Corner' section.\n*   **Support:** If you have questions, please raise a ticket via **ServiceNow** or reach out to your designated HR Business Partner (HRBP).\n\nThank you for your continued commitment to excellence and for being a vital part of the Cognizant family.\n\nBest regards,\n\n**[Your Name/HR Leadership Team]**\nCognizant India\n\n---\n\n### Summary Checklist for Managers:\n*   **Workday:** Ensure performance reviews and skill tags are current to prevent talent risk.\n*   **iHR:** Use for all policy queries and leave/benefit management.\n*   **ServiceNow:** The single point of contact for IT assets (NHOK) and HR service requests.\n\n*Should you require deeper analysis on specific attrition data or compliance audits, please refer to the 'HR Analytics Dashboard' within Workday.*"}
