2026-07-10 01:35:08 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 01:35:07 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Regulatory_Agent\nAs the Chief Compliance Officer for Cognizant India, I provide the following regulatory framework overview. For a listed IT services entity operating in India, adherence is not optional; it is the cornerstone of our fiduciary duty and operational license.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Regulatory Framework Overview\n\n| Regulation | Scope of Application | Key Regulatory Authority |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **CERT-In Directions 2022** | Cybersecurity incident reporting & log retention. | MeitY (CERT-In) |\n| **DPDP Act 2023** | Processing of digital personal data of Indian residents. | Data Protection Board of India |\n| **SEBI LODR 2015** | Corporate governance & material event disclosures. | SEBI |\n| **Companies Act 2013** | Board composition, filings, and financial reporting. | Ministry of Corporate Affairs (MCA) |\n| **GST Act 2017** | Indirect taxation on IT services exports/domestic. | CBIC |\n| **RBI Master Directions** | IT outsourcing norms & data localization (if applicable). | Reserve Bank of India |\n\n---\n\n### 2. Mandatory Reporting Timelines\n\n*   **CERT-In (2022 Directions):** Cyber incidents (e.g., unauthorized access, data breaches, phishing) must be reported within **6 hours** of detection via email (incident@cert-in.org.in) or phone.\n*   **SEBI (LODR Regulations 2015):** \n    *   **Material Events:** Disclosure must be made within **12 hours** (if originated by the Board) or **24 hours** (if other events) of the occurrence.\n    *   **Financial Results:** Published within **45 days** of the end of the quarter.\n*   **Companies Act 2013:** Annual General Meeting (AGM) must be held within **6 months** of the end of the financial year. Filing of Form MGT-7 (Annual Return) within **60 days** of the AGM.\n*   **GST Act 2017:** GSTR-1 (Outward Supplies) due by the **11th** of the succeeding month; GSTR-3B (Summary Return) due by the **20th** of the succeeding month.\n\n---\n\n### 3. GST Calculation Logic (IT Services)\n\n*   **HSN Code:** 9983 (Other professional, technical, and business services).\n*   **GST Rate:** **18%** (Standard rate for IT/Software services).\n*   **Place of Supply (PoS):**\n    *   **Export of Services:** If the recipient is outside India, the transaction is a "Zero-Rated Supply" under Section 16 of the IGST Act. Subject to LUT (Letter of Undertaking) filing, no GST is paid.\n    *   **Domestic (Intra-state):** If the service provider and recipient are in the same state, charge **9% CGST + 9% SGST**.\n    *   **Domestic (Inter-state):** If the recipient is in a different state, charge **18% IGST**.\n\n---\n\n### 4. COMPLIANCE STATUS: ACTION REQUIRED\n\nAs of today, the following mandates require immediate internal audit and verification:\n\n1.  **DPDP Act 2023 Readiness:** While the Act is notified, the Rules are currently being finalized. **Action:** Map all Data Fiduciary processing activities and appoint a Data Protection Officer (DPO) as per Section 8.\n2.  **SEBI LODR Compliance:** Ensure the "Materiality Policy" is updated per the latest SEBI circulars (dated July 13, 2023) regarding the quantitative threshold for materiality.\n3.  **CERT-In Log Retention:** Verify that all ICT systems maintain logs for a rolling period of **180 days** within Indian jurisdiction, as per the April 2022 mandate.\n4.  **Companies Act - Secretarial Audit:** Ensure Form MR-3 is ready for the upcoming board cycle.\n\n**Chief Compliance Officer’s Directive:** All business units must perform a "Compliance Gap Analysis" by the end of this quarter. Any failure to report a cybersecurity incident within the 6-hour window will be treated as a **BREACH** of internal policy and statutory obligation, subject to severe penalties under Section 70B of the IT Act.\n\n***Disclaimer:** This summary is for professional guidance within the Cognizant India governance framework and does not substitute for specific legal counsel on evolving judicial interpretations.*'}
