2026-07-10 01:35:11 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow: {"type": "AI", "text": "As the Chief of Staff for Cognizant Technology Solutions India Pvt. Ltd., I have compiled the following executive briefing based on the capabilities of our specialized internal departments. This memo outlines the operational, financial, and regulatory frameworks available to support your initiatives across our major delivery centers.\n\n### ### Cyber Security & Infrastructure Hardening\nCognizant India enforces a \"Golden Standard\" for all delivery centers to align with **ISO 27001:2022** and the **DPDP Act 2023**.\n*   **Mandatory Stack:** All endpoints must run **CrowdStrike Falcon** and **Microsoft Defender** in active blocking mode. Access is strictly controlled via **CyberArk (PAM)**.\n*   **Compliance:** Adherence to **Section 43A of the IT Act 2000** is mandatory. Infrastructure hardening follows CIS Benchmark Level 1.\n*   **Action:** All delivery center heads must complete the \"Hardening Compliance Report\" by EOD Friday to avoid network revocation.\n\n### ### Procurement & Supply Chain Operations\nOperations are managed through **SAP S/4HANA** and the **iSource** portal.\n*   **Logistics:** Standard lead time for IT hardware from OEMs (e.g., Dell India) is **5–7 business days**. Inter-city shipping costs range between **INR 400–800** per unit.\n*   **Governance:** Every asset must be tagged and updated in the **ServiceNow CMDB** within 24 hours of receipt.\n*   **Procurement Tip:** Submit PRs with correct Cost Center codes at least 10 business days before the required \"In-Hand\" date.\n\n### ### Financial Risk & Budget Management\nFiscal discipline is maintained through strict approval thresholds and GST compliance.\n*   **Thresholds:** Approvals range from BU Head (up to **INR 2 Lakhs**) to CFO (above **INR 10 Lakhs**).\n*   **GST:** All IT hardware (HSN 8471) attracts **18% GST**. Proper invoice documentation is essential for claiming Input Tax Credit (ITC).\n*   **Terms:** We operate on a **Net-30 day** payment cycle. Advances require a **Bank Guarantee (BG)** and formal Exception to Policy (ETP) approval.\n\n### ### HR, Talent & Workforce Safety\nPolicy management is centralized in **Workday** and the **iHR portal**.\n*   **Safety:** Operations must comply with the **Factories Act, 1948**. All safety incidents must be reported via the iHR portal immediately.\n*   **Onboarding:** Managers must initiate the **New Hire IT Setup (NHOK)** in **ServiceNow** 5 days prior to the start date.\n*   **Talent Risk:** We utilize the 'Cognizant Talent Marketplace' to mitigate churn and manage flight risk across all grades (C1–M5).\n\n### ### Legal, Regulatory & Compliance\nLegal and regulatory frameworks are non-negotiable for our operating license in India.\n*   **Contractual:** All MSAs must include arbitration clauses under the **Arbitration & Conciliation Act, 1996**. MSME vendors must be paid within 45 days per the **MSME Development Act, 2006**.\n*   **Regulatory:** **CERT-In** requires cyber incident reporting within **6 hours**. **SEBI LODR** mandates disclosure of material events within **12–24 hours**.\n*   **Retention:** ICT system logs must be retained for **180 days** within India.\n\n### ### Client Support & Corporate Communications\nOur \"Client-for-Life\" strategy relies on proactive transparency.\n*   **SLA Management:** Breaches are managed via the **STAR framework** (Situation, Task, Action, Result). Service credits for breaches are typically 10–15% of MRR.\n*   **PR/Social Media:** Crisis management follows the **\"Cognizant Impact Matrix\"**. All public/social media responses must be vetted by the Corporate Communications team to ensure compliance with the **IT Rules 2021**.\n\n***\n\n**STATUS: OPERATIONAL / COMPLIANCE-READY**\n\n**NEXT STEPS:**\n1.  **Cyber Security:** IT Ops to complete asset inventory scan by EOD Thursday (Owner: CISO Office).\n2.  **Procurement:** Verify all Q2 pending PRs against current Cost Center budgets (Owner: Finance/Supply Chain Leads).\n3.  **Compliance:** Conduct internal Gap Analysis for DPDP Act 2023 readiness by end of Q2 (Owner: Regulatory/Legal Teams).\n4.  **HR:** Audit NHOK provisioning SLAs for new hires joining in June (Owner: HR Operations)."}
