2026-07-10 01:53:41 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 01:53:41 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff', 'PR_Comms_Agent'], 'text': ''}
2026-07-10 01:53:41 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 01:53:41 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from PR_Comms_Agent\nThis is a critical situation involving potential regulatory scrutiny and market sensitivity. As Head of Corporate Communications, I have outlined the containment strategy below.\n\n### 1. Reputational Risk Assessment\n**Rating: 8/10**\n*   **Justification:** A premature disclosure of financial results is a material breach of compliance protocols. It triggers immediate concerns regarding internal controls, market fairness (insider trading risks), and regulatory oversight (SEC/SEBI). If not contained, it invites volatility in stock price and erodes investor trust, which is the cornerstone of our $19.4B valuation.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Media Holding Statement\n"Cognizant is aware of the unauthorized circulation of preliminary financial information regarding our third-quarter performance. We are currently conducting a comprehensive investigation into the source of this disclosure and are working closely with relevant regulatory authorities. We remain committed to transparency and will provide our official Q3 results during our scheduled earnings call on [Date]."\n\n---\n\n### 3. Press Release (AP Style)\n\n**FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE**\n\n**Cognizant Addresses Unauthorized Disclosure of Preliminary Financial Information**\n\n**TEANECK, N.J. — [Date]** — Cognizant (Nasdaq: CTSH) today announced that it is investigating the unauthorized disclosure of preliminary financial data related to its third-quarter performance.\n\nThe company is taking immediate steps to verify the integrity of the information and has engaged external counsel and forensic experts to determine the origin of the leak. Cognizant is cooperating fully with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) and other regulatory bodies as appropriate.\n\nCognizant reiterates that its scheduled earnings call remains set for [Date/Time]. The company will not be commenting further on the unauthorized data at this time and encourages stakeholders to rely only on official company filings and announcements.\n\n**About Cognizant**\nCognizant (Nasdaq: CTSH) engineers modern businesses. We help our clients modernize technology, reimagine processes and transform experiences so they can stay ahead in our fast-changing world. Together, we’re improving everyday life. See how at www.cognizant.com or @cognizant.\n\n### 4. Key Media Outlets to Monitor\n*   **The Economic Times (ET) / ET Now:** Critical for tracking immediate market sentiment and analyst reactions in our largest delivery hub.\n*   **Mint:** Essential for monitoring regulatory and corporate governance critique.\n*   **Economic Times Tech:** To manage the narrative regarding operational stability and associate morale.\n*   **NDTV Profit:** Primary channel for investor-focused scrutiny and live market impact.\n\n---\n\n### 5. CEO Internal Town Hall Talking Points\n\n*   **Acknowledge and Validate:** "I know there is significant chatter regarding the recent unauthorized disclosure of our Q3 data. I want to address this directly: we take the integrity of our financial reporting with the utmost seriousness."\n*   **Reassure on Process:** "Our core business remains strong, and our commitment to our clients and our 340,000 associates is unchanged. We have robust internal protocols, and we are currently investigating how this breach occurred to ensure it does not happen again."\n*   **Call for Focus:** "While the external noise is distracting, our focus must remain on delivering excellence for our clients. I ask that you refrain from speculating on social media or with external parties; please direct all external inquiries to the Corporate Communications team."\n*   **Commitment to Transparency:** "We will share the official, verified results during our scheduled earnings call. I thank you for your continued dedication to Cognizant’s values and for maintaining our focus on the work that matters."'}
