2026-07-10 01:53:41 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 01:53:41 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff', 'Cyber_Security_Agent'], 'text': ''}
2026-07-10 01:53:42 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 01:53:41 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Cyber_Security_Agent\nAs the CISO representative for Cognizant India, I have evaluated the unauthorized disclosure of Q3 earnings data by a senior delivery manager. This constitutes a severe breach of Cognizant’s **Global Code of Conduct**, **Insider Trading Policy**, and the **Non-Disclosure Agreement (NDA)**.\n\n### 1. Risk Assessment\n*   **Confidentiality Breach:** Exposure of Material Non-Public Information (MNPI) prior to official SEBI/SEC filings.\n*   **Regulatory/Legal Risk:** Violation of SEBI (Prohibition of Insider Trading) Regulations and potential criminal liability under the IT Act 2000.\n*   **Reputational Risk:** Market volatility and loss of investor trust.\n*   **Data Leakage Vector:** Social media platforms bypass internal Data Loss Prevention (DLP) controls (e.g., Forcepoint/Microsoft Purview) as the content was likely posted from a personal device or an unmonitored web session.\n\n### 2. Mandatory Security Controls & Remediation\nTo contain the fallout and prevent recurrence, the following controls are mandated:\n*   **Identity & Access Management:** Immediate revocation of the associate’s active directory (AD) credentials and suspension of O365/Teams access via **Microsoft Entra ID (formerly Azure AD)**.\n*   **Endpoint Forensics:** Remote forensic imaging of the associate’s issued laptop via **CrowdStrike Falcon Real Time Response (RTR)** to determine if the data was exfiltrated from Cognizant’s secure VDI (Virtual Desktop Infrastructure).\n*   **DLP Enforcement:** Trigger a retrospective scan across the associate’s OneDrive and SharePoint logs using **Microsoft Purview** to identify the source file accessed.\n*   **MDM Lock:** Ensure the device is marked as "Non-Compliant" in **Microsoft Intune** to prevent further synchronization with corporate resources.\n\n### 3. Relevant Standards & Compliance\n*   **DPDP Act 2023:** As a Data Fiduciary, Cognizant is required to ensure the integrity and confidentiality of processed data; this breach highlights a failure in the "Duty of Care."\n*   **IT Act 2000 (Section 43A):** Failure to maintain "reasonable security practices" regarding sensitive corporate/financial data.\n*   **ISO 27001 (Annex A.7.2.2):** Information security awareness, education, and training of employees.\n*   **Cognizant CISO Mandate:** Zero-tolerance policy for the unauthorized dissemination of MNPI on external social channels.\n\n### 4. Risk Rating: CRITICAL\n**Justification:** The disclosure involves financial information that directly impacts market valuation. It exposes the organization to regulatory audits, shareholder litigation, and potential de-listing risks if the breach is classified as systemic.\n\n### 5. 48-72 Hour Action Plan\n\n| Timeframe | Action Item | Responsibility |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **0-12 Hours** | Suspend all corporate access for the associate. Issue a "Cease and Desist" notice via Legal. | IT Security / Legal |\n| **12-24 Hours** | Capture volatile memory and logs from the associate\'s laptop via CrowdStrike RTR. Verify if data originated from Cognizant servers. | SOC / Forensics Team |\n| **24-48 Hours** | Coordinate with LinkedIn to remove the post. Conduct a "Data Breach Impact Assessment" as per DPDP Act requirements. | Legal / Corporate Comms |\n| **48-72 Hours** | Initiate internal disciplinary proceedings. Present a "Root Cause Analysis" (RCA) to the Board and update internal DLP policies to block LinkedIn/Social media uploads for specific high-access roles. | HR / CISO Office |\n\n**Authoritative Directive:** All delivery managers are reminded that any data pertaining to financial performance, client contracts, or internal strategy is strictly classified as **"Cognizant Confidential."** Unauthorized posting is a terminable offense. \n\n**Report any suspicious activity or accidental disclosures immediately to the Global Security Operations Center (GSOC).**'}
