2026-07-10 01:53:42 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 01:53:42 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Social_Media_Agent\nAs the Head of Social Media & Digital Reputation for Cognizant India, I have established the following framework to manage a crisis scenario involving a viral negative post (e.g., allegations of mass layoffs or toxic workplace culture).\n\n---\n\n### 1. Risk Assessment: The "Viral" Threshold\n*   **Current Status:** Assuming a post alleging systemic workplace issues has gained 500+ reactions and 100+ comments in the first 2 hours.\n*   **Viral Spread Estimation:** **High (>10K mentions in 24 hours).**\n*   **Rationale:** LinkedIn’s algorithm favors high-velocity engagement. If not addressed within the "Golden Hour," the narrative shifts from individual complaint to corporate trend.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Drafted Responses\n\n#### **For X (Twitter) – Priority: Containment & Directing to Support**\n*   **Draft:** "We are aware of the concerns raised regarding our workplace practices. Cognizant takes all feedback seriously and is currently reviewing the situation internally. We encourage anyone with specific concerns to reach out to our Ethics & Compliance team at [email/portal]. Transparency is our priority." (268 characters)\n\n#### **For LinkedIn – Priority: Professionalism & Accountability**\n*   **Draft:** "At Cognizant, our associates are our greatest strength, and we are committed to fostering a culture of respect, inclusion, and professional growth. We are aware of the recent discussions regarding [Topic] and are taking these concerns very seriously. We are conducting a thorough internal review to ensure our policies align with our values. We remain dedicated to supporting our people and maintaining a workplace where everyone can thrive. We encourage our associates to utilize our internal channels, including our Open Door policy and Ethics Helpline, so we can address concerns directly and effectively." (680 characters)\n\n---\n\n### 3. IT Rules 2021 (Intermediary Guidelines) Compliance\n*   **Reporting Protocol:** I will trigger a report to LinkedIn’s Legal/Safety team under **Rule 3(2)(b)** of the IT Rules 2021 if the content contains:\n    *   Defamatory or libelous claims based on falsified documents.\n    *   Threats of physical violence against employees or leadership.\n    *   Doxing (sharing private contact information of HR/leadership).\n*   **Action:** If the post violates these, we will flag it via the "Report Content" tool, citing "Harassment/Defamation" and referencing the specific violation of the IT Rules regarding the protection of corporate and individual digital reputation.\n\n---\n\n### 4. 24-Hour Social Media Monitoring Action Plan\n\n| Timeframe | Action Item | Success Metric |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **0-2 Hours** | **Triage:** Identify if the post is a PR bot attack or genuine employee grievance. | Sentiment score (Positive/Neutral/Negative). |\n| **2-4 Hours** | **Engagement:** Deploy the prepared LinkedIn/X responses. Do not delete comments unless they violate platform policy. | Engagement Rate; Growth of negative sentiment. |\n| **4-8 Hours** | **Social Listening:** Use Brandwatch/Sprinklr to track cross-platform spread (Reddit/Blind/Twitter). | Volume of mentions (Target: <5% increase/hr). |\n| **8-16 Hours** | **Internal Alignment:** Coordinate with HR/Legal to draft a formal statement if the story is picked up by media outlets (e.g., Economic Times/Moneycontrol). | Media pickup tracking. |\n| **16-24 Hours** | **Resolution:** Close the loop by posting a follow-up if appropriate or shifting focus to positive company initiatives to dilute the negative search results. | Sentiment recovery percentage. |\n\n**Monitoring Tools:**\n*   **Sprinklr:** For centralized listening across X, LinkedIn, and Glassdoor.\n*   **Brandwatch:** For identifying the "influencer" nodes spreading the narrative.\n*   **Glassdoor/Indeed:** Monitor for a spike in 1-star reviews; trigger "Employer Response" templates for any reviews that mention the viral post topic specifically.'}
