2026-07-10 01:53:42 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 01:53:42 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from HR_Safety_Agent\nAs the Head of HR for Cognizant India, I am addressing this situation with the gravity it requires. The unauthorized disclosure of financial information is a severe breach of the **Cognizant Code of Conduct** and the **Global Information Security Policy (GISP)**. \n\nBelow is the structured approach to handling this disciplinary procedure in alignment with our internal governance frameworks.\n\n### 1. Impact Assessment & Classification\n*   **Affected Associate:** Senior Delivery Manager (M3/M4 grade level).\n*   **Risk Profile:** High. This constitutes a "Major Misconduct" under the Cognizant Disciplinary Policy.\n*   **Immediate Action:** The associate must be placed on **Administrative Leave (Suspension)** pending a formal investigation to prevent further data exposure.\n*   **Communication:** A restricted-access communication will be sent to the Associate Relations (AR) team, the Business Unit (BU) Head, and the Legal/Compliance department. No information will be shared with the wider project team to maintain confidentiality and avoid speculation.\n\n### 2. HR Process & Investigation (Workday/iHR)\n*   **Case Initiation:** Log the incident in the **Workday HRMS** under the "Employee Relations" module. Open an investigation case titled "Data Privacy Breach - [Associate ID]."\n*   **Investigation:** The internal investigation team (comprising HR Business Partners and Global Security) will conduct a fact-finding mission, reviewing access logs, email trails, and system audit logs.\n*   **Disciplinary Action:** If the breach is confirmed, the process will follow the **Cognizant Disciplinary Action Policy**, which includes:\n    *   Issuance of a Show Cause Notice (SCN) via the iHR portal.\n    *   Opportunity for the associate to provide a written explanation.\n    *   Final determination by the Disciplinary Committee (ranging from a formal warning to separation for cause).\n\n### 3. Asset & Access Revocation (IT/ServiceNow)\n*   **Immediate Revocation:** Raise an emergency request via the **ServiceNow \'Security/Access\' portal** to immediately revoke all project-specific and financial system access (SAP/ERP) for the associate.\n*   **Hardware Retrieval:** If the associate is remote, coordinate with the **Asset Management Team** to facilitate a secure return of the laptop and peripheral devices as per the \'Offboarding/Suspension\' protocol.\n\n### 4. Internal Communication Memo Template\n*This memo is strictly for the internal stakeholders involved in the investigation.*\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** CONFIDENTIAL: Disciplinary Investigation – [Associate Name/ID]\n\n**Dear [Stakeholder Name],**\n\nThis email serves to formally notify you that an investigation has been initiated regarding [Associate Name], [Grade: M3/M4], following a potential breach of Cognizant’s financial data confidentiality protocols.\n\nIn accordance with our Code of Conduct, the associate has been placed on administrative leave effective [Date] while we conduct a thorough review. Please ensure that all project-related access for the individual is suspended immediately.\n\nWe request your strict adherence to confidentiality regarding this matter. Any inquiries from team members or external parties should be redirected to the HRBP team without comment. Further updates will be provided once the investigation concludes.\n\nRegards,\n\n**[Your Name]**\nHead of Human Resources, Cognizant India\n\n***\n\n### 5. Compliance & Policy References\n*   **Cognizant Code of Conduct:** Section on "Protecting Company Assets and Information."\n*   **iHR Portal:** Refer to the "Policy Library" for the *Data Privacy and Information Security Policy*.\n*   **Legal Standing:** This action is consistent with our contractual obligations regarding **Intellectual Property (IP) protection** and the **Information Technology Act, 2000** (India), which governs the unauthorized access and disclosure of sensitive data.\n\n**Next Steps:** I will monitor the case in Workday and provide a summary report to the Global Compliance Office once the evidence review is complete. Please ensure no further documentation is shared via unsecured channels.'}
