2026-07-10 01:53:46 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow: {"type": "AI", "text": "### Executive Action Summary: Unauthorized Q3 Earnings Disclosure\n\n**Date:** Friday, 10 July 2026 | **Time:** 02:15 am IST  \n**Subject:** Emergency Response to Material Non-Public Information (MNPI) Leak via LinkedIn\n\n---\n\n### ### 1. Regulatory & Compliance (SEBI/LODR)\nThe premature disclosure of Q3 earnings constitutes a severe violation of **SEBI (Listing Obligations and Disclosure Requirements) Regulations, 2015** (Regulation 30) and **SEBI (Prohibition of Insider Trading) Regulations, 2015**. \n*   **Action Required:** Immediate filing of a \"Clarification\" disclosure to the BSE/NSE is mandatory under Regulation 30 to mitigate market rumors and potential allegations of selective disclosure.\n*   **Risk:** Failure to act exposes the firm to penalties up to **INR 25 Crores** or three times the profit/loss avoided, under Section 15G of the SEBI Act.\n\n### ### 2. Security & Forensics (CISO Office)\nThe breach involves a failure of data loss prevention (DLP) controls.\n*   **Immediate Action:** IT Security has revoked the associate's AD credentials via **Microsoft Entra ID**. \n*   **Forensics:** **CrowdStrike Falcon RTR** is currently imaging the associate’s laptop to determine if the data was exfiltrated from the secure VDI. All access to SAP/ERP systems has been terminated via **ServiceNow**.\n\n### ### 3. Legal & Disciplinary (HR/Legal)\nThe associate (Senior Delivery Manager) has committed a \"Major Misconduct\" under the **Cognizant Code of Conduct** and **Information Technology Act, 2000 (Section 72A)**.\n*   **Status:** Associate is placed on **Immediate Administrative Leave** pending investigation. \n*   **Legal Action:** A \"Cease and Desist\" notice is being prepared to prevent further dissemination. We are evaluating filing an FIR under the IT Act for unauthorized disclosure of sensitive data.\n\n### ### 4. PR & Digital Reputation (Corporate Comms)\nThe viral LinkedIn post (800+ likes) poses a **Critical (8/10)** reputational risk.\n*   **Containment:** The Social Media team is using **Sprinklr** to monitor sentiment and has drafted a holding statement for the BSE disclosure.\n*   **Action:** We are flagging the content to LinkedIn’s legal team under **Rule 3(2)(b) of the IT Rules 2021** for violating corporate confidentiality and market integrity policies.\n\n---\n\n### STATUS: CRITICAL BREACH / UNDER INVESTIGATION\n**NEXT STEPS:**\n\n1.  **Regulatory Filing (Owner: Compliance/Legal):** Submit formal clarification to BSE/NSE by 09:00 am IST today (T+0).\n2.  **Forensic Evidence (Owner: CISO/SOC):** Complete forensic report on data exfiltration source by 02:00 pm IST.\n3.  **Disciplinary Hearing (Owner: HRBP):** Issue Show Cause Notice (SCN) via iHR portal by 04:00 pm IST.\n4.  **Media/Investor Management (Owner: Corporate Comms):** Monitor ET/Mint for market impact; prepare talking points for the investor relations team by 09:00 am IST.\n5.  **Board Notification (Owner: Office of the CoS):** Brief the Audit Committee on the internal control failure by end-of-day today."}
