2026-07-10 01:55:35 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 01:55:35 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff', 'HR_Safety_Agent'], 'text': ''}
2026-07-10 01:55:35 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 01:55:35 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from HR_Safety_Agent\nAs Head of Human Resources, I have reviewed the situation regarding the unauthorized disclosure of Q3 earnings on a public social media platform. This is a critical breach of our **Code of Business Conduct (COBC)** and confidentiality agreements.\n\n### 1. Impact Assessment\n*   **Affected Headcount:** The Senior Delivery Manager (SDM) at the **M3/M4 grade level**.\n*   **Risk Profile:** This constitutes a potential violation of SEBI (LODR) regulations regarding insider trading/material non-public information (MNPI) and a severe breach of Cognizant’s confidentiality policy.\n*   **Communications:** \n    *   **Immediate:** Formal "Notice to Appear" for a fact-finding meeting.\n    *   **Follow-up:** Communication to the internal Compliance and Legal teams.\n\n### 2. CognizantOne Social Media Policy & Inquiry Process\nUnder the **CognizantOne Associate Experience framework**, all associates are bound by the "Social Media Guidelines." Specifically:\n*   **Policy Violation:** Associates are strictly prohibited from discussing financial performance, client-specific data, or internal strategy on public forums prior to official corporate disclosure.\n*   **Inquiry Process:** \n    *   **Workday Action:** Initiate a "Disciplinary Case" file under the \'Performance/Conduct\' module in Workday HRMS.\n    *   **Evidence Collection:** HR must secure screenshots and timestamps of the post.\n    *   **Fact-Finding:** Conduct a formal interview with the SDM to determine intent. If willful, this proceeds to the **Disciplinary Action Committee (DAC)** for potential separation or severe reprimand.\n\n### 3. Asset & Access Management\nPending the inquiry, we must mitigate further risk:\n*   **IT Access:** Raise a request via **ServiceNow** for "Temporary Restricted Access" to the SDM’s corporate credentials to prevent further dissemination of sensitive data.\n*   **Asset Recovery:** Should the inquiry result in termination, the **Offboarding Workflow** in Workday must be triggered immediately to initiate the retrieval of the NHOK assets (Laptop, RSA Token, ID Badge).\n\n### 4. Internal Communication Template (For HR/Management)\n\n***\n\n**Subject: INTERNAL NOTICE: Fact-Finding Inquiry – [Associate Name/Emp ID]**\n\n**Dear [Associate Name],**\n\nIt has been brought to the attention of the HR and Compliance teams that a recent social media post originating from your account references Cognizant’s Q3 financial performance prior to the official company-wide release.\n\nAs an associate at the [M3/M4] level, you are aware of our strict adherence to the Code of Business Conduct (COBC) and our legal obligations regarding the protection of material non-public information. This post constitutes a potential violation of our Social Media Policy and internal confidentiality standards.\n\nYou are hereby requested to attend a fact-finding meeting to discuss this matter:\n\n*   **Date:** [Date]\n*   **Time:** [Time]\n*   **Location/Link:** [Conference Room/MS Teams Link]\n*   **Attendees:** HR Business Partner, Legal Counsel, and [Department Head].\n\nPlease be advised that this is a formal inquiry. You are expected to provide a statement regarding the circumstances of the post. Failure to comply or participate in this inquiry may lead to further disciplinary action, up to and including termination of employment.\n\nRegards,\n\n**[Your Name]**\nHead of Human Resources, Cognizant India\n\n***\n\n### 5. HR Tools Reference\n*   **Workday HRMS:** All records of this inquiry, including the initial notice and the final outcome (DAC decision), must be uploaded to the associate’s \'Documents\' tab in Workday for audit trail purposes.\n*   **iHR Portal:** Refer to the "Policy Library" under the \'Compliance\' tab to ensure the specific section on \'Financial Disclosure\' is cited in the final disciplinary letter.'}
