2026-07-10 01:55:35 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 01:55:35 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from PR_Comms_Agent\nThis situation requires immediate, high-touch communication to maintain investor confidence and regulatory compliance. As Head of Corporate Communications, my priority is to contain speculation while ensuring we remain in lockstep with the BSE/NSE disclosure requirements.\n\n### 1. Reputational Risk Assessment\n**Risk Level: 8/10**\n*   **Justification:** A premature earnings leak is a significant regulatory breach that invites scrutiny from SEBI and the SEC. It undermines investor trust, invites volatility in stock price, and suggests potential internal control failures. Immediate, transparent, and firm action is required to prevent it from being perceived as a systemic governance issue.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Holding Statement (For Media Inquiries)\n"Cognizant is aware of reports regarding a premature disclosure of our Q3 financial results and is currently investigating the source of this unauthorized information. We are working closely with regulatory authorities, including the BSE, to ensure full compliance and maintain the integrity of our disclosure process. Cognizant will provide further updates during our scheduled earnings call on [Date/Time] and has no further comment at this time."\n\n---\n\n### 3. Press Release (AP Style)\n\n**FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE**\n\n**Cognizant Addresses Unauthorized Disclosure of Q3 Financial Information**\n\n**BENGALURU – [Date]** – Cognizant (Nasdaq: CTSH) today addressed reports concerning the premature circulation of its third-quarter financial results. The company has launched an internal investigation into the matter and is cooperating fully with the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) and relevant regulatory bodies.\n\nCognizant maintains rigorous internal controls regarding financial reporting and takes the security of non-public material information with the utmost seriousness. The company remains committed to transparency and will host its scheduled earnings conference call at [Time] to discuss the Q3 results in detail. \n\nNo further information will be provided until the official earnings release.\n\n# # #\n\n**About Cognizant:**\nCognizant (Nasdaq: CTSH) engineers modern businesses. We help our clients modernize technology, reimagine processes and transform experiences so they can stay ahead in our fast-changing world. Together, we’re improving everyday life. See how at www.cognizant.com or @cognizant.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Media Monitoring Strategy\nWe will deploy a 24/7 monitoring task force focused on:\n*   **Economic Times (Tech/Markets):** To monitor market sentiment and analyst speculation.\n*   **Mint:** To track regulatory reporting and institutional investor feedback.\n*   **ET Now & NDTV Profit:** To manage the narrative on live television, ensuring the "investigation" angle remains the primary focus to prevent "leak" from becoming "malfeasance."\n\n---\n\n### 5. CEO Internal Town Hall Talking Points\n\n*   **Acknowledge and Validate:** "I want to address the reports regarding our Q3 earnings. I know this creates uncertainty, and I want to be clear: we are taking this very seriously."\n*   **Emphasize Integrity:** "Integrity is the bedrock of Cognizant. We are conducting a thorough investigation to understand how this happened and to prevent it from recurring. Our internal controls are designed to protect our reputation, and we are holding ourselves to that standard."\n*   **Focus on the Business:** "While we manage this process, our primary focus remains on the exceptional work you are doing for our clients. Let’s stay focused on our Q4 goals and continue to deliver the value our clients expect from us."\n*   **Media Protocol:** "If approached by external parties or media, please do not comment. Direct all inquiries to the Corporate Communications team. This ensures we speak with one voice and remain compliant with our regulatory obligations."'}
