2026-07-10 01:55:35 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 01:55:35 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Social_Media_Agent\nAs the Head of Social Media & Digital Reputation for Cognizant India, I have assessed the situation regarding the Q3 earnings leak. Given the sensitivity of financial data and market regulations (SEBI/SEC compliance), this is a critical incident.\n\n### 1. Social Media Risk Assessment\n*   **Risk Level:** **High (>10K mentions in 24 hours).**\n*   **Rationale:** Earnings leaks trigger algorithmic trading, retail investor panic, and institutional scrutiny. Financial news bots and aggregators will amplify this across X and LinkedIn, creating a "firestorm" effect.\n*   **Reputation Impact:** Severe. It triggers questions regarding internal controls, data security, and fiduciary responsibility.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Action Plan: Takedown & Mitigation (24-Hour)\n\n**A. Legal & Compliance (Takedown Request)**\n*   **Immediate Action:** Issue a formal "Cease and Desist" to the platform (LinkedIn/X) citing **IT Rules 2021 (Rule 3(1)(b))**.\n*   **Legal Basis:** The content contains "Confidential/Proprietary Information" and "Material Non-Public Information (MNPI)" which violates platform terms regarding illegal acts and potential market manipulation.\n*   **Reporting:** Use the "Report Content" tool under "Intellectual Property/Confidential Information" and follow up with a direct email to the platform’s legal compliance desk.\n\n**B. Social Media Monitoring Action Plan**\n*   **0-2 Hours:** Activate "Crisis Mode" on Sprinklr/Brandwatch. Filter mentions by "Earnings," "Leak," "Cognizant," and "Q3."\n*   **2-6 Hours:** Deploy the "Hold Statement" (see below). Monitor for bot-driven amplification.\n*   **6-24 Hours:** Engage with Tier-1 financial journalists to ensure the official statement is the primary source of truth. Ignore speculative threads; do not engage in back-and-forth in comments.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Draft Communications\n\n#### **X (Twitter) - Official Statement (250 characters)**\n"We are aware of unauthorized posts regarding our Q3 financial data. We are investigating the source and have notified relevant authorities. Please rely only on official Cognizant channels for verified financial information. #Cognizant #Q3Update"\n\n#### **LinkedIn - Official Statement (Professional/Formal)**\n"Cognizant is aware of unauthorized information circulating online regarding our Q3 earnings. We take data integrity and our obligations to our shareholders and the market with the utmost seriousness. \n\nWe are currently investigating the matter and have initiated our standard incident response protocols. We urge our community and stakeholders to exercise caution and rely solely on official communications and SEC/market filings for accurate financial data. We remain committed to transparency and will provide further updates through our official Investor Relations portal as appropriate. \n\nThank you for your continued trust."\n\n---\n\n### 4. IT Rules 2021 Compliance Check\n*   **Applicability:** Under the IT (Intermediary Guidelines and Digital Media Ethics Code) Rules 2021, platforms are required to remove content that is "patently false and untrue" or violates intellectual property within 72 hours.\n*   **Reporting:** Since this involves potential financial fraud/market manipulation, I will flag this under **"Harmful to the financial interests of the entity"** and **"Unauthorised disclosure of confidential information."** \n*   **Evidence:** Maintain screenshots of the original post, the timestamp, and the URL to provide to the Cyber Cell/Platform legal team as evidence of the breach.\n\n### 5. Engagement Strategy\n*   **Community Management:** Set all official social accounts to "Limited Comment Mode" for 24 hours to prevent the spread of misinformation in the comment sections.\n*   **Influencer/Employee Policy:** Issue a mandatory internal memo to all employees via the intranet: *"Do not comment, share, or speculate on the earnings leak on personal social media accounts. Refer all inquiries to Investor Relations."*'}
