2026-07-10 01:55:36 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 01:55:36 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Cyber_Security_Agent\n**To:** Cognizant Executive Leadership / Global Security Operations Center (GSOC)\n**From:** Office of the CISO, Cognizant India\n**Subject:** Security Incident Investigation: Unauthorized Disclosure of Q3 Earnings Data\n\n### 1. Risk Assessment\nThis incident represents a **Critical Information Security Breach**. The unauthorized disclosure of Q3 earnings data (non-public, material information) constitutes a violation of the **Insider Trading Policy** and the **Cognizant Code of Business Conduct**. From an IT security perspective, this suggests a failure in Data Loss Prevention (DLP) controls, potential unauthorized exfiltration from secure environments (SharePoint/OneDrive), and a failure of the \'Need-to-Know\' access principle.\n\n### 2. Mandatory Security Controls & Forensic Requirements\nTo contain the leak and identify the forensic trail, the following controls are mandatory:\n*   **Microsoft Purview/DLP Audit:** Immediate extraction of audit logs from Microsoft 365 to track the user’s access history to the specific earnings files.\n*   **CrowdStrike Falcon Horizon/Insight:** Review of endpoint activity logs on the Senior Delivery Manager’s (SDM) workstation to identify file movement (USB transfer, cloud sync, or print-to-PDF activity).\n*   **Intune MDM/MAM:** If the post was made via mobile, initiate a remote compliance check to ensure the device is not jailbroken and verify the integrity of the Managed App environment.\n*   **CyberArk Privileged Session Management (PSM):** If the SDM accessed these files via a Jump Server, review the session recordings to determine if the data was exported through non-standard channels.\n\n### 3. Regulatory & Compliance Framework\n*   **DPDP Act 2023:** As this involves internal data handling, we are obligated to ensure that the processing of such data adheres to the fiduciary duties defined under the Act.\n*   **IT Act 2000 (Section 43A):** Failure to maintain "reasonable security practices" for sensitive corporate information exposes Cognizant to legal liability.\n*   **ISO 27001 (Annex A.7.2.2):** Violation of Information Security Awareness and Training protocols.\n*   **Cognizant CISO Mandate:** Strict enforcement of the *Information Classification and Handling Policy*.\n\n### 4. Risk Rating: CRITICAL\n**Justification:** The leak involves material non-public information (MNPI), which carries severe legal, financial, and reputational consequences. There is a high risk of market manipulation and regulatory scrutiny from SEBI (Securities and Exchange Board of India) and global financial watchdogs.\n\n### 5. 48-72 Hour Action Plan\n\n| Timeline | Action Item | Responsibility |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **0-12 Hours** | **Containment:** Disable the SDM’s Active Directory account and revoke all O365/Azure tokens. Issue a formal "Preservation of Evidence" notice to the employee. | GSOC / IAM Team |\n| **12-24 Hours** | **Forensic Imaging:** Capture a forensic image of the SDM’s workstation and mobile device. Analyze browser history and local cache for evidence of data exfiltration. | Digital Forensics Team |\n| **24-48 Hours** | **DLP Correlation:** Cross-reference the timestamp of the LinkedIn post with Microsoft Purview logs to identify the exact file accessed and the egress point. | DLP/Compliance Team |\n| **48-72 Hours** | **Reporting:** Compile a formal Incident Report for the CISO and Legal/HR. Prepare a disclosure statement for regulatory bodies if required by Legal Counsel. | CISO Office / Legal |\n\n**Directives:**\n1.  **Immediate action:** The workstation must be isolated from the network via CrowdStrike\'s "Network Contain" feature to prevent further data movement.\n2.  **Legal Coordination:** The Legal department must be looped in immediately to handle the LinkedIn takedown request via formal legal channels, bypassing standard user reporting.\n3.  **Zero-Tolerance:** As this involves potential insider trading, this case is escalated to the highest level of internal disciplinary review.\n\n**CISO Representative, Cognizant India**\n*Security is a collective responsibility. Protect Cognizant.*'}
