2026-07-10 01:55:36 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 01:55:36 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Regulatory_Agent\n**MEMORANDUM**\n\n**TO:** Board of Directors / Disclosure Committee\n**FROM:** Chief Compliance Officer, Cognizant India\n**SUBJECT:** Preliminary Assessment of Premature Disclosure of Q3 Earnings (Price Sensitive Information)\n\n---\n\n### 1. Applicable Regulatory Framework\n*   **SEBI (Listing Obligations and Disclosure Requirements) Regulations, 2015 (LODR):** Specifically Regulation 30 (Disclosure of Material Events) and Schedule III, Part A.\n*   **SEBI (Prohibition of Insider Trading) Regulations, 2015 (PIT):** Regulation 3 (Communication of UPSI) and Regulation 4 (Trading when in possession of UPSI).\n*   **Companies Act, 2013:** Section 128 (Books of Account) and Section 143 (Auditor’s duties).\n*   **SEBI Circular No. SEBI/HO/CFD/CFD-PoD-1/P/CIR/2023/123:** Regarding the verification of market rumors and timely disclosures.\n\n### 2. Regulatory Breach Analysis\nThe premature disclosure of Q3 earnings 72 hours prior to the official BSE filing constitutes a **violation of the "Fair Disclosure" code** and **selective disclosure of Unpublished Price Sensitive Information (UPSI)**.\n\n*   **LODR Regulation 30(1):** Requires the listed entity to disclose all events/information to the stock exchange *first*, before releasing it to the public or media.\n*   **LODR Regulation 30(11):** Mandates that the listed entity must ensure that no information is leaked, and if leaked, it must be disseminated to the stock exchanges immediately.\n*   **PIT Regulation 3(1):** Prohibits the communication of UPSI except for legitimate purposes, performance of duties, or discharge of legal obligations.\n\n### 3. Mandatory Reporting Timelines & Requirements\n*   **Immediate Disclosure (SEBI LODR Reg 30):** Any material event, including financial results, must be disclosed to the Stock Exchanges within **30 minutes** of the conclusion of the Board Meeting.\n*   **Breach Notification:** Under the PIT Regulations, the company must initiate an internal investigation immediately upon discovery of the leak and inform the SEBI within the prescribed reporting mechanism if a formal investigation reveals a systemic lapse.\n\n### 4. GST Implications\n*   **Service Classification:** IT Services provided by Cognizant fall under **SAC 9983**.\n*   **GST Rate:** **18%** (CGST 9% + SGST 9% for intra-state; IGST 18% for inter-state).\n*   *Note:* While this specific breach is a regulatory/securities matter, any penalties paid to SEBI are generally not considered \'input services\' and are not eligible for Input Tax Credit (ITC) under Section 17(5) of the CGST Act, 2017.\n\n### 5. Potential Penalties\nUnder the **SEBI Act, 1992 (as amended by the Finance Act, 2021)**:\n*   **Section 15A:** Penalty for failure to furnish information/return can extend to **\u20b91 Lakh for each day** during which such failure continues, or **\u20b91 Crore**, whichever is less.\n*   **Section 15HB:** Penalty for contravention of any provision where no separate penalty is provided can extend up to **\u20b91 Crore**.\n*   **Adjudication:** SEBI may impose "debarment" on key managerial personnel (KMPs) or the company from the securities market for a specified period.\n\n---\n\n### 6. COMPLIANCE STATUS: BREACH\n\n**Action Required:**\n1.  **Immediate Filing:** File a \'Clarification/Confirmation\' with BSE/NSE under Regulation 30(11) within **2 hours** of this report to address the "leak" and provide the official Q3 results to ensure a level playing field.\n2.  **Internal Audit:** Initiate an investigation under the **Code of Practices and Procedures for Fair Disclosure of UPSI** (as required by PIT Regulations).\n3.  **Insider Trading Window:** Ensure the trading window for Designated Persons remains closed until 48 hours after the information becomes public.\n4.  **Reporting:** Submit a preliminary report to the SEBI Regional Office within **24 hours** detailing the cause of the premature disclosure and the remedial measures taken.\n\n**DEADLINE FOR FILING:** Immediate (Within 2 hours of discovery).\n\n**Disclaimer:** *This report is for internal compliance purposes and does not constitute external legal advice. As CCO, I recommend immediate engagement with our external legal counsel for formal representation before SEBI.*'}
