2026-07-10 01:55:39 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow: {"type": "AI", "text": "### Executive Action Summary: Unauthorized Q3 Earnings Disclosure\n\n**Date:** 10 July 2026 | **Time:** 02:45 am IST\n**Incident:** Unauthorized disclosure of MNPI (Q3 Earnings) by a Senior Delivery Manager (M3/M4 level) on LinkedIn.\n**Risk Status:** **CRITICAL**\n\n---\n\n### ### Cyber Security & Forensic Containment\n*   **Action:** Immediate \"Network Containment\" of the SDM’s workstation via CrowdStrike Falcon. All Active Directory, O365, and Azure tokens have been revoked.\n*   **Forensics:** Forensic imaging of the device is underway to identify the exfiltration path (USB/Cloud Sync/Screenshot).\n*   **DLP Audit:** Microsoft Purview logs are being correlated against the post timestamp to confirm the specific files accessed.\n\n### ### Regulatory & Compliance (SEBI/BSE)\n*   **Breach:** Violation of SEBI (LODR) Regulation 30(11) and PIT Regulations (Regulation 3).\n*   **Immediate Filing:** Compliance team is drafting a mandatory \"Clarification/Confirmation\" disclosure for the BSE/NSE to neutralize market impact. This must be filed within 2 hours of this memo.\n*   **Reporting:** A preliminary investigation report is being prepared for the SEBI Regional Office, as required by the Code of Practices and Procedures for Fair Disclosure of UPSI.\n\n### ### HR & Disciplinary Action\n*   **Status:** Formal Fact-Finding Inquiry initiated under the CognizantOne Code of Business Conduct (COBC).\n*   **Disciplinary Process:** The SDM has been issued a \"Notice to Appear\" for a formal inquiry on 10 July 2026 at 10:00 am IST. Case filed in Workday HRMS.\n*   **Outcome:** Potential for immediate suspension pending Disciplinary Action Committee (DAC) review, with termination likely due to the severity of the fiduciary breach.\n\n### ### PR & Digital Reputation\n*   **Containment:** \"Crisis Mode\" activated on social monitoring tools (Sprinklr).\n*   **Takedown:** Formal \"Cease and Desist\" submitted to LinkedIn legal desk under IT Rules 2021, Rule 3(1)(b).\n*   **Communication:** Holding statement prepared for media; all employees instructed via internal memo to refrain from commenting or sharing.\n\n### ### Legal Exposure\n*   **Risk:** High probability of SEBI adjudication under Section 15G (Penalty up to INR 25 Crores). \n*   **Action:** Engaging external legal counsel to represent the company in potential regulatory hearings. Ensuring the \"Insider Trading Window\" remains closed for all Designated Persons.\n\n---\n\n**STATUS: ESCALATED**\n\n**NEXT STEPS:**\n1.  **BSE Disclosure:** Submit the official clarification to the Stock Exchange by 04:00 am IST (Owner: Compliance Officer).\n2.  **Forensic Report:** Complete the initial forensic trail of the exfiltration by 10:00 am IST (Owner: CISO).\n3.  **Fact-Finding:** Execute the disciplinary interview with the SDM at 10:00 am IST (Owner: HRBP / Legal).\n4.  **Board Briefing:** Provide a comprehensive incident report to the Board of Directors by 12:00 pm IST (Owner: Chief of Staff)."}
