2026-07-10 02:00:51 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:00:50 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'As Senior VP of Finance & Risk Management for Cognizant India, I have reviewed the advance payment request for **M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd.**\n\n### 1. Financial Risk Assessment\n*   **Gross Transaction Value:** \u20b92,32,332 (Inclusive of 18% GST).\n*   **Base Value (Excl. GST):** \u20b91,96,891.53.\n*   **GST Liability (18% on HSN 8471):** \u20b935,440.47.\n*   **Risk Profile:** High. Requesting an advance payment deviates from our standard Net-30 credit policy. Without a Bank Guarantee (BG), this creates an unsecured credit exposure. If the vendor fails to deliver the IT hardware, Cognizant faces a direct cash-out loss and potential operational downtime.\n\n### 2. Budget Head & Cost Center\n*   **Budget Head:** IT Infrastructure / Capex-Hardware.\n*   **Cost Center:** The request must be mapped to the specific Delivery Unit (DU) or Corporate IT cost center initiating the requisition. \n*   **Action:** Ensure the PO is raised in Ariba/Coupa against the approved FY24-25 IT budget. The "Advance Payment" flag must be triggered in the workflow to initiate the ETP process.\n\n### 3. Payment Terms & Compliance (ETP Required)\n*   **Deviation:** The request bypasses our standard Net-30 payment term.\n*   **Requirement:** \n    *   **Bank Guarantee (BG):** Mandatory. The vendor must provide a BG equivalent to the advance amount (\u20b92,32,332) valid until the delivery of hardware.\n    *   **Exception to Policy (ETP):** As this is a deviation from standard procurement policy, a formal ETP must be signed by the Finance Controller.\n    *   **Approval Thresholds:** Since the transaction exceeds \u20b92 Lakhs, this **requires my (VP Finance) sign-off**. If the total PO value exceeds \u20b910 Lakhs, CFO escalation is mandatory.\n\n### 4. GST & Tax Implications\n*   **Input Tax Credit (ITC):** Cognizant can claim the \u20b935,440.47 as ITC, provided the vendor uploads the invoice in GSTR-1 and it reflects in our GSTR-2B.\n*   **TDS:** Under Section 194Q (Purchase of Goods), Cognizant must ensure TDS is deducted at 0.1% on the value exceeding \u20b950 Lakhs (if applicable on the aggregate annual turnover with this vendor).\n\n### 5. FY Impact (April–March)\n*   **P&L Impact:** The expense will be recognized upon Goods Receipt (GRN). If the asset is capitalized (Capex), it will impact the P&L via depreciation over the useful life (typically 3 years for IT hardware).\n*   **Cash Flow:** Immediate outflow of \u20b92,32,332. This impacts the Q1/Q2 cash flow projection. We must ensure this is reconciled against the quarterly IT hardware budget allocation to prevent overspending.\n\n### Final Directive:\n**Recommendation:** **Conditional Approval.**\n1.  **Procurement:** Verify if the vendor has a Master Service Agreement (MSA) in place.\n2.  **Finance:** Obtain the Bank Guarantee. Without the BG, the request is **rejected**.\n3.  **Workflow:** Once the BG is provided and scanned into Ariba, route the ETP to my office for signature.\n\n*Please update the Ariba requisition with the BG reference number and attach the vendor’s formal request for advance payment before submitting for my final review.*'}
