tions\n*   **Input Tax Credit (ITC):** Cognizant can claim the \u20b935,440.47 as ITC, provided the vendor uploads the invoice in GSTR-1 and it reflects in our GSTR-2B.\n*   **TDS:** Under Section 194Q (Purchase of Goods), Cognizant must ensure TDS is deducted at 0.1% on the value exceeding \u20b950 Lakhs (if applicable on the aggregate annual turnover with this vendor).\n\n### 5. FY Impact (April–March)\n*   **P&L Impact:** The expense will be recognized upon Goods Receipt (GRN). If the asset is capitalized (Capex), it will impact the P&L via depreciation over the useful life (typically 3 years for IT hardware).\n*   **Cash Flow:** Immediate outflow of \u20b92,32,332. This impacts the Q1/Q2 cash flow projection. We must ensure this is reconciled against the quarterly IT hardware budget allocation to prevent overspending.\n\n### Final Directive:\n**Recommendation:** **Conditional Approval.**\n1.  **Procurement:** Verify if the vendor has a Master Service Agreement (MSA) in place.\n2.  **Finance:** Obtain the Bank Guarantee. Without the BG, the request is **rejected**.\n3.  **Workflow:** Once the BG is provided and scanned into Ariba, route the ETP to my office for signature.\n\n*Please update the Ariba requisition with the BG reference number and attach the vendor’s formal request for advance payment before submitting for my final review.*'}
