2026-07-10 02:00:51 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:00:51 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff', 'Cyber_Security_Agent'], 'text': ''}
2026-07-10 02:00:51 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:00:51 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Cyber_Security_Agent\nAs the CISO representative for Cognizant India, I am defining the mandatory security hardening and provisioning requirements for the 20 Dell Latitude 5540 units destined for the Chennai delivery center. \n\nFailure to adhere to these standards puts Cognizant at risk of non-compliance with the **Digital Personal Data Protection (DPDP) Act 2023** and our global **ISO 27001** certifications.\n\n### 1. Security Risk Assessment\nThe primary risks involve unauthorized data exfiltration, physical theft, and lateral movement in the event of a breach. Deploying unhardened assets creates a "shadow IT" footprint that bypasses our Zero Trust architecture, potentially exposing sensitive client data (PII/SPI) processed within the Chennai DC.\n\n### 2. Mandatory Security Controls\n*   **Asset Tagging:** All 20 units must be tagged via the **Cognizant Asset Management System (CAMS)**. Each device must have a physical tamper-evident barcode and a virtual tag registered in **Intune** for automated tracking.\n*   **Golden Image Deployment:** Deployment must utilize the standardized **Cognizant Windows 11 Enterprise Golden Image**. Custom configurations are strictly prohibited.\n*   **Endpoint Security:**\n    *   **CrowdStrike Falcon:** Must be installed and registered to the Chennai-specific tenant policy.\n    *   **Microsoft Defender for Endpoint (MDE):** Integration with the MDE portal for EDR/XDR monitoring.\n    *   **Intune MDM:** Mandatory enrollment for policy enforcement, remote wipe capability, and conditional access.\n*   **Encryption:** **BitLocker** must be enabled with XTS-AES 256-bit encryption. Recovery keys must be escrowed to **Azure AD/Entra ID** automatically.\n*   **Access Control:** **CyberArk** integration is required for local admin privilege management; no user shall have permanent local administrative rights.\n\n### 3. Standards & Regulatory Compliance\n*   **ISO 27001 (A.8.1):** Mandates inventory of assets and ownership.\n*   **India DPDP Act 2023:** Requires "reasonable security safeguards" to prevent personal data breaches.\n*   **IT Act 2000 (Section 43A):** Imposes liability on corporate entities for failure to maintain reasonable security practices for sensitive personal data.\n*   **Cognizant CISO Mandate:** All endpoints must adhere to the "Secure-by-Default" configuration policy before connecting to the corporate backbone.\n\n### 4. Risk Rating: HIGH\n**Justification:** The Chennai delivery center handles high-volume client data. Deploying 20 unverified endpoints creates a high-probability vector for data leakage or ransomware entry points if the devices are compromised before securing them.\n\n### 5. 48-72 Hour Action Plan\n\n| Timeframe | Action Item | Responsibility |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **0-12 Hours** | Physical asset tagging in CAMS and hardware verification against procurement manifest. | Chennai IT Ops |\n| **12-24 Hours** | PXE/Autopilot boot; deployment of Cognizant Golden Image via Intune. | Desktop Engineering |\n| **24-48 Hours** | Verification of CrowdStrike Falcon and MDE heartbeat in the security console. Patching to latest baseline. | Security Operations (SecOps) |\n| **48-60 Hours** | BitLocker encryption status audit and successful escrow of keys to Azure AD. | Security Compliance Team |\n| **60-72 Hours** | Final "Compliance Check" scan via Intune. Approval for delivery to end-users. | CISO Compliance Office |\n\n**Authoritative Directive:** Any device failing to report a "Compliant" status in the Intune dashboard after 72 hours must be quarantined from the corporate network until remediation. No exceptions.'}
