2026-07-10 02:00:55 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow: {"type": "AI", "text": "### Executive Action Summary: Bangalore-Chennai Procurement & Onboarding\n\n**Subject:** Emergency Procurement & Onboarding Alignment for New Client Project (Chennai Delivery Center)\n\nFollowing the urgent escalation regarding the procurement of 20 Dell Latitude 5540 laptops (₹2,32,332) from M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd., the cross-functional leadership team has reviewed the request. The project kick-off deadline of Monday, 13 July 2026, necessitates immediate action.\n\n---\n\n### ### Finance & Risk Management\n*   **Approval Status:** **Conditional Approval.**\n*   **Advance Payment:** A deviation from the standard Net-30 credit policy is permitted solely if the vendor provides a **Bank Guarantee (BG)** equal to the advance amount (₹2,32,332).\n*   **Compliance:** The ETP (Exception to Policy) form must be filed in Ariba. The transaction is subject to Section 194Q TDS compliance and verification of the vendor's MSME status under the MSMED Act, 2006.\n*   **Owner:** Finance Controller, Cognizant India.\n\n### ### Supply Chain & Logistics\n*   **Operational Status:** **High Risk.**\n*   **Logistics:** Standard lead time is 5–7 days. To meet the 3-day deadline, the vendor must initiate \"Priority Dispatch\" via Blue Dart Air-Express.\n*   **Asset Lifecycle:** Upon arrival at the Chennai delivery center, the warehouse must execute a GRN via transaction `MIGO` immediately. All serial numbers must be updated in ServiceNow (CMDB) within 24 hours of receipt.\n*   **Owner:** Procurement Manager (Bangalore/Chennai).\n\n### ### Cyber Security & Compliance\n*   **Security Status:** **Mandatory Hardening.**\n*   **Directives:** No device shall be connected to the corporate network until the 72-hour security hardening sequence is completed (CrowdStrike, Intune enrollment, BitLocker encryption, and Golden Image deployment). Failure to meet \"Compliant\" status in the Intune dashboard will trigger an automatic quarantine.\n*   **Regulatory:** Adherence to the **Digital Personal Data Protection (DPDP) Act 2023** and **ISO 27001** is non-negotiable.\n*   **Owner:** CISO Compliance Office / Chennai IT Ops.\n\n### ### Human Resources\n*   **Status:** **Action Required.**\n*   **Process:** The Project Manager must submit 20 individual 'New Hire IT Setup' requests via ServiceNow immediately. Workday profiles must be verified as 'Ready for Hire.'\n*   **Owner:** Project Manager / HRBP Team.\n\n---\n\n### STATUS: ESCALATED / CONDITIONAL APPROVAL\n\n### NEXT STEPS\n1.  **Procurement:** Confirm MSME status of Rashi Peripherals and secure the Bank Guarantee (BG) for ₹2,32,332 by 05:00 pm IST today. (Owner: Procurement Lead)\n2.  **Finance:** Once the BG is uploaded to Ariba, the Finance Controller will sign the ETP. (Owner: VP Finance)\n3.  **Logistics:** Coordinate \"Priority Dispatch\" with Rashi Peripherals for air-freight delivery to Chennai. (Owner: Supply Chain Lead)\n4.  **IT/Security:** Initiate the 72-hour hardening protocol in the Chennai DC immediately upon hardware arrival. (Owner: IT Operations Manager)\n5.  **Project Management:** Submit 20 ServiceNow tickets and confirm 'Ready for Hire' status in Workday. (Owner: Project Manager)"}
