each of Annex A controls (A.5.15 Access Control, A.8.7 Protection against malware).\n*   **India’s DPDP Act 2023:** As a Data Fiduciary, Cognizant is mandated to report significant data breaches to the Data Protection Board of India. Failure to contain this risk constitutes a violation of Section 8.\n*   **IT Act 2000 (Section 43A):** Failure to implement reasonable security practices resulting in wrongful loss of sensitive personal data.\n*   **Cognizant CISO Mandate:** Zero-Trust Architecture (ZTA) enforcement.\n\n### 4. Risk Rating\n**CRITICAL**\n*   **Justification:** The threat actor has demonstrated the capability to bypass standard perimeter defenses. The potential for large-scale exfiltration of sensitive client data could result in severe financial penalties, irreparable reputational damage, and loss of "Trusted Partner" status with global clients.\n\n---\n\n### 5. 72-Hour Action Plan\n\n| Timeframe | Action Item | Responsibility |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **0-12 Hours** | Complete isolation of affected network segments. Initiate full global password reset for all privileged accounts. | IAM/SOC Team |\n| **12-24 Hours** | Forensic imaging of compromised nodes. Forensic analysis of **CrowdStrike** telemetry to identify the "Patient Zero" entry point. | Incident Response |\n| **24-48 Hours** | Patching of identified vulnerabilities. Hardening of **Intune** configuration profiles to prevent further unauthorized enrollment. | Infrastructure Team |\n| **48-72 Hours** | Final verification of security posture. Submission of incident report to the Board and regulatory authorities as required by the **DPDP Act**. | CISO/Legal Counsel |\n\n**Note:** Any deviation from this protocol must be documented and signed off by the Global CISO office. We are currently operating under "Defcon 1" status.\n\n**[End of Briefing]**'}
2026-07-10 02:06:31 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:06:31 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Legal_Agent\n**LEGAL ADVISORY NOTE: BOARD ESCALATION PROTOCOLS**\n\n**TO:** Executive Leadership Team / Board of Directors\n**FROM:** Office of the Associate General Counsel, Cognizant India\n**SUBJECT:** Legal Implications of Immediate Board Escalation under Indian Corporate Law\n\n---\n\n### 1. Legal Framework & Statutory Compliance\nThe obligation to escalate matters to the Board of Directors is governed primarily by the **Companies Act, 2013** and the **SEBI (Listing Obligations and Disclosure Requirements) Regulations, 2015**.\n\n*   **Section 134 & 177 of the Companies Act, 2013:** The Board is responsible for the integrity of financial controls and risk management. Failure to escalate material breaches (e.g., systemic vendor fraud or catastrophic service delivery failures) can lead to personal liability for Directors under the "Duty of Care" doctrine.\n*   **Section 166 (Duties of Directors):** A Director must act in good faith to promote the objects of the company. Withholding material information from the Board constitutes a breach of fiduciary duty.\n*   **SEBI (LODR) Regulations, 2015 (Regulation 30):** For a publicly listed entity, the company is mandate-bound to disclose "material events" to stock exchanges. The Board must be apprised immediately to determine the materiality of any IT service delivery failure or contractual breach.\n\n### 2. Contractual & Vendor Risk Analysis\nWhen an escalation involves a vendor, we must cross-reference the **Master Service Agreement (MSA)** and the **Indian Contract Act, 1872**:\n\n*   **Section 39 (Anticipatory Breach):** If a vendor expresses an inability to perform, the Board must be apprised immediately to mitigate damages. Failure to act may waive our right to terminate for cause.\n*   **MSME Development Act, 2006:** If the vendor is an MSME and the dispute involves payment, the Board must be notified of the risk of mandatory interest (three times the bank rate) and potential public disclosure requirements.\n*   **Arbitration & Conciliation Act, 1996:** If the dispute is heading toward litigation, the Board must approve the legal strategy to avoid adverse findings that could impact our Indian balance sheet.\n\n### 3. Legal Risk Exposure (INR)\n*   **Financial Exposure:** Unmitigated contractual penalties and liquidated damages (LDs) for service non-delivery can scale into the range of **INR 50 Cr – 500 Cr+** depending on the client account size.\n*   **Regulatory Exposure:** Fines under SEBI regulations for non-disclosure can reach **INR 1 Cr – 25 Cr**, coupled with potential "debarment" or "cease and desist" orders against key management personnel (KMPs).\n*   **Reputational Risk:** Immediate Board intervention is the only mechanism to invoke "Force Majeure" or "Limitation of Liability" clauses effectively, protecting the firm’s valuation.\n\n### 4. Legal Recommendations\n1.  **Immediate Materiality Assessment:** Conduct a "Materiality Test" under the company’s internal Policy on Disclosure of Material Events.\n2.  **Formal Board Memo:** Draft a precise, factual memorandum detailing the breach, financial impact, and proposed mitigation (e.g., invoking the Dispute Resolution clause of the MSA).\n3.  **Preservation of Evidence:** Issue a "Legal Hold" notice to all relevant delivery teams to prevent spoliation of data, as per the **Indian Evidence Act, 1872**.\n4.  **Audit Trail:** Ensure all escalations are documented in the Minutes of the Meeting (MoM) to provide a "Business Judgment Rule" defense for the Board.\n\n---\n\n### **LEGAL RISK RATING: HIGH**\n\n**Advisory:** Escalation to the Board is not merely a procedural step; it is a statutory shield. In the event of a material breach, silence constitutes professional negligence. I recommend an immediate convening of the Risk Management Committee (RMC) to review the vendor\'s performance data against our MSA obligations.\n\n**Signed,**\n\n*Associate General Counsel*\n*Cognizant India*'}
2026-07-10 02:06:31 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:06:31 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'As the Head of HR for Cognizant India, I have outlined the strategic assessment and actionable framework regarding the current crisis. Our priority remains the safety and wellbeing of our associates, ensuring business continuity while maintaining the integrity of our \'CognizantOne\' associate experience.\n\n### 1. Assessment of Impact & Talent Risk\n*   **Headcount & Grades:** We are evaluating the impact across all levels (C1–C5, M1–M5). \n    *   **C1–C3:** High risk of productivity dip due to anxiety; require immediate pastoral support.\n    *   **C4–M5:** High risk of burnout; these cohorts are managing client expectations and delivery pressure.\n*   **Talent Risk:** We are utilizing **Workday’s ‘Retention Dashboard’** to identify high-potential (HiPo) associates in critical delivery centers. We must proactively address "flight risk" by emphasizing our internal mobility programs and the \'CognizantOne\' mental health resources.\n*   **Communication:** All updates must be cascaded via the **\'CognizantOne\' portal**. Direct managers are empowered to conduct "pulse check" 1-on-1s.\n\n### 2. Safety & Regulatory Compliance\nIn line with the **Factories Act, 1948** (specifically regarding workplace safety and welfare) and **Cognizant’s Occupational Safety and Health (OSH) Policy**, we are mandating the following:\n*   **Incident Reporting:** Any safety-related incident must be logged immediately via the **\'Cognizant Safety Portal\'**.\n*   **Compliance:** We are ensuring that all delivery centers are compliant with the OSH policy, including mandatory safety audits and the provision of emergency response protocols.\n*   **Wellbeing:** We are reinforcing the "Cognizant Wellbeing" module on the iHR portal, providing 24/7 access to counseling services for associates affected by the crisis.\n\n### 3. Asset Allocation (If scaling/relocating teams)\nTo ensure business continuity, if teams are shifted or new resources are onboarded:\n*   **NHOK Process:** All IT provisioning must follow the standard **ServiceNow** workflow.\n*   **Protocol:** Managers must raise the **\'New Hire IT Setup\'** catalog item in ServiceNow strictly **5 days prior** to the required date. This ensures the asset reaches the associate’s primary location or hub, preventing productivity loss.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Internal Communication Memo Template\n\n**Subject:** Standing Together: Our Commitment to Your Safety and Wellbeing\n\n**Dear Associates,**\n\nAt Cognizant, our greatest strength is our people. We are aware of the challenges posed by the current situation and want to reassure you that your safety and professional wellbeing remain our highest priority.\n\nWe are actively monitoring the situation across all delivery centers. We encourage you to utilize the resources available on the **iHR Portal**, including our dedicated wellbeing support lines and the updated OSH guidelines. \n\n**Key Actions:**\n*   **Support:** Please reach out to your People Manager for any immediate concerns. If you require further support, our HR Business Partners (HRBPs) are available via the \'HelpDesk\' feature in Workday.\n*   **Communication:** Please stay tuned to the **\'CognizantOne\'** dashboard for official updates. Please avoid relying on unverified sources.\n*   **Flexibility:** We are empowering managers to adopt flexible working arrangements where possible, ensuring that client commitments are met without compromising your personal safety.\n\nWe are in this together. Your resilience is what defines Cognizant, and we are committed to supporting you every step of the way.\n\nWarm regards,\n\n**[Your Name/Head of HR]**\n**Cognizant India**\n\n---\n\n### 5. Tools & References\n*   **Workday HRMS:** Used for tracking headcount, updating emergency contact information, and monitoring performance/retention metrics.\n*   **iHR Portal:** The centralized repository for all policy-related queries, leave management, and wellbeing resources.\n*   **ServiceNow:** The mandatory tool for all IT infrastructure requests and facility-related support tickets.'}
