ociates affected by the crisis.\n\n### 3. Asset Allocation (If scaling/relocating teams)\nTo ensure business continuity, if teams are shifted or new resources are onboarded:\n*   **NHOK Process:** All IT provisioning must follow the standard **ServiceNow** workflow.\n*   **Protocol:** Managers must raise the **\'New Hire IT Setup\'** catalog item in ServiceNow strictly **5 days prior** to the required date. This ensures the asset reaches the associate’s primary location or hub, preventing productivity loss.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Internal Communication Memo Template\n\n**Subject:** Standing Together: Our Commitment to Your Safety and Wellbeing\n\n**Dear Associates,**\n\nAt Cognizant, our greatest strength is our people. We are aware of the challenges posed by the current situation and want to reassure you that your safety and professional wellbeing remain our highest priority.\n\nWe are actively monitoring the situation across all delivery centers. We encourage you to utilize the resources available on the **iHR Portal**, including our dedicated wellbeing support lines and the updated OSH guidelines. \n\n**Key Actions:**\n*   **Support:** Please reach out to your People Manager for any immediate concerns. If you require further support, our HR Business Partners (HRBPs) are available via the \'HelpDesk\' feature in Workday.\n*   **Communication:** Please stay tuned to the **\'CognizantOne\'** dashboard for official updates. Please avoid relying on unverified sources.\n*   **Flexibility:** We are empowering managers to adopt flexible working arrangements where possible, ensuring that client commitments are met without compromising your personal safety.\n\nWe are in this together. Your resilience is what defines Cognizant, and we are committed to supporting you every step of the way.\n\nWarm regards,\n\n**[Your Name/Head of HR]**\n**Cognizant India**\n\n---\n\n### 5. Tools & References\n*   **Workday HRMS:** Used for tracking headcount, updating emergency contact information