2026-07-10 02:06:32 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:06:31 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Social_Media_Agent\nAs the Head of Social Media & Digital Reputation for Cognizant India, I am treating this request as a **High-Alert scenario**. Given our scale (2.5M LinkedIn followers), any negative sentiment can rapidly spiral into a PR crisis if left unaddressed.\n\nBelow is the strategic framework for managing a reputation-sensitive situation.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Social Media Risk Assessment\n*   **Potential Viral Spread:** **High (>10K mentions/24h).** \n    *   *Rationale:* Cognizant’s large employee base often uses LinkedIn/Twitter as a megaphone for internal grievances. Algorithmic bias in favor of "corporate controversy" means negative posts gain traction quickly among peer tech companies (TCS, Infosys, Wipro).\n*   **Sentiment Drivers:** Usually tied to layoffs, appraisal delays, return-to-office (RTO) mandates, or client-side project instability.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Draft Response Content\n\n#### **For X (Twitter) - Character Limit: 280**\n*Strategy: Direct, empathetic, and moves the conversation to private channels.*\n> "We hear the concerns being raised regarding [Specific Issue]. At Cognizant, our associates are our greatest strength. We are actively reviewing this and are committed to transparency. For specific concerns, please reach out to us at [Dedicated Email/DM]. We are listening."\n\n#### **For LinkedIn - Character Limit: 3000**\n*Strategy: Professional, values-based, and reassuring to clients/investors.*\n> "At Cognizant, we value the open dialogue within our community. We are aware of the recent discussions regarding [Issue] and want to assure our associates and stakeholders that we are addressing these matters with the seriousness they deserve. \n> \n> Our focus remains on fostering an inclusive, supportive, and high-performance culture. We are currently engaging with internal teams to ensure clarity and provide the necessary support. We encourage all associates to utilize our established feedback channels or contact their HR partners directly. Thank you for your continued dedication to our clients and our shared purpose."\n\n---\n\n### 3. IT Rules 2021 (Intermediary Guidelines) Compliance\nI will monitor for content that triggers **Rule 3(2)(b)** of the IT Rules 2021. If content contains:\n*   **Defamation, harassment, or falsehoods** that threaten the integrity of the company.\n*   **Incitement to violence or illegal acts** (e.g., threats against leadership).\n*   **Disclosure of proprietary/confidential client data.**\n\n**Action:** If these thresholds are met, I will file a **Grievance Redressal Request** directly to platform Nodal Officers (LinkedIn/X) citing the IT Rules 2021, requesting removal within 24 hours of notification.\n\n---\n\n### 4. 24-Hour Monitoring Action Plan\n\n| Timeframe | Action Item | Goal |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **0-2 Hours** | Initialize **Brandwatch/Meltwater** alerts for "Cognizant + [Issue]". | Identify the "Patient Zero" post. |\n| **2-4 Hours** | Internal alignment with HR and Legal. | Draft and approve the "holding statement." |\n| **4-8 Hours** | Deploy "Community Management" team to reply to high-engagement comments. | De-escalate via DM to prevent comment-section pile-ons. |\n| **8-16 Hours** | Monitor for "Influencer/Tech Journalist" amplification. | Brief the Corporate Comms lead if media outlets (e.g., Moneycontrol, ET) pick up the story. |\n| **16-24 Hours** | Post a "Culture/Value-focused" piece of content. | Pivot the narrative back to positive company milestones (e.g., ESG initiatives or AI innovation). |\n\n**Key Metric to Track:** **Net Sentiment Score (NSS).** If the NSS drops below -20, we trigger an "Executive Video Message" from the India MD to stabilize morale and reassure stakeholders. \n\n**Pro-tip:** Never engage in public arguments. The goal is to acknowledge, validate, and move the conversation to a non-public, controlled environment.'}
