2026-07-10 02:14:17 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:14:17 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff', 'Finance_Risk_Agent'], 'text': ''}
2026-07-10 02:14:17 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:14:17 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Finance_Risk_Agent\nAs the Senior VP of Finance & Risk Management for Cognizant India, I have reviewed the request for an advance payment exception regarding the procurement from M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd. \n\nBelow is the formal financial risk assessment and compliance review.\n\n### 1. Financial Breakdown & Tax Impact\n*   **Base Amount:** \u20b91,96,891.53\n*   **GST (18% on HSN 8471):** \u20b935,440.47\n*   **Total Gross Amount:** **\u20b92,32,332.00**\n\n### 2. Budget Head & Cost Center\n*   **Budget Head:** IT Infrastructure / Hardware Procurement (Capital Expenditure - CAPEX or Opex-Refresh depending on asset life).\n*   **Cost Center:** Must be verified against the specific Business Unit (BU) requesting the hardware. *Note: Ensure the cost center has sufficient unutilized budget for the current FY quarter.*\n\n### 3. Financial Risk Assessment & Compliance Check\n*   **Approval Threshold Status:** The amount of \u20b92,32,332 exceeds the \u20b92 Lakhs threshold for VP Finance sign-off. **Formal VP approval is mandatory.**\n*   **Payment Terms Risk:** Standard payment terms for Cognizant India are Net-30 days post-invoice validation and receipt of goods. Requesting an advance payment is a deviation from our standard Procure-to-Pay (P2P) policy.\n*   **Risk Mitigation:** \n    *   **Bank Guarantee (BG):** Per company policy, an advance payment of this magnitude requires a Bank Guarantee from M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd. for the equivalent amount to protect Cognizant against non-delivery.\n    *   **ETP Requirement:** An \'Exception to Policy\' (ETP) document must be filed in Ariba/Coupa, citing the business justification for the advance.\n*   **Counterparty Risk:** While Rashi Peripherals is a known distributor, the advance payment exposes the firm to liquidity risk if the vendor fails to fulfill the delivery timeline.\n\n### 4. FY Impact\n*   **Fiscal Year:** Cognizant India FY runs April–March.\n*   **Impact:** This expenditure will be recognized in the current quarter of the FY. If the hardware delivery is delayed beyond the current quarter, it will impact the "Goods Received Not Invoiced" (GRNI) account, necessitating a manual accrual adjustment at month-end close.\n\n### 5. Mandatory Action Items for Approval\nTo proceed with this payment, the following must be uploaded to the Ariba/Coupa portal:\n\n1.  **Justification Memo:** Detailed business rationale explaining why standard credit terms (Net-30) were not acceptable to the vendor.\n2.  **BG Documentation:** A copy of the Bank Guarantee issued in favor of Cognizant Technology Solutions India Pvt. Ltd.\n3.  **ETP Approval:** Signed ETP form approved by the respective BU Finance Lead.\n4.  **Tax Compliance:** Ensure the vendor’s GSTIN is validated on the GST portal to prevent input tax credit (ITC) denial.\n\n**Decision:** The request is **conditionally approved** subject to the submission of the Bank Guarantee and the formal ETP process. As the amount exceeds \u20b92 Lakhs, I will require the final Ariba workflow notification to apply my digital signature. \n\n**Regards,**\n\nSenior VP, Finance & Risk Management\nCognizant India'}
