2026-07-10 02:14:18 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:14:17 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from HR_Safety_Agent\nAs the Head of HR for Cognizant India, I have outlined the onboarding logistics and asset allocation protocol for the 20 new joiners at our Chennai delivery center. Adhering to our \'CognizantOne\' associate experience framework, we must ensure a seamless "Day 1" integration.\n\n### 1. Impact Assessment\n*   **Affected Headcount:** 20 Associates.\n*   **Grade Levels:** Typically C1 (Associate) to C2 (Senior Associate).\n*   **Communication:** A personalized "Welcome to Cognizant" email must be triggered via Workday, including the Chennai campus reporting instructions, dress code, and the pre-boarding digital documentation checklist.\n\n### 2. Asset Allocation & Onboarding Logistics\nTo ensure the 20 Dell laptops are ready for the Chennai batch, follow the mandatory process:\n\n*   **ServiceNow Request:** The Onboarding Coordinator must raise a request via the **ServiceNow catalog item: \'New Hire IT Setup\'**. \n*   **Lead Time:** This request **must be submitted at least 5 working days prior** to the joining date to ensure the Chennai IT Desk has sufficient time for imaging, security patching, and asset tagging.\n*   **Asset Tagging:** Ensure the asset tags are mapped to the associate’s Employee ID in the Asset Management module within our internal IT portal.\n*   **NHOK (New Hire Onboarding Kit):** The NHOK (which includes the laptop, security dongle, and Cognizant-branded welcome collateral) must be verified at the Chennai delivery center’s IT kiosk 24 hours before the arrival of the associates.\n\n### 3. Safety & Compliance\n*   **Policy:** Per our **Occupational Safety and Health (OSH) Policy**, the Chennai facility lead must ensure the workstation area designated for these 20 associates complies with the **Factories Act 1948** (provisions regarding lighting, ventilation, and ergonomic seating).\n*   **Safety Induction:** A mandatory safety briefing must be part of the Day 1 agenda, covering emergency exits, fire safety protocols, and the use of the Cognizant emergency alert system.\n\n### 4. Internal Communication Memo Template\n\n**Subject:** Welcome to Cognizant – Onboarding Logistics for Chennai Delivery Center\n\n**Dear Team,**\n\nWe are excited to welcome 20 new associates to the Chennai delivery center on [Joining Date]. To ensure a seamless onboarding experience, please note the following:\n\n*   **IT Readiness:** All 20 Dell laptops have been requested via the \'New Hire IT Setup\' ServiceNow portal. The IT team will finalize asset handover by [Date/Time].\n*   **Onboarding Agenda:** Associates are requested to report to the [Building Name/Floor] reception at 09:00 AM. \n*   **Documentation:** Please ensure all pre-boarding documents are uploaded to the **Workday** portal. Our HR team will be available at the \'CognizantOne\' helpdesk to assist with biometric registration and ID badge issuance.\n\nWe look forward to a successful onboarding day. Please reach out to the Chennai HRBP team if you require further clarification.\n\nBest regards,\n\n**Head of Human Resources**\nCognizant India\n\n### 5. Tools Reference\n*   **Workday:** For tracking onboarding status, background verification (BGV) clearance, and payroll setup.\n*   **iHR Portal:** Associates should be directed to the iHR portal for their "Associate Handbook" and benefits enrollment.\n*   **ServiceNow:** Sole channel for IT, facilities, and logistics requests.'}
