*Cognizant CISO Mandate:** Strict adherence to the "Zero Trust" architecture for all new hardware deployments.\n*   **DPDP Act 2023:** Ensures that processing of personal data occurs only on secured, audited devices to prevent unauthorized processing or leakage.\n*   **IT Act 2000 (Section 43A):** Cognizant’s legal obligation to maintain "reasonable security practices" to protect sensitive personal data.\n\n### 4. Risk Rating: HIGH\n**Justification:** While these are new assets, the "Day 0" deployment phase is the most vulnerable period. If a machine is connected to the network without MDM/CrowdStrike protection, it becomes an unmanaged node capable of lateral movement if compromised, potentially leading to a breach of client data held at the Chennai delivery center.\n\n### 5. 72-Hour Action Plan\n\n| Timeline | Action Item | Responsibility |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **0-12 Hours** | Physical audit, CAMS tagging, and BIOS/UEFI hardening (Secure Boot enabled, USB ports disabled). | IT Infrastructure Team |\n| **12-36 Hours** | PXE/SCCM Imaging with Cognizant Golden Image; push Intune enrollment profile. | Desktop Support / IT Ops |\n| **36-60 Hours** | Verification of CrowdStrike Falcon and MDE connectivity via the Security Console. Confirm BitLocker status. | Infosec/SOC Team |\n| **60-72 Hours** | Final Security Posture Audit. Validation of Conditional Access policy enforcement. Sign-off for deployment. | CISO Compliance Office |\n\n**Instruction:** Submit the final compliance report (exported from Intune/CrowdStrike) to the Chennai Site Security lead by T+72 hours. No asset is to be deployed to the floor without a "Green" status in the compliance dashboard.'}
