2026-07-10 02:14:22 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow: {"type": "AI", "text": "### Executive Action Summary: Procurement Exception for Chennai Delivery Center\n\n**DATE:** 10 July 2026 | **STATUS:** UNDER REVIEW (Awaiting Bank Guarantee & ETP)\n\nFollowing a cross-functional review regarding the request for 20 Dell Latitude 5540 laptops (Total Value: ₹2,32,332) from M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd., the following directive is issued. The request is **conditionally approved** provided the mandatory risk mitigation steps are completed within the designated timelines.\n\n---\n\n### ### Finance & Procurement\n*   **Approval Status:** The request exceeds the ₹2 Lakh threshold for routine procurement. Formal approval from the VP Finance is required via the Ariba/Coupa ETP workflow.\n*   **Payment Terms:** Advance payment is authorized as an exception, contingent upon the vendor providing a **100% Performance Bank Guarantee (PBG)** to mitigate financial risk.\n*   **Compliance:** The procurement team must ensure the vendor is registered in SAP (ME21N) and that the Invoice/GRN process is strictly followed to maintain GST input tax credit eligibility.\n\n### ### Legal & Contractual\n*   **Risk Mitigation:** The deviation from Net-30 credit terms requires a formal Addendum to the existing vendor MSA.\n*   **Key Clauses:** The Addendum must include a \"Right of Offset\" clause allowing Cognizant to recover damages from other outstanding payments should the vendor fail to deliver, as per the Indian Contract Act, 1872.\n*   **Regulatory:** Ensure compliance with the MSME Development Act, 2006, regarding prompt payment if applicable, and secure arbitration rights under the Arbitration & Conciliation Act 1996.\n\n### ### Cyber Security & IT Infrastructure\n*   **Risk Rating:** HIGH. The 72-hour deployment window is critical.\n*   **Mandatory Controls:** Assets must undergo PXE/SCCM imaging, BitLocker encryption, and CrowdStrike Falcon deployment. No asset shall be deployed to the Chennai delivery floor without a \"Green\" status in the Microsoft Intune compliance dashboard.\n*   **Asset Management:** All units must be tagged in the Cognizant Asset Management System (CAMS) and documented in the ServiceNow CMDB prior to user handover.\n\n### ### HR & Onboarding\n*   **Logistics:** The Chennai HRBP team must initiate the \"New Hire IT Setup\" request in ServiceNow at least 5 working days prior to joiners' arrival.\n*   **Compliance:** The Chennai facility lead must ensure workspace compliance with the Factories Act 1948, including ergonomic and safety requirements.\n\n---\n\n### ### NEXT STEPS\n1.  **Procurement (Lead: Bangalore Team):** Validate vendor stock and request the Performance Bank Guarantee (PBG) from M/s. Rashi Peripherals. **[Deadline: 10 July 2026, 05:00 PM IST]**\n2.  **Finance (Lead: BU Finance Manager):** Initiate the Exception to Policy (ETP) request in Ariba/Coupa and attach the Justification Memo. **[Deadline: 11 July 2026, 12:00 PM IST]**\n3.  **Legal (Lead: Legal Dept):** Draft and execute the Addendum to the MSA/PO, incorporating the \"Right of Offset\" clause. **[Deadline: 11 July 2026, 05:00 PM IST]**\n4.  **IT/Security (Lead: Chennai IT Desk):** Execute the 72-hour security hardening plan (Imaging, Intune, CrowdStrike) immediately upon receipt of hardware. **[Deadline: T+72 Hours from delivery]**\n5.  **HR (Lead: Chennai HRBP):** Coordinate the onboarding schedule and ensure all 20 associates have completed the pre-boarding digital checklist in Workday. **[Deadline: 13 July 2026, 09:00 AM IST]**"}
