2026-07-10 02:18:19 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:18:19 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'As the Senior VP of Finance & Risk Management for Cognizant India, I have reviewed the proposed advance payment request to M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd. Below is the formal financial risk assessment and compliance audit.\n\n### 1. Financial Risk Assessment & Breakdown\n*   **Base Amount:** \u20b91,96,891.53\n*   **GST (18% on HSN 8471):** \u20b935,440.47\n*   **Total Payment Amount:** **\u20b92,32,332.00**\n\n**Risk Assessment:**\n*   **Approval Threshold Breach:** The amount of \u20b92,32,332 exceeds the \u20b92 Lakh threshold for VP Finance approval. This transaction cannot proceed without my formal sign-off.\n*   **Liquidity/Cash Flow Impact:** A cash outflow of \u20b92.32 Lakhs in advance negatively impacts our working capital cycle. Since this is an *advance* payment, we face "Counterparty Risk"—the risk that the vendor fails to deliver the IT hardware after receiving funds.\n*   **Policy Breach:** Standard Cognizant terms are **Net-30 days** post-delivery and invoice verification. An advance payment is a deviation from this policy.\n\n### 2. Budget Head & Cost Center\n*   **Budget Head:** IT Infrastructure / Hardware Procurement (CapEx or OpEx depending on the asset threshold).\n*   **Cost Center:** Must be mapped to the specific Business Unit (BU) or Corporate IT unit initiating the procurement.\n*   **Action:** The requestor must provide the Cost Center code (e.g., IN-XXXX) to ensure budget availability in the current FY.\n\n### 3. Compliance & Payment Terms Analysis\nTo proceed with this advance payment, the following mandatory controls must be enforced:\n*   **Bank Guarantee (BG):** Given the advance nature, Rashi Peripherals must provide a BG equivalent to the advance amount (\u20b92,32,332) valid until the goods are delivered and inspected.\n*   **Exception to Policy (ETP):** An ETP form must be filed in our Spend Management system (Ariba/Coupa), citing the business justification for bypassing Net-30 terms.\n*   **Approval Path:**\n    *   **VP Finance (Me):** Mandatory sign-off required (as the amount is >\u20b92 Lakhs).\n    *   **CFO:** Not required (as the amount is <\u20b910 Lakhs).\n\n### 4. Tax & Regulatory Implications (GST)\n*   **GST Liability:** The 18% GST (\u20b935,440.47) is applicable. \n*   **Input Tax Credit (ITC):** We must ensure Rashi Peripherals uploads the invoice to the GSTR-1 portal so we can claim the ITC in our GSTR-3B filing. Failure to do so will result in a cash loss of 18% on the transaction value.\n*   **TDS:** Ensure TDS under Section 194Q (Purchase of Goods) is applied if the aggregate purchase value exceeds \u20b950 Lakhs in the current FY.\n\n### 5. FY Impact\n*   **Cognizant India FY:** April 1 – March 31.\n*   **Impact:** This transaction will be recorded in the current FY ledger. If the goods are not delivered before the FY-end, this creates a "Prepaid Expense" on the balance sheet, which requires reconciliation during the year-end audit.\n\n### Final Recommendation\n**Do not process this payment yet.** \n1. The requestor must upload the pro-forma invoice and the ETP justification into the procurement portal.\n2. The vendor must submit a Bank Guarantee.\n3. Once the BG is verified by our Treasury team, I will provide the VP-level approval required to release the funds.\n\n**Status:** *Pending Documentation & Compliance.*'}
