2026-07-10 02:18:21 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:18:20 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Cyber_Security_Agent\nAs the CISO representative for Cognizant India, I have outlined the mandatory security provisioning requirements for the 20 new Dell Latitude 5540 assets. These units must not be handed over to end-users until they pass the "Ready for Secure Deployment" (RFSD) validation check.\n\n### 1. Risk Assessment\n**Risk Identified:** Unauthorized access to corporate data, data exfiltration, and non-compliance with the Digital Personal Data Protection (DPDP) Act 2023. Deploying unmanaged or improperly hardened assets creates a blind spot in our Security Operations Center (SOC) visibility, potentially allowing for lateral movement of threats.\n\n### 2. Mandatory Security Controls\nTo ensure these assets meet the Cognizant standard, the following controls are **non-negotiable**:\n\n*   **Golden Image Deployment:** Assets must be reimaged using the standard Cognizant Windows 11 Enterprise image, ensuring all bloatware is removed and baseline security configurations (CIS Level 1) are applied.\n*   **Intune MDM Enrollment:** Assets must be enrolled via Autopilot using the hardware hash. Compliance policies (password complexity, inactivity timeouts, and OS update versions) must be active.\n*   **Endpoint Protection:**\n    *   **CrowdStrike Falcon:** Must be installed and registered to the Cognizant tenant (Sensor version 7.x+).\n    *   **Microsoft Defender for Endpoint:** Must be active for EDR/AV integration.\n*   **Data Protection:** BitLocker Drive Encryption (AES-256) is mandatory, with recovery keys escrowed to the Microsoft Entra ID (formerly Azure AD) tenant.\n*   **Identity & Access:** CyberArk EPM (Endpoint Privilege Management) must be installed to enforce "Least Privilege," removing local admin rights from the end-user.\n*   **Asset Tagging:** Physical asset tags (barcodes) must be affixed and mapped in the Cognizant Asset Management System (CAMS) against the device Serial Number and MAC address.\n\n### 3. Regulatory & Internal Standards\n*   **ISO 27001 (A.8.1):** Responsibility for assets; ensuring information is protected throughout the lifecycle.\n*   **Cognizant CISO Mandate:** Strict adherence to the "Zero Trust" architecture policy.\n*   **DPDP Act 2023:** Obligations of the Data Fiduciary; failure to secure endpoints containing personal data can lead to financial penalties up to \u20b9250 crore.\n*   **IT Act 2000 (Section 43A):** Failure to maintain "reasonable security practices" for sensitive personal data.\n\n### 4. Risk Rating: **HIGH**\n**Justification:** New joiners often handle sensitive client data and PII. If these devices are deployed without full disk encryption (BitLocker) and EDR (CrowdStrike), a physical loss or malware infection would result in an immediate data breach, violating both client SLAs and Indian law.\n\n### 5. 72-Hour Action Plan\n\n| Timeline | Task | Responsible Team |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **0-12 Hours** | Import hardware hashes into Autopilot; verify BIOS settings (Secure Boot ON, TPM 2.0 active). | IT Infrastructure / Asset Mgmt |\n| **12-36 Hours** | Execute PXE boot/Autopilot provisioning; verify successful enrollment into Intune and compliance report generation. | IT Operations |\n| **36-60 Hours** | Push security baseline policies (CyberArk EPM, CrowdStrike, Defender). Confirm "Healthy" status in the SOC dashboard. | Information Security |\n| **60-72 Hours** | Final audit: Verify BitLocker encryption status and CAMS tagging. Sign-off for deployment to HR/New Joiner onboarding team. | CISO Compliance Team |\n\n**Directives:** No device shall be released to a user without a "Green" status in the Intune/CrowdStrike management console. Any failure to sync policies must be escalated to the IT Security lead immediately.'}
