Intune/Autopilot.\n    *   Installation of **CrowdStrike Falcon** and **CyberArk EPM**.\n    *   BitLocker encryption (AES-256) with recovery keys in Entra ID.\n*   **Asset Compliance:** Physical tagging in the Cognizant Asset Management System (CAMS) is mandatory before deployment to end-users to prevent data exfiltration and ensure compliance with the **DPDP Act 2023**.\n\n### ### HR & Onboarding\n*   **Timeline:** 3 days to kick-off. Standard 5-day lead time has been breached.\n*   **Action:** Immediately raise 20 'New Hire IT Setup' requests in ServiceNow with 'High Priority' tags.\n*   **Coordination:** Contact the Chennai IT Helpdesk to obtain manual override for the SLA breach. Ensure all 20 associates have completed the LMS Security Induction upon receipt of assets.\n\n---\n\n### **STATUS: UNDER REVIEW**\n\n**NEXT STEPS:**\n1.  **Procurement Lead:** Negotiate Net-15 terms with M/s. Rashi Peripherals and obtain a Bank Guarantee. (**Owner: Procurement Team**)\n2.  **Finance Lead:** Review and sign-off on the ETP and release payment only after BG verification. (**Owner: VP Finance**)\n3.  **IT Infrastructure:** Create the PO in S/4HANA (ME21N) and monitor logistics tracking via iSource. (**Owner: IT Asset Management**)\n4.  **Security/SOC:** Coordinate the 72-hour provisioning plan (Autopilot, CrowdStrike, BitLocker) to meet the 3-day deadline. (**Owner: CISO Team**)\n5.  **HR Operations:** Submit 20 ServiceNow tickets and coordinate with Chennai ITAM for staging. (**Owner: HR Onboarding Coordinator**)"}
