2026-07-10 02:21:50 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:21:50 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Finance_Risk_Agent\nAs the Senior VP of Finance & Risk Management for Cognizant India, I have reviewed the proposed advance payment request to M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd. Below is the formal financial risk assessment and compliance mandate.\n\n### 1. Financial Risk Assessment & Breakdown\nThe gross amount for the procurement is **\u20b92,32,332**. Based on the HSN code 8471 (IT Hardware), the GST liability is 18%.\n\n*   **Base Value (Taxable Amount):** \u20b91,96,891.53\n*   **GST (18%):** \u20b935,440.47\n*   **Total Advance Payment:** **\u20b92,32,332.00**\n\n**Risk Assessment:**\n*   **Liquidity Risk:** Low, given the quantum; however, advance payments represent a "Cash-at-Risk" scenario. Without a Bank Guarantee (BG), Cognizant lacks recovery recourse should the vendor fail to deliver.\n*   **Compliance Risk:** High. The request triggers an **Exception to Policy (ETP)** as Cognizant’s standard payment terms are Net-30 days post-delivery/acceptance.\n*   **Control Risk:** Since the amount exceeds the \u20b92 Lakh threshold for VP-level approval, unauthorized processing would constitute a breach of our Internal Financial Controls (IFC).\n\n### 2. Budget Head & Cost Center\n*   **Budget Head:** CAPEX (if hardware is for asset capitalization) or OPEX (if hardware is for IT consumables/replacement).\n*   **Cost Center:** Must be mapped to the specific BU/Function (e.g., *IN-CORP-IT-INFRA*). The initiator must ensure the Cost Center has sufficient "Budget-to-Actual" (BTA) availability for the current FY.\n\n### 3. Approval & Policy Requirements\nBecause this is an **advance payment**, the following mandatory controls apply:\n\n1.  **Bank Guarantee (BG):** You are required to obtain an unconditional, irrevocable Bank Guarantee from M/s. Rashi Peripherals for the full amount (\u20b92,32,332) valid until at least 30 days post-delivery.\n2.  **ETP Approval:** An \'Exception to Policy\' form must be filed in our Spend Management system (Coupa/Ariba). \n3.  **Sign-off Thresholds:**\n    *   **VP Finance Sign-off:** Mandatory, as the amount exceeds \u20b92 Lakhs.\n    *   **CFO Sign-off:** Not required (threshold is >\u20b910 Lakhs).\n4.  **Procurement Verification:** The vendor must be active in our Vendor Master, and the Purchase Order (PO) must be linked to the advance payment request to prevent double-invoicing.\n\n### 4. FY Impact (Cognizant India: April–March)\n*   **Cash Flow:** The cash outflow occurs in the current month. If the asset is not commissioned before March 31st, the expense must be carried as "Advances to Suppliers" on the Balance Sheet and cannot be recognized as a P&L expense for the current FY.\n*   **Tax Credit:** The 18% GST (\u20b935,440.47) can be claimed as Input Tax Credit (ITC) only upon receipt of the tax invoice and the physical delivery of the hardware. The advance payment itself does not qualify for ITC until the goods are received.\n\n### Mandatory Directives for Execution:\n1.  **Stop Payment:** Do not initiate the payment via the ERP system until the ETP is digitally signed by the Cost Center Head and myself (VP Finance).\n2.  **BG Verification:** Treasury must verify the authenticity of the BG provided by the vendor’s bank before the release of funds.\n3.  **Audit Trail:** Attach all approval emails and the BG document to the Coupa requisition to ensure compliance with Internal Audit and SOX requirements.\n\n**Status:** *Pending mandatory ETP and BG submission. Approval denied until these documents are uploaded to the system.*'}
