2026-07-10 02:21:55 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow: {"type": "AI", "text": "### Executive Action Summary: Bangalore Procurement Request (20 Dell Latitude 5540 Units)\n\n**DATE:** 10 July 2026 | **LOCATION:** Chennai/Bangalore | **STATUS:** UNDER REVIEW\n\n---\n\n### Procurement & Supply Chain\nThe request to procure 20 Dell Latitude 5540 units (₹2,32,332) from M/s. Rashi Peripherals is currently held pending vendor negotiation. \n*   **Policy Deviation:** The vendor’s demand for advance payment violates Cognizant’s global Net-30 credit terms. \n*   **Action:** Procurement must negotiate a \"Payment on GRN\" (Net-7) basis. If the vendor rejects, a Bank Guarantee (BG) for the full amount is mandatory before any advance payment can be processed.\n\n### Finance & Risk\n*   **Compliance:** The request requires an 'Exception to Policy' (ETP) form to be filed in the Spend Management system. \n*   **Approvals:** As the amount exceeds ₹2 Lakhs, the ETP requires sign-off from the Cost Center Head and the VP of Finance. \n*   **Tax:** GST (₹35,440.47) will only be eligible for Input Tax Credit (ITC) upon physical receipt of goods and tax invoice. Advance payments do not qualify for immediate ITC.\n\n### Legal & Regulatory\n*   **Risk:** Waiving credit terms creates an \"unsecured creditor\" status and violates the spirit of our Master Service Agreement.\n*   **Statutory:** Any payment modification must be documented via a formal Addendum to the MSA. We must avoid creating a precedent that weakens our leverage in service-level disputes under the Arbitration & Conciliation Act 1996.\n\n### HR & Asset Management\n*   **Onboarding:** The Project Resource Manager must initiate the \"New Hire IT Setup\" in ServiceNow immediately.\n*   **Documentation:** All 20 assets must be registered in Workday HRMS. Associates must complete digital asset acknowledgement via the iHR portal upon physical receipt at the Chennai center.\n\n### Cyber Security & IT Hardening\n*   **Mandatory Controls:** Assets must undergo \"Golden Image\" deployment via MECM, BitLocker FDE, and CrowdStrike Falcon installation.\n*   **Compliance:** Systems must comply with the DPDP Act 2023 and the IT Act 2000. \n*   **Timeline:** Assets must undergo a 72-hour hardening process (BIOS hardening, vulnerability scanning, and SOC audit) before being connected to the production VLAN.\n\n---\n\n### NEXT STEPS\n1.  **Procurement Lead (Bangalore):** Negotiate \"Payment on GRN\" with Rashi Peripherals. If unsuccessful, request a Bank Guarantee (BG). **Due: 10 July 2026, 17:00 IST.**\n2.  **Cost Center Head:** File 'Exception to Policy' (ETP) in Coupa/Ariba and secure VP Finance approval. **Due: 11 July 2026, 12:00 IST.**\n3.  **Treasury/Finance:** Verify the authenticity of any provided BG before fund release. **Due: 11 July 2026, 17:00 IST.**\n4.  **IT Infrastructure (Chennai):** Prepare the staging environment for 72-hour hardening and imaging. **Due: 12 July 2026, 09:00 IST.**\n5.  **Project Manager:** Initiate ServiceNow hardware provisioning tickets for all 20 associates. **Due: 10 July 2026, 18:00 IST.**"}
