2026-07-10 02:25:01 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:25:01 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Finance_Risk_Agent\nAs the Senior VP of Finance & Risk Management for Cognizant India, I have reviewed the proposed advance payment request for M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd. \n\nBelow is the formal financial risk assessment and compliance audit based on Cognizant’s internal control framework.\n\n### 1. Financial Risk Assessment & Breakdown\n*   **Base Amount:** \u20b91,96,891.53\n*   **GST (18% on HSN 8471):** \u20b935,440.47\n*   **Total Payment Amount:** **\u20b92,32,332.00**\n\n**Risk Analysis:**\n*   **Threshold Breach:** The total amount of \u20b92.32 Lakhs exceeds the \u20b92 Lakh threshold for VP Finance sign-off. This transaction cannot proceed without my explicit approval.\n*   **Advance Payment Risk:** Making an advance payment carries significant counterparty risk. Without a Bank Guarantee (BG), Cognizant is exposed to the risk of non-delivery or insolvency of the vendor.\n*   **Treasury Policy Violation:** Per policy, any advance payment requires:\n    1.  A Bank Guarantee (BG) of equivalent value from the vendor.\n    2.  An approved \'Exception to Policy\' (ETP) form.\n    3.  If no BG is obtained, the transaction is classified as an \'Unsecured Advance,\' which is a high-risk audit finding.\n\n### 2. Budget Head & Cost Center\n*   **Budget Head:** IT Infrastructure / Hardware Procurement (Capex/Opex depending on the asset life cycle).\n*   **Cost Center:** Must be verified against the originating business unit (e.g., GTO India or Corporate IT). \n*   **Action Required:** The requester must provide the specific Cost Center code to ensure the debit does not cause a budget variance in the current quarter.\n\n### 3. Payment Terms & Compliance\n*   **Standard Terms:** Cognizant standard payment terms are **Net-30 days** post-delivery and verification of the Tax Invoice.\n*   **Advance Payment Protocol:** \n    *   Since this is an advance, the "Net-30" rule is waived, triggering the requirement for an **ETP**.\n    *   **Requirement:** The procurement team must confirm if the vendor has submitted a valid Proforma Invoice and if the BG is in the process of being issued. \n    *   **Recommendation:** I advise against releasing this payment until the BG is validated by the Treasury team.\n\n### 4. GST & Tax Compliance\n*   **HSN Code:** 8471 (Automatic Data Processing Machines).\n*   **GST Impact:** The 18% GST (\u20b935,440.47) is recoverable as Input Tax Credit (ITC). \n*   **Compliance:** The payment must be processed through the Ariba/Coupa system against a valid Purchase Order (PO). The invoice must reflect Cognizant’s GSTIN to ensure we claim the ITC in the current month\'s GSTR-3B filing.\n\n### 5. FY Impact (April–March)\n*   **Period:** This transaction falls within the current FY (April 2024 – March 2025).\n*   **P&L Impact:** If the hardware is capitalized, the impact will be recognized via depreciation over the asset\'s useful life. If treated as a low-value asset expense, it will hit the P&L immediately in the month of delivery. \n*   **Cash Flow:** The advance payment will create a temporary "Prepaid Expense" entry on the Balance Sheet until the goods are received and the PO is marked as "Goods Receipt/Invoice Receipt" (GRIR) cleared.\n\n### Final Directive:\n**This payment is currently flagged as "HOLD."** \n\nTo proceed, the following items must be uploaded to the portal:\n1.  **Approved ETP Form:** Signed by the relevant BU Head and Procurement Lead.\n2.  **Bank Guarantee:** Scanned copy of the BG valid for at least 6 months beyond the expected delivery date.\n3.  **VP Finance Approval:** Once the above are attached, forward the Coupa requisition to my queue for final sign-off.\n\nFailure to adhere to these controls will result in a rejection of the payment request to maintain compliance with SOX and internal audit standards.'}
