2026-07-10 02:25:01 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:25:01 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from HR_Safety_Agent\nAs the Head of HR for Cognizant India, I understand the urgency of this request. Ensuring a seamless "Day 1" experience is a cornerstone of our **CognizantOne** associate experience framework.\n\nWhen onboarding new joiners, we must adhere strictly to our IT provisioning SLAs to prevent productivity loss.\n\n### 1. Assessment of Impact\n*   **Affected Headcount:** All new joiners starting in 3 days.\n*   **Grade Levels:** Typically C1 (Associate) to C3 (Senior Associate).\n*   **Required Action:** Immediate escalation is required because the standard procurement window is **5 business days**. Since we are at the 3-day mark, we are currently outside the standard SLA.\n\n### 2. Asset Allocation Process (NHOK)\nAccording to our **New Hire Onboarding Kit (NHOK)** policy:\n*   **The Process:** The Hiring Manager or the SPOC (Single Point of Contact) must raise a request via the **ServiceNow portal** under the catalog item **\'New Hire IT Setup\'**.\n*   **The Constraint:** This request must be submitted at least **5 days prior** to the joining date to ensure the laptop is configured, imaged with the Cognizant standard build, and dispatched to the associate\'s registered location or the Chennai ODC.\n*   **Current Mitigation:** Since we are at T-minus 3 days, you must:\n    1.  Immediately raise the ServiceNow ticket.\n    2.  Add a comment in the ticket: *"Urgent: Onboarding T-3. Requesting expedited provisioning for [Associate Name/Employee ID]."*\n    3.  Contact the **Chennai GEC (Global Experience Center) IT Desk** via the CognizantOne support chat to flag the ticket number for manual intervention.\n\n### 3. Tools and Systems\n*   **Workday HRMS:** Ensure the associate’s status is updated to "Ready for Hire" to trigger the automated IT provisioning workflow.\n*   **iHR Portal:** Refer to the \'Onboarding\' section for the latest guidelines on hardware delivery tracking.\n*   **ServiceNow:** The primary system of record for tracking the hardware lifecycle.\n\n### 4. Internal Communication Memo Template\n*You may use the following draft to communicate with the affected new joiners if a delay is anticipated.*\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** Update regarding your Onboarding Logistics – Cognizant Chennai\n\n**Dear [Associate Name],**\n\nWelcome to Cognizant! We are thrilled to have you join our team.\n\nAs we prepare for your first day on [Joining Date], I am writing to provide an update on your equipment provisioning. Our team is working diligently to ensure your hardware is configured to meet our security and performance standards.\n\nDue to current logistics timelines, there is a possibility that your New Hire Onboarding Kit (NHOK) may arrive shortly after your start date. Please rest assured that our IT support team is prioritizing your request to ensure you have full system access as quickly as possible.\n\n**Next Steps:**\n1. You will receive an automated email from ServiceNow with your tracking details once the kit is dispatched.\n2. Please log into the **iHR portal** using your temporary credentials to complete your Day 1 compliance modules and welcome sessions.\n3. If you have any immediate concerns, please reach out to your designated Onboarding SPOC or the Chennai GEC support desk.\n\nWe look forward to your successful start with us.\n\nBest regards,\n\n**[Your Name/HR Team]**\nHuman Resources, Cognizant India\n\n***\n\n### HR Compliance Note:\nPlease ensure all associates complete the **\'Information Security & Data Privacy\'** mandatory training modules via the Learning Management System (LMS) as soon as they gain system access, as this is a strict requirement for all Cognizant associates regardless of hardware delivery status.'}
