2026-07-10 02:25:02 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:25:01 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Cyber_Security_Agent\nAs the CISO representative for Cognizant India, I have outlined the security provisioning and asset lifecycle requirements for the 20 Dell Latitude 5540 units destined for the Chennai delivery center. \n\nThese assets must adhere to our "Secure-by-Design" workstation policy before they are handed over to any associate.\n\n### 1. Risk Assessment\nThe primary risks involve **unauthorized data exfiltration, loss of PII (Personally Identifiable Information), and lateral movement** within the Cognizant internal network. Failure to properly provision these assets creates a "shadow IT" vulnerability, where endpoints lack visibility, patching, and encryption, violating our contractual obligations to clients and statutory requirements under Indian law.\n\n### 2. Mandatory Security Controls\nAll 20 laptops must undergo the following provisioning sequence:\n*   **Hardware/Asset Tagging:** Physical asset tags (Cognizant Asset ID) must be applied to the chassis. The serial number must be mapped to the **Cognizant IT Asset Management (ITAM) database** via ServiceNow.\n*   **Golden Image Deployment:** Deployment of the standard Cognizant Windows 11 Enterprise image via SCCM/Autopilot. This includes pre-configured GPOs and hardened OS settings.\n*   **Endpoint Management:** Enrollment in **Microsoft Intune MDM**. Compliance policies must be enforced (e.g., minimum OS version, password complexity, screen lock timeouts).\n*   **Encryption:** **BitLocker Drive Encryption** must be enabled, with recovery keys escrowed automatically to Azure Active Directory (Entra ID).\n*   **Security Stack:**\n    *   **CrowdStrike Falcon:** Must be installed and verified in the "Reporting" state before moving to "Full Prevention" mode.\n    *   **Microsoft Defender for Endpoint (MDE):** Integrated for XDR telemetry.\n    *   **CyberArk EPM:** Implementation of Least Privilege access; local admin rights must be stripped from end-users.\n\n### 3. Regulatory & Compliance Standards\n*   **ISO/IEC 27001:2022 (A.5.9/A.8.1):** Mandates rigorous inventory and protection of information assets.\n*   **Digital Personal Data Protection (DPDP) Act 2023:** Requires "reasonable security safeguards" to prevent personal data breaches. Failure to secure these endpoints could lead to significant financial penalties.\n*   **IT Act 2000 (Section 43A):** Imposes liability on corporate entities for failure to maintain reasonable security practices for sensitive personal data.\n*   **Cognizant CISO Mandate:** All hardware must be centrally managed and compliant with the "Zero Trust" architecture framework.\n\n### 4. Risk Rating: **HIGH**\n*   **Justification:** Chennai delivery centers frequently handle high-sensitivity projects (BFSI/Healthcare). Deploying unmanaged or improperly provisioned assets into this environment creates an immediate entry point for ransomware and data leakage, which would trigger a mandatory report to the CERT-In (Indian Computer Emergency Response Team).\n\n### 5. Action Plan (72-Hour Window)\n\n| Timeline | Action Item | Responsibility |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **0-12 Hours** | Physical asset tagging and registration in ServiceNow/ITAM. | Chennai IT Ops |\n| **12-24 Hours** | PXE boot/Autopilot provisioning for Golden Image deployment. | Deployment Team |\n| **24-48 Hours** | Verification of Intune enrollment, BitLocker status, and CrowdStrike/CyberArk heartbeat in the console. | Security Operations (SecOps) |\n| **48-72 Hours** | Final audit of security posture via MDE/Intune dashboard; sign-off for asset issuance to end-users. | CISO Compliance Team |\n\n**Directive:** No laptop is to be connected to the production network (VLAN) until the "Security Compliance" status is marked as \'Passed\' in the Intune portal. Any unit failing to report to the console by the 48-hour mark must be physically quarantined for forensic inspection.'}
