2026-07-10 02:25:05 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow: {"type": "AI", "text": "### Executive Action Summary: Bangalore-Chennai Hardware Procurement\n\n**To:** Executive Leadership Team, Cognizant India  \n**From:** Office of the Chief of Staff  \n**Date:** May 22, 2024  \n**Subject:** Urgent Procurement Exception Request: 20 Dell Latitude 5540 Units\n\n---\n\n### Procurement & Financial Governance\nThe request for an advance payment of **₹2,32,332** to M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd. is currently **UNDER REVIEW**. The transaction violates the standard Cognizant **Net-30 credit policy**. Per the Finance Risk assessment, this payment requires an Exception to Policy (ETP) and explicit approval from the VP of Finance, as it exceeds the ₹2 Lakh threshold. \n*   **Recommendation:** Reject the advance request. Counter-offer a \"Fast-Track\" 10-day payment cycle. If an advance is unavoidable, a **Bank Guarantee (BG)** equal to the invoice value is mandatory to mitigate counterparty risk.\n\n### Legal & Regulatory Compliance\nThe 3-day delivery window is aggressive and carries significant risk under the **Indian Contract Act, 1872**. \n*   **Compliance:** If the vendor is an MSME, we must adhere to the **MSMED Act, 2006** to avoid penal interest (3x RBI rate). \n*   **Legal Mandate:** Any contract must include a \"Time is of the Essence\" clause and clear Liquidated Damages (LD) provisions to protect Cognizant in case of delivery failure.\n\n### Cyber Security & Asset Management\nThe deployment of these assets is classified as **HIGH RISK**. \n*   **Mandatory Controls:** Assets must be registered in the **ServiceNow CMDB** and provisioned via **Microsoft Intune/Autopilot** with BitLocker and CrowdStrike Falcon installed. \n*   **Regulatory Alignment:** Failure to secure these endpoints violates the **Digital Personal Data Protection (DPDP) Act 2023** and **IT Act 2000 (Section 43A)**. No laptop is to connect to the production network until the security heartbeat is confirmed in the Intune console.\n\n### HR & Onboarding Logistics\nThe current procurement timeline of 3 days falls outside our standard 5-day SLA for NHOK (New Hire Onboarding Kit) provisioning. \n*   **Action:** Hiring Managers must immediately raise a ServiceNow ticket for \"New Hire IT Setup\" and escalate via the Chennai GEC support desk for manual intervention. Affected new joiners should be proactively notified of potential delays to maintain a positive employee experience.\n\n---\n\n### STATUS: UNDER REVIEW\n\n### NEXT STEPS\n1.  **Negotiation (Procurement Lead):** Re-negotiate payment terms with Rashi Peripherals (target: Net-30 or 10-day expedited pay; no advance without BG).\n2.  **Budget/Finance Approval (VP Finance/Site Lead):** Approve the ETP and Cost Center mapping for the ₹2,32,332 expenditure.\n3.  **IT/Security Provisioning (Chennai IT Ops/SecOps):** Execute the 72-hour security hardening protocol upon receipt of hardware.\n4.  **HR Coordination (HR SPOC):** Update the NHOK ServiceNow tickets and provide proactive communication to the incoming associates.\n5.  **Logistics Tracking (Supply Chain):** Monitor the iSource portal for dispatch status; report any variance from the 3-day timeline immediately."}
