2026-07-10 02:26:52 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:26:52 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Finance_Risk_Agent\nAs Senior VP of Finance & Risk Management for Cognizant India, I have reviewed the proposed advance payment request for M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd. Below is the formal financial risk assessment and compliance audit.\n\n### 1. Financial Risk Assessment & Calculation\n*   **Gross Amount:** \u20b92,32,332\n*   **GST Calculation (18% under HSN 8471):**\n    *   Base Amount (Excl. GST): \u20b91,96,891.53\n    *   GST Component (18%): \u20b935,440.47\n*   **Total Disbursement:** \u20b92,32,332\n*   **Risk Profile:** **High.** Advance payments represent an unsecured credit risk. In the event of vendor insolvency or non-delivery, Cognizant India faces a direct loss of capital. \n\n### 2. Budget Head & Cost Center\n*   **Budget Head:** IT Infrastructure / Hardware Procurement (Capital Expenditure - CAPEX).\n*   **Cost Center:** Must be mapped to the requesting business unit (e.g., Delivery or Shared Services). The requestor must confirm that the **Budget Utilization Report (BUR)** reflects sufficient headroom in the specific Cost Center code before procurement initiation.\n\n### 3. Compliance & Approval Thresholds\n*   **VP Finance Sign-off:** Since the total payment amount (\u20b92,32,332) exceeds the **\u20b92 Lakh threshold**, this transaction requires my formal sign-off as VP Finance.\n*   **CFO Sign-off:** Not required as it falls below the \u20b910 Lakh threshold.\n*   **Advance Payment Policy:** Per Cognizant India internal policy, any advance payment requires:\n    1.  **Bank Guarantee (BG):** A BG equivalent to the advance amount (\u20b92,32,332) must be submitted by Rashi Peripherals, valid until the delivery of goods is verified in the Fixed Asset Register (FAR).\n    2.  **Exception to Policy (ETP):** An ETP form must be signed by the Delivery Head and Finance Controller, justifying why standard Net-30 payment terms are being bypassed.\n\n### 4. Cash Flow & FY Impact\n*   **Cash Flow Impact:** Immediate liquidity outflow. This will be reflected in the "Prepaid Expenses" ledger for the current month.\n*   **FY Impact:** Our fiscal year runs **April–March**. This transaction must be accounted for in the current month\'s Opex/Capex cycle. If the hardware is not delivered and "Good Receipt Note" (GRN) is not processed within the same financial quarter, this will create a reconciliation discrepancy during the quarterly internal audit.\n\n### 5. Final Recommendations & Required Actions\nTo proceed with this payment, the following documentation must be uploaded to the Ariba/Coupa portal:\n\n1.  **Proforma Invoice:** Clearly stating the HSN 8471 and GST bifurcation.\n2.  **BG Document:** Verified by our Treasury team to ensure it is from a nationalized/scheduled bank.\n3.  **ETP Approval:** Signed and stamped by the authorized stakeholders.\n4.  **Vendor Compliance:** Ensure Rashi Peripherals is active in our vendor master and has a valid GSTIN registered in the state of delivery.\n\n**Risk Mitigation Directive:** I advise against releasing the funds until the BG is physically verified by the Finance Shared Services (FSS) team. Failure to secure the BG constitutes a breach of Cognizant’s financial internal controls, which will result in an audit finding.\n\n**Status:** *Pending receipt of Bank Guarantee and ETP documentation for VP-level approval.*'}
