2026-07-10 02:29:09 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:29:08 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Legal_Agent\n**LEGAL ADVISORY NOTE**\n\n**TO:** Procurement/Finance Department\n**FROM:** Office of the Associate General Counsel, Cognizant India\n**DATE:** October 26, 2023\n**SUBJECT:** Legal Addendum for One-Time Advance Payment – Vendor [Vendor Name]\n\n---\n\n### 1. Legal Analysis & Regulatory Context\nTo mitigate the risk of "unjust enrichment" and ensure performance, any advance payment made to a vendor must be strictly tethered to the Master Service Agreement (MSA). Under **Section 73 of the Indian Contract Act, 1872**, the vendor is liable for compensation for any loss or damage caused by a breach of contract. By issuing this addendum, we establish a "performance-linked" disbursement, ensuring the advance is recoverable as a debt should the vendor fail to perform.\n\n*   **MSME Compliance:** If the vendor is registered under the **MSME Development Act, 2006**, ensure that the advance payment terms do not conflict with the mandatory 45-day settlement window if the contract is for goods/services.\n*   **Performance Security:** The advance must be secured by a Bank Guarantee (BG) or a clear clawback clause to prevent financial exposure.\n\n### 2. Legal Risk Exposure\n*   **Financial Exposure:** Total value of the advance payment (INR).\n*   **Risk Rating: MEDIUM** (Risk arises from potential vendor insolvency or non-performance post-payment).\n\n---\n\n### 3. Draft Addendum (Formal)\n\n**ADDENDUM TO MASTER SERVICE AGREEMENT (MSA) DATED [DATE]**\n\nThis Addendum is entered into by and between Cognizant Technology Solutions India Pvt. Ltd. ("Cognizant") and [Vendor Name] ("Vendor").\n\n**1. ADVANCE PAYMENT:** Cognizant agrees to pay an advance of INR [Amount] as a one-time payment. This payment is subject to the Vendor providing a valid Proforma Invoice.\n\n**2. PERFORMANCE OBLIGATION:** The Vendor acknowledges that this advance is strictly for the delivery of [Project Name/Service]. The Vendor represents that they are capable of fulfilling the delivery obligations as per the SOW.\n\n**3. LIABILITY & RECOVERY:** \n(a) Pursuant to **Section 39 of the Indian Contract Act, 1872**, if the Vendor fails to perform their obligations, Cognizant shall be entitled to terminate the contract and demand a full refund of the advance payment within 7 days of notice.\n(b) The Vendor acknowledges that failure to deliver constitutes a material breach, and the advance amount shall be treated as a debt due to Cognizant, recoverable under the provisions of the **Code of Civil Procedure, 1908**.\n\n**4. GOVERNING LAW:** This Addendum shall be governed by the laws of India. Any disputes arising hereunder shall be resolved through binding arbitration in accordance with the **Arbitration & Conciliation Act, 1996**, with the seat of arbitration in [City, e.g., Chennai/Mumbai].\n\n**IN WITNESS WHEREOF**, the parties have executed this Addendum as of the date first written above.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Recommended Legal Remedies\n1.  **Clawback Clause:** Ensure the contract explicitly states that the advance is "recoverable on demand" if milestones are not met.\n2.  **Bank Guarantee:** For advances exceeding INR 10 Lakhs, insist on a Bank Guarantee for the equivalent amount to protect Cognizant’s capital.\n3.  **Set-off Rights:** Explicitly reserve the right to set off the advance payment against future invoices if the vendor defaults.\n\n**LEGAL RISK RATING: MEDIUM** \n*(Note: Risk is mitigated to LOW upon receipt of a signed Addendum and a corresponding Bank Guarantee.)*\n\n**[Signature]**\nAssociate General Counsel\nCognizant India'}
2026-07-10 02:29:09 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:29:09 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': "As Senior VP of Finance & Risk Management, I have reviewed the request for a one-time advance payment of \u20b92,32,332 to M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd. \n\nBelow is the formal financial risk assessment and compliance roadmap for this transaction.\n\n### 1. Financial Risk Assessment & Threshold Validation\n*   **Transaction Amount:** \u20b92,32,332 (Inclusive of 18% GST).\n*   **Base Value (Excl. GST):** \u20b91,96,891.53\n*   **GST Liability (18% on HSN 8471):** \u20b935,440.47\n*   **Threshold Trigger:** Under Cognizant India’s delegation of authority (DOA), any single vendor payment exceeding **\u20b92 Lakhs** requires **VP Finance sign-off**. As this is an *advance* payment, it carries an elevated risk profile and strictly mandates an approved Exception to Policy (ETP).\n*   **Risk Rating:** **Moderate-High.** Advance payments create unsecured credit risk. The risk is mitigated only by the mandatory submission of a Bank Guarantee (BG).\n\n### 2. Budget Head & Cost Center\n*   **Budget Head:** IT Infrastructure / Hardware Procurement (Capital Expenditure - CAPEX).\n*   **Cost Center:** Must be mapped to the requesting BU (e.g., *IN-INFRA-PROD-001*). \n*   **Action Required:** The requester must provide the specific Profit Center/Cost Center code to ensure the debit is recorded against the correct FY2026-27 budget allocation.\n\n### 3. Payment Terms & Compliance Requirements\nPer Cognizant India financial policy:\n*   **Standard Terms:** Net-30 days.\n*   **Advance Payment Policy:** As we are bypassing standard terms, the following are mandatory:\n    *   **Bank Guarantee (BG):** The vendor must provide a BG equivalent to the advance amount, valid for a minimum of 90 days post-delivery.\n    *   **ETP Approval:** An 'Exception to Policy' form must be digitally signed via our internal workflow (Ariba/Coupa), citing the business criticality of this procurement.\n    *   **Audit Trail:** All correspondence and the ETP sign-off must be archived in the central repository for the July 2026 audit.\n\n### 4. GST & Tax Compliance\n*   **HSN Code:** 8471 (Automatic Data Processing Machines).\n*   **Tax Treatment:** Ensure the vendor’s GST invoice is validated against the GST portal (GSTR-2B) to ensure the Input Tax Credit (ITC) is eligible. The payment must not be released until the vendor has uploaded the invoice on the GST portal to ensure our ITC realization.\n\n### 5. FY Impact & Audit Readiness\n*   **Financial Year:** This transaction falls under **FY 2026-27** (April 1, 2026 – March 31, 2027).\n*   **Audit Readiness:** For the July 2026 internal audit, the following documents must be attached to the Ariba/Coupa requisition:\n    1.  Copy of the executed Bank Guarantee.\n    2.  Digitally signed ETP form.\n    3.  Purchase Order (PO) referencing the advance payment terms.\n    4.  Vendor's Pro-forma invoice.\n\n### Final Authorization Directive\n**I hereby approve the request for the advance payment subject to the following conditions:**\n1.  **Submission of a valid Bank Guarantee** from a scheduled commercial bank is non-negotiable.\n2.  **ETP Workflow:** The requester must route the ETP via the internal portal for my digital signature; manual emails will not suffice.\n3.  **Treasury Verification:** The Finance Operations team must verify the vendor's bank account details against our Master Vendor File (MVF) to prevent fraud.\n\n**Proceed with the requisition entry in Ariba immediately.** Once the BG is verified by the Treasury team, the payment will be released."}
