2026-07-10 02:29:09 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:29:09 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Cyber_Security_Agent\n**MEMORANDUM: OFFICE OF THE CISO (COGNIZANT INDIA)**\n\n**TO:** Chennai IT Infrastructure & Operations Team\n**SUBJECT:** MANDATORY SECURITY PROVISIONING – BATCH ID: CHN-LAP-20-Q3\n**REFERENCE:** Endpoint Hardening Policy (EHP-2024)\n\n---\n\n### 1. Risk Assessment\nThe deployment of unprovisioned "out-of-the-box" hardware represents a **CRITICAL** supply chain and data leakage risk. Unauthorized devices lack visibility, lack encryption, and are susceptible to persistent threats (APT) or data exfiltration. Failure to enforce EHP-2024 before associate hand-off creates a significant vulnerability window, potentially exposing Cognizant to unauthorized access to client environments and non-compliance with regulatory mandates.\n\n### 2. Mandatory Security Controls\nNo device shall be released to an associate unless the following technical gates are verified via the **Cognizant IT Service Management (ITSM) portal**:\n\n*   **Intune Enrollment:** Mandatory Autopilot enrollment for identity-based policy enforcement.\n*   **BitLocker Encryption:** Full Disk Encryption (FDE) with recovery keys escrowed to the corporate Azure AD/Entra ID tenant.\n*   **CrowdStrike Falcon:** Installation of the latest sensor version (N-1) with "Aggressive" prevention policy enabled.\n*   **Golden Image Deployment:** Verification of the standard Cognizant SOE (Standard Operating Environment) baseline.\n*   **CyberArk Integration:** Deployment of the EPM (Endpoint Privilege Management) agent to enforce Least Privilege access.\n\n### 3. Compliance & Regulatory Standards\nThis directive is enforced under:\n*   **ISO/IEC 27001:2022 (A.8.1):** User endpoint device management.\n*   **Cognizant CISO Mandate:** Zero-Trust Architecture (ZTA) compliance requirement.\n*   **India’s DPDP Act 2023:** Mandatory implementation of "reasonable security safeguards" to prevent personal data breaches.\n*   **IT Act 2000 (Section 43A):** Liability for failure to maintain reasonable security practices for sensitive personal data or information (SPDI).\n\n### 4. Risk Rating: **CRITICAL**\n*   **Justification:** The risk of data loss on unencrypted devices, combined with the potential for unauthorized network entry through non-monitored endpoints, poses an existential threat to our client trust and legal compliance profile.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Action Plan (Execution Timeline: 72 Hours)\n\n| Timeframe | Action Item | Responsibility |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **0-12 Hours** | Quarantine all 20 units in the "Pending Secure Provisioning" VLAN. Block MAC addresses from accessing the production network. | Chennai IT Infra |\n| **12-36 Hours** | Execute Autopilot deployment. Verify successful check-in with **Intune** and **CrowdStrike Falcon** heartbeat. | Desktop Support Team |\n| **36-48 Hours** | Run an automated **Compliance Report** in Intune. Verify BitLocker status (must be \'Compliant/Encrypted\'). | Security Operations (SOC) |\n| **48-60 Hours** | Final audit of EPM policies via **CyberArk**. Ensure local admin rights are revoked for the associate. | Identity & Access Team |\n| **60-72 Hours** | Sign-off on the "Device Readiness Certificate." Only then release hardware to the designated associate. | Chennai IT Manager |\n\n**Non-compliance with this directive will be escalated to the Regional CISO office and may result in immediate suspension of the Chennai facility\'s provisioning privileges.**\n\n*Compliance is not optional; it is our baseline.*\n\n**[Authorized by]**\nOffice of the CISO, Cognizant India'}
