2026-07-10 02:29:25 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:29:25 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Finance_Risk_Agent\nTo: Procurement Operations / IT Infrastructure Team\nFrom: Office of the SVP, Finance & Risk Management, Cognizant India\nDate: October 26, 2023\nSubject: Financial Risk Assessment – Advance Payment Request: M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Financial Risk Assessment & Calculation\nThe requested amount of **\u20b92,32,332** falls into a high-risk category due to the "Advance Payment" nature, which deviates from standard Cognizant procurement policy.\n\n*   **Gross Amount:** \u20b92,32,332\n*   **GST Impact (18% on HSN 8471):**\n    *   Base Price: \u20b91,96,892\n    *   GST (18%): \u20b935,440\n    *   *Note: Ensure the vendor provides a valid Tax Invoice compliant with GST Rule 46 to enable Input Tax Credit (ITC) claim.*\n*   **Approval Threshold Status:**\n    *   The amount exceeds the **\u20b92 Lakh threshold**, mandating mandatory **VP Finance sign-off**.\n    *   Since it is an advance payment, this also triggers an **Exception to Policy (ETP)** process.\n\n### 2. Budget Head & Cost Center\n*   **Budget Head:** Capital Expenditure (CAPEX) – IT Infrastructure / Hardware Refresh.\n*   **Cost Center:** Must be mapped to the specific BU/Function requesting the hardware. \n*   **Action:** The request must be routed through the Ariba/Coupa workflow with the specific Cost Center code attached. Finance will verify if the remaining budget for this Cost Center for FY2023-24 can absorb this outflow without triggering a budget variance report.\n\n### 3. Payment Terms & Policy Compliance\nPer Cognizant India Financial Policy, standard payment terms are **Net-30 days** post-delivery and verification. An advance payment request constitutes a significant risk to the organization.\n\n*   **Risk Mitigation Requirement:** As this is an advance payment, M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd. must provide a **Bank Guarantee (BG)** for the full amount (\u20b92,32,332) valid until the delivery and successful commissioning of the hardware.\n*   **ETP Requirement:** The requestor must document the business justification for the advance (e.g., supply chain scarcity or vendor-specific credit terms). This ETP must be approved by the Finance Controller before the payment is released in the ERP.\n\n### 4. FY Impact Analysis\n*   **FY Cycle:** Cognizant India follows the April–March fiscal year.\n*   **Cash Flow:** Releasing this payment in the current period will impact our Q3/Q4 Cash Flow projections. \n*   **Asset Capitalization:** Since this is hardware (HSN 8471), the amount must be capitalized as an asset upon receipt. Depreciation will be calculated on a pro-rata basis from the date of deployment in the current FY.\n\n### 5. Mandatory Action Items\n1.  **Vendor Master Check:** Confirm M/s. Rashi Peripherals is active in our ERP with updated GSTIN and banking details.\n2.  **Workflow Routing:** \n    *   Submit via Ariba/Coupa.\n    *   Attach the **ETP Form** signed by the BU Head.\n    *   Attach the **Bank Guarantee** copy.\n3.  **Financial Approval:** Upon receipt of the above, I will review for final VP Finance sign-off. \n\n**Risk Verdict:** **High Risk.** The request is currently non-compliant with standard payment terms. **Do not initiate the payment** until the ETP is approved and the Bank Guarantee is verified by the Treasury team.\n\nRegards,\n\n**Senior VP, Finance & Risk Management**\nCognizant India'}
