2026-07-10 02:29:26 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:29:26 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from HR_Safety_Agent\nAs the Head of HR for Cognizant India, I have outlined the process for managing the allocation of these 20 assets for our upcoming cohort in the Chennai delivery center. \n\nTo ensure we meet the **Monday, 13 July 2026** deadline, we must adhere strictly to our internal workflows.\n\n### 1. Impact Assessment\n*   **Affected Headcount:** 20 new associates (likely Grade C1/C2 - Entry-level/Associate).\n*   **Grade Levels:** C1 (Entry-level) / C2 (Associate).\n*   **Required Action:** Ensure all 20 associates have their Workday profiles fully transitioned to "Active" status by EOD Friday, 10 July, to trigger the provisioning workflow.\n\n### 2. Asset Allocation: The NHOK Process\nPer Cognizant’s **New Hire Onboarding Kit (NHOK)** policy, we must ensure IT readiness. Since the onboarding is Monday, 13 July:\n\n*   **ServiceNow Protocol:** The request must be raised via the **ServiceNow portal** using the catalog item **\'New Hire IT Setup\'**. \n*   **Timeline Compliance:** Per policy, IT requests must be submitted at least **5 days prior** to the joining date. Given the lead time, the Chennai Onboarding Lead must verify that the 20 asset tags are already mapped to the specific Employee IDs in the Asset Management module.\n*   **Validation:** Confirm with the Chennai IT Support Team that the "Ready for Pickup/Dispatch" status is reflected in the **IT Asset Dashboard** by Friday, 10 July.\n\n### 3. Safety & Compliance\nWhile this is an asset deployment task, if any physical handling of hardware is required at the Chennai delivery center, we must adhere to our **Occupational Safety and Health (OSH) Policy** and the **Factories Act, 1948** (specifically regarding ergonomic workstation setup and safety protocols for employees handling electronic equipment). Ensure the Chennai facility’s floor manager confirms the seating and hardware station is compliant with local safety standards.\n\n### 4. Internal Communication Memo Template\n\n**Subject:** Action Required: Onboarding Readiness for 13 July Batch – Chennai DC\n\n**Dear Chennai Onboarding Team,**\n\nWith the upcoming onboarding of 20 associates scheduled for Monday, 13 July 2026, I am reaching out to ensure our \'CognizantOne\' associate experience is seamless from Day 1.\n\nPlease confirm the following by EOD, Friday, 10 July:\n1. **IT Readiness:** Verify that the \'New Hire IT Setup\' requests in ServiceNow are marked as \'Provisioned\' for all 20 Employee IDs.\n2. **NHOK Verification:** Ensure all 20 laptops are staged at the designated Chennai delivery center onboarding zone.\n3. **Workday Sync:** Verify that all 20 profiles are active in Workday to ensure seamless access to the \'CognizantOne\' portal.\n\nLet’s ensure these new associates have a smooth transition into the Cognizant family. If there are any blockers regarding asset availability or account provisioning, please escalate them to the HRBP office immediately.\n\nRegards,\n\n**Head of Human Resources, Cognizant India**\n\n---\n\n### 5. Tools Reference\n*   **Workday HRMS:** Use the "Manage Onboarding" dashboard to track the status of the 20 new joiners.\n*   **iHR Portal:** Refer to the "Onboarding & Induction" knowledge base if any associate reports issues with their pre-boarding credentials.\n*   **ServiceNow:** The primary source of truth for tracking the \'New Hire IT Setup\' ticket status.'}
