2026-07-10 02:29:30 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow: {"type": "AI", "text": "### Executive Action Summary: Hardware Procurement & Onboarding Readiness\n\n**TO:** Executive Leadership Team, Cognizant India\n**FROM:** Office of the Chief of Staff\n**DATE:** Friday, 10 July 2026 | 02:28 AM IST\n**SUBJECT:** Urgent Procurement Approval & Onboarding Risk Mitigation (Chennai Delivery Center)\n\n---\n\n### 1. Procurement & Financial Strategy\n*   **Status:** **REJECTED** (Advance Payment Request).\n*   **Rationale:** The request for an advance payment of **₹2,32,332** to M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd. violates standard corporate Net-30 payment terms and exposes Cognizant to significant financial risk. Per Finance policy, any deviation (Exception to Policy) requires a Bank Guarantee (BG) of equivalent value, which is not feasible within a 3-day window.\n*   **Action:** Procurement must leverage our Master Service Agreement (MSA) to demand priority fulfillment based on volume history.\n\n### 2. Legal & Regulatory Compliance\n*   **Indian Contract Act, 1872:** The procurement team must ensure the Purchase Order (PO) includes a \"Time is of the Essence\" clause and a defined Liquidated Damages (LD) provision (capped at 10%) to protect Cognizant against delivery failure.\n*   **Statutory Compliance:** Ensure all tax invoices comply with GST Rule 46 to enable Input Tax Credit (ITC) claims. Any failure to deliver by the stipulated deadline will be treated as a \"refusal to perform\" under Section 39 of the Indian Contract Act.\n\n### 3. Cyber Security & Asset Management\n*   **Security Posture:** Devices constitute a \"High Risk\" until fully onboarded.\n*   **Mandatory Protocol:** No laptop is to be handed over to a new joiner until it is marked \"Compliant\" in Microsoft Intune, with BitLocker encryption active and CrowdStrike Falcon/Microsoft Defender sensors reporting active heartbeats.\n*   **Compliance:** All units must be registered in the ServiceNow CMDB and tagged with a CTS Asset Tag prior to deployment to satisfy **DPDP Act 2023** and **ISO 27001:2022** requirements.\n\n### 4. HR & Onboarding Coordination\n*   **Readiness:** 20 new associates are joining the Chennai delivery center on Monday, 13 July 2026.\n*   **Requirement:** The Chennai Onboarding Lead must verify that all 20 Employee IDs have the \"New Hire IT Setup\" request status as \"Provisioned\" in ServiceNow by EOD today, Friday, 10 July.\n\n---\n\n### STATUS: UNDER REVIEW (Procurement Strategy Adjusted)\n\n### NEXT STEPS\n1.  **Procurement Team (Lead: Head of Procurement):** Negotiate \"Priority Fulfillment\" with Rashi Peripherals without advance payment; raise SAP PO (ME21N) immediately. **Deadline: 10 July, 12:00 PM IST.**\n2.  **Asset Management/IT Infrastructure (Lead: IT Manager, Chennai):** Confirm local stock readiness and initiate the 72-hour provisioning roadmap (Autopilot/Golden Image/Security Stack). **Deadline: 12 July, 06:00 PM IST.**\n3.  **Security Operations Center (SOC) (Lead: CISO Chennai):** Perform final compliance audit on all 20 units before physical handover. **Deadline: 13 July, 08:00 AM IST.**\n4.  **HRBP (Lead: HR Manager, Chennai):** Verify all 20 associates' Workday profiles and confirm \"Onboarding Readiness\" to the project manager. **Deadline: 10 July, 05:00 PM IST.**"}
