es if the service provider is registered in a different state than the Cognizant entity receiving the invoice.\n\n### 4. Compliance Status Determination\n\n**ACTION REQUIRED:** Please provide the following details to finalize the status:\n1.  **Nature of Data:** Did the incident involve PII (Personally Identifiable Information)? (Triggers DPDP Act).\n2.  **Operational Impact:** Is there a disruption to Cognizant’s service delivery to clients? (Triggers SEBI LODR material event disclosure).\n3.  **Time of Discovery:** When was the incident first logged in the ITSM tool?\n\n#### Current Status Matrix:\n*   **COMPLIANT:** If the incident is a minor internal glitch with no data leakage or service disruption.\n*   **ACTION REQUIRED:** If the incident involves any unauthorized access or data exfiltration. **You must immediately notify the CERT-In portal (cert-in.org.in) within the 6-hour window.**\n*   **BREACH:** If the 6-hour window has already elapsed without filing a report for a reportable incident under the CERT-In 2022 mandate.\n\n**Immediate Directive:** \nIf this incident involves a breach of customer data or a ransomware attack, **do not wait for further analysis.** File an initial "Preliminary Report" with CERT-In to stop the clock on non-compliance, and simultaneously notify the Legal & Compliance Office to assess the materiality threshold under SEBI LODR.\n\n**Please provide the incident summary to confirm if the 6-hour window is still open.**'}
