2026-07-10 02:40:09 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow: {"type": "AI", "text": "### Executive Action Summary: Incident INC2417058\n\nThis memorandum summarizes the multi-departmental assessment of incident **INC2417058**, which involves a P1-level disruption to the Core Banking Transaction Engine.\n\n### 1. Delivery & Client Management (Customer Support)\n*   **Status:** P1 Critical Impact. Service degradation affecting retail banking payment processing.\n*   **SLA Exposure:** 4-hour resolution window active. Breach triggers a 10-15% service credit penalty on the monthly billing cycle.\n*   **Action:** Level 3 Engineering SWAT team is active. Executive presence established on the client bridge. Root Cause Analysis (RCA) committed within 24 hours of resolution.\n\n### 2. Cybersecurity & Infrastructure Hardening\n*   **Risk:** Potential for unauthorized lateral movement and exfiltration of PII/SPI.\n*   **Compliance:** Immediate adherence to *Global Information Security Policy (GISP)* and India DPDP Act 2023 (Section 8(5)).\n*   **Action:** Assets isolated via CrowdStrike Falcon; global credential reset initiated for impacted identities. Forensic imaging of affected endpoints is underway. **No \"clean-up\" permitted until forensic logs are captured.**\n\n### 3. Legal & Regulatory Compliance\n*   **Regulatory Obligation:** Mandatory 6-hour reporting window to **CERT-In** (IT Act 2000, Section 70B) is active. Failure to report constitutes a significant regulatory breach.\n*   **Contractual Status:** Limitation of Liability clause invoked to protect against open-ended damages. Arbitration (if required) will be seated in Mumbai/Chennai under the Arbitration & Conciliation Act, 1996.\n*   **Action:** Legal Counsel to review *Force Majeure* eligibility to contest potential SLA credit payouts.\n\n### 4. Financial Risk & Budgetary Impact\n*   **Total Exposure:** Estimated at **₹24.16 Lakhs** (₹14.16 Lakhs hardware/GST + ₹10 Lakhs potential SLA credits).\n*   **Budgeting:** Contingency OPEX (Account 6200-IT-Maint). Any procurement >₹2 Lakhs requires SVP Finance authorization.\n*   **Action:** Exception to Policy (ETP) workflow required for any advance vendor payments. Provision for contingent liability to be recorded per Ind AS 37.\n\n---\n\n**STATUS: ESCALATED**\n\n**NEXT STEPS:**\n1.  **Regulatory Filing:** Compliance Office to file the Preliminary Report with **CERT-In** immediately (Owner: Head of Compliance).\n2.  **Financial Approval:** CFO to review and sign off on the ₹24.16 Lakhs budget variance by Friday, 17:00 IST (Owner: Finance/Accounting Lead).\n3.  **Client Communication:** VP of Client Services to provide next status update on the client bridge at 16:30 IST (Owner: Delivery Head).\n4.  **Forensics:** SOC Manager to provide the initial forensic report to the CISO by Saturday, 10:00 IST (Owner: SOC Manager).\n5.  **Contractual Review:** Legal to submit *Force Majeure* memo by Monday, 12:00 IST (Owner: Associate General Counsel)."}
