2026-07-10 02:40:21 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:40:20 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Finance_Risk_Agent\nTo provide a precise financial assessment for **INC2417058**, I am proceeding under the assumption that this incident involves the urgent procurement of high-end IT infrastructure (servers/workstations) for the Bangalore campus. \n\nAs the Senior VP of Finance & Risk Management, my assessment is as follows:\n\n### 1. Financial Risk Assessment & INR Impact\nAssuming the procurement request (INC2417058) involves an invoice value of **\u20b915,00,000 (Base Price)** for hardware:\n\n*   **Base Value:** \u20b915,00,000\n*   **GST Liability (18% on HSN 8471):** \u20b92,70,000\n*   **Total Liability (Gross):** **\u20b917,70,000**\n\n**Risk Assessment:**\n*   **Approval Threshold Breach:** This exceeds the \u20b910 Lakhs limit, triggering a **mandatory CFO sign-off**. Any attempt to split this purchase order (PO) into smaller invoices to bypass the CFO threshold is a violation of the Cognizant Code of Business Ethics and will be flagged as a high-risk audit finding.\n*   **Liquidity Risk:** If this is a one-time unbudgeted expense, it creates an immediate variance in the Bangalore campus Opex/Capex budget.\n\n### 2. Budget Head & Cost Center\n*   **Budget Head:** IT Infrastructure / Hardware Refresh (Capex).\n*   **Cost Center:** **BLR-INFRA-001** (Bangalore Campus Infrastructure).\n*   **FY Impact:** Cognizant India FY runs from April 1 to March 31. This expense will be recognized in the current quarter (Qx). If the vendor delivers post-March 31, the liability shifts to the next fiscal year, impacting the current budget utilization forecast.\n\n### 3. Payment Terms & Compliance\n*   **Standard Terms:** Our default is **Net-30 days**. \n*   **Advance Payment Protocol:** If the vendor demands an advance, it is strictly prohibited without a **Bank Guarantee (BG)** equal to the advance amount.\n*   **Exception to Policy (ETP):** Any deviation from Net-30 or a request for advance payment requires a formal **ETP approval** submitted through the Ariba/Coupa workflow, routed through Finance. Without this, the payment will be blocked by the Shared Services center.\n\n### 4. Summary of Required Actions for INC2417058\nTo proceed with this procurement, the following documentation is required:\n\n1.  **Approval Matrix:** \n    *   VP Finance Sign-off (Required for >\u20b92L).\n    *   **CFO Sign-off** (Mandatory for >\u20b910L).\n2.  **Tax Compliance:** Ensure the vendor invoice reflects the correct GSTIN for the Bangalore entity. The 18% GST input tax credit must be claimed in the GSTR-3B filing for the month of the invoice date.\n3.  **Procurement Gateway:** The request must be logged in the **Coupa/Ariba portal**. Ensure the "Bill To" and "Ship To" addresses are correctly mapped to the Bangalore GST-registered location.\n4.  **Vendor Risk:** Confirm the vendor is active in our ERP system and has passed the **Vendor Due Diligence (VDD)** check regarding financial stability and anti-bribery/corruption compliance.\n\n**Recommendation:** \nDo not authorize the release of the PO until the CFO approval is attached to the INC ticket. Given the value, the procurement team must also verify that this hardware is not available through our existing global master supply agreements (MSAs) to ensure we are receiving the negotiated corporate discount rate.\n\n**Please provide the exact invoice value if it differs from the \u20b915 Lakhs estimate so I can recalibrate the tax liability and approval routing.**'}
