2026-07-10 02:46:48 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:46:48 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'As the Head of HR for Cognizant India, I have outlined the protocol for the onboarding asset lifecycle for the 20 new joiners at our Chennai delivery centers. Ensuring seamless asset deployment is a critical component of the **\'CognizantOne\'** associate experience framework, as it sets the tone for the new hire\'s professional journey.\n\n### 1. Impact Assessment\n*   **Affected Headcount:** 20 new associates.\n*   **Grade Levels:** Typically C1–C3 (Entry-level to Senior Associate).\n*   **Communication:** A "Welcome to Cognizant" email must be triggered via the automated onboarding workflow, including instructions on how to collect the asset from the Chennai IT Helpdesk/Onboarding Lounge on their DOJ (Date of Joining).\n\n### 2. Asset Allocation & ServiceNow Protocol\nTo ensure compliance with Cognizant’s Global Asset Management policy, the following steps are mandatory:\n\n*   **ServiceNow Request:** The TA (Talent Acquisition) team or the hiring manager must raise a request via the **ServiceNow catalog item: \'New Hire IT Setup\'**. \n*   **Timeline:** This must be submitted no later than **5 business days prior** to the DOJ. \n*   **Asset Tagging:** All 20 Dell Latitude 5540 units must be scanned into the **Workday HRMS/Asset Management module** upon receipt from the vendor. The IT team must ensure the serial number is mapped to the Associate ID immediately upon handover.\n*   **Compliance:** Physical verification of the asset tag must be performed by the IT asset custodian. Associates will be required to sign a digital **\'Asset Acknowledgement Form\'** via the iHR portal upon logging in for the first time.\n\n### 3. Safety & Policy Alignment\nWhile this is an asset allocation task, all IT hardware setup must comply with the **Cognizant Occupational Safety and Health (OSH) policy**. Ensure that the workstation area designated for these 20 associates meets the ergonomic standards prescribed under the **Factories Act, 1948** (as applicable to our office infrastructure), ensuring adequate lighting, ventilation, and safe electrical grounding for the docking stations.\n\n### 4. Internal Communication Memo Template\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** Action Required: IT Asset Provisioning for [Batch Date] New Joiners – Chennai\n\n**Dear IT Operations Team,**\n\nIn alignment with our \'CognizantOne\' onboarding excellence initiative, we are preparing for the induction of 20 new associates in Chennai on [Date]. \n\nTo ensure a seamless Day 1 experience, please prioritize the following:\n\n*   **Asset Allocation:** 20 Dell Latitude 5540 laptops have been identified for this cohort. Please ensure these are staged in the Chennai Onboarding Lounge by [Date - 1 day before DOJ].\n*   **ServiceNow Compliance:** Please verify that the \'New Hire IT Setup\' tickets have been processed for all 20 associates. \n*   **Asset Tracking:** Ensure all 20 assets are updated in the inventory management system with the correct asset tags linked to the respective Associate IDs.\n\nOur goal is to ensure that every associate is "plug-and-play" ready by 10:00 AM on their DOJ. Should there be any delays in procurement or imaging, please escalate to the HR Business Partner (HRBP) team immediately.\n\nThank you for your partnership in delivering a world-class onboarding experience.\n\nBest regards,\n\n**[Your Name/Head of HR]**\nCognizant India\n\n***\n\n### 5. Tool References\n*   **Workday HRMS:** Used for tracking the associate\'s lifecycle status from \'Pre-hire\' to \'Active\'.\n*   **iHR Portal:** The primary source for associates to track their asset status and raise support tickets if they face issues with the Latitude 5540 configuration.\n*   **ServiceNow:** The single source of truth for IT hardware provisioning and tracking.'}
2026-07-10 02:46:48 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 02:46:48 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'As the Senior VP of Finance & Risk Management for Cognizant India, I have evaluated the proposal to issue an advance payment of **\u20b92,32,332** to M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd. \n\nBelow is the formal financial risk assessment and compliance roadmap for this transaction.\n\n### 1. Financial Risk Assessment & GST Calculation\nThe proposed payment is for IT hardware (HSN 8471). Under GST law, the tax liability arises at the time of receipt of advance payment.\n\n*   **Base Amount:** \u20b91,96,891.53\n*   **GST (18%):** \u20b935,440.47\n*   **Total Advance:** **\u20b92,32,332.00**\n\n**Risk Assessment:**\n*   **Liquidity Risk:** Outflow of working capital ahead of asset delivery.\n*   **Performance Risk:** High risk of "Non-Delivery" or "Defective Supply" without a corresponding Bank Guarantee (BG).\n*   **Audit Risk:** Advance payments are red-flagged in internal audits unless supported by a formal Exception to Policy (ETP).\n\n### 2. Budgetary Control & Approval Thresholds\n*   **Budget Head:** IT Infrastructure / Hardware Procurement.\n*   **Cost Center:** [To be specified by the Requester, e.g., CC: 12345 - India IT Ops].\n*   **Approval Matrix:** \n    *   Since the amount exceeds **\u20b92 Lakhs**, this transaction **strictly requires my (VP Finance) sign-off**.\n    *   As it is below \u20b910 Lakhs, it does not require CFO sign-off, but it must be logged in the Ariba/Coupa system with the ETP documentation attached.\n\n### 3. Payment Terms & Compliance Requirements\nCognizant India’s standard procurement policy mandates **Net-30 days** post-delivery and invoice verification. Deviating to an advance payment triggers the following mandatory controls:\n\n1.  **Bank Guarantee (BG):** The vendor must provide an unconditional, irrevocable Bank Guarantee for the full amount (\u20b92,32,332) valid for the duration of the delivery lead time plus a 30-day buffer.\n2.  **Exception to Policy (ETP):** The business owner must submit a formal ETP request justifying why standard credit terms could not be negotiated. \n3.  **Vendor Master Check:** Verification that Rashi Peripherals is active in our ERP and that their GST registration is "Active" on the portal to ensure we can claim the Input Tax Credit (ITC) of \u20b935,440.47.\n\n### 4. FY Impact (FY 2024-25)\n*   **Cash Flow:** The \u20b92.32 Lakh outflow will hit the Q1/Q2 cash flow statement immediately upon disbursement.\n*   **Capex/Opex Treatment:** If the hardware is capitalized, the depreciation will commence from the date the asset is put to use. If expensed, it will hit the P&L as a direct cost in the current FY (April–March).\n*   **Impact:** This will reduce the available budget for the specific Cost Center for the remainder of the fiscal year.\n\n### Final Recommendation\n**I do not approve this payment at this stage.** \n\n**Required Actions for Approval:**\n1.  **Submit ETP:** Justify why Rashi Peripherals requires an advance (e.g., supply chain scarcity).\n2.  **BG Submission:** Upload the scanned copy of the Bank Guarantee into the Coupa/Ariba requisition.\n3.  **Procurement Validation:** Ensure the purchase order (PO) reflects the advance payment terms, not just the invoice.\n\nOnce the ETP is filed and the BG is verified by the Treasury team, resubmit the request to my desk for the required VP-level sign-off.'}
