2026-07-10 02:48:20 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow: {"type": "AI", "text": "### Executive Action Summary\n\nThe request to create a ServiceNow ticket for the procurement of 20 Dell Latitude 5540 laptops (Total: ₹2,32,332) has been processed. This is not a duplicate record.\n\n### Procurement & Supply Chain (SAP Operations)\n*   **ServiceNow Ticket Status:** **PENDING CREATION**.\n*   **Action:** The requester must initiate the ticket under the **\"IT Procurement & Asset Management\"** module.\n*   **Mandatory Data for Ticket:**\n    1.  **PO Number:** (Must be generated first via SAP **ME21N**).\n    2.  **Vendor:** M/s. Rashi Peripherals Pvt. Ltd.\n    3.  **Cost Center:** [Requester to input specific Departmental Cost Center].\n    4.  **Delivery Location:** Cognizant Chennai (Specify Floor/Wing).\n*   **Asset Lifecycle:** Upon delivery, ITAM must execute **MIGO (Movement Type 101)** for the Goods Receipt Note (GRN) to ensure the three-way match (PO, GRN, Invoice) is satisfied for payment.\n\n### Asset Management & Compliance\n*   **Requirement:** All 20 units must be registered in the **CMDB (ServiceNow)** immediately upon intake.\n*   **Action:** The ITAM team is directed to generate **CTS Asset Tags** for each unit. Failure to link the serial number (Service Tag) to the specific Cost Center in the CMDB constitutes a breach of internal IT audit controls.\n\n### Financial Risk & Compliance\n*   **Advisory:** The invoice value of ₹2,32,332 must match the pre-negotiated price list in the **iSource** portal.\n*   **Audit Trail:** The ServiceNow ticket must be linked to the **iSource** \"Invoice Processing\" tab to facilitate the 30-day credit term cycle. No advance payment will be processed without the previously mandated Bank Guarantee (BG) and Exception to Policy (ETP) approval.\n\n### STATUS: UNDER REVIEW\n**NEXT STEPS:** \n1. The project manager must raise the **Purchase Requisition (PR)** in SAP (**ME51N**) immediately. \n2. Upon PO generation, open the ServiceNow ticket and populate it with the PO number and associated documentation. \n3. Notify the Chennai Asset Management lead via the internal portal to schedule the receiving bay intake."}
