2026-07-10 10:31:51 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 10:31:51 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Social_Media_Agent\nAs the Head of Social Media & Digital Reputation for Cognizant India, I am treating this situation as a **Tier-2 Reputation Risk**. The conflict involves a B2B service delivery dispute that has spilled into the public domain, potentially impacting our employer brand and client trust.\n\n### 1. Social Media Risk Assessment\n*   **Current Status:** Monitoring active threads.\n*   **Viral Spread Potential:** **Medium (1K–5K mentions/engagements in 24 hours).** The topic is niche (B2B/IT services) but is gaining traction among the tech-influencer community and industry analysts.\n*   **Risk Drivers:** Potential for the narrative to shift from a "contractual dispute" to a "service quality/competency" issue, which could affect future deal cycles.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Draft Response Content\n*Note: Our strategy is to maintain a professional, neutral, and non-litigious tone. We do not litigate specific client disputes on public forums.*\n\n**X (Twitter) - Strategy: "De-escalation & Redirect"**\n*Draft:* "At Cognizant, we value our client relationships and are committed to maintaining the highest standards of service delivery. We are aware of the ongoing discussions and are addressing the matter directly with the client involved. We remain focused on delivering value for all our partners."\n\n**LinkedIn - Strategy: "Corporate Integrity Post"**\n*Draft:* "At Cognizant, our reputation is built on the trust our clients place in us. We hold ourselves to rigorous delivery standards and maintain robust governance frameworks to resolve contractual or service-related queries. While we do not comment on specific client-vendor disputes in the public domain, we want to assure our stakeholders, associates, and investors that our commitment to operational excellence remains our top priority. We continue to engage constructively with all our partners to ensure mutual success. #Cognizant #BusinessIntegrity #OperationalExcellence"\n\n---\n\n### 3. IT Rules 2021 (Intermediary Guidelines) Compliance\n*   **Reporting Analysis:** Under the IT Rules 2021, we are monitoring for **defamatory, impersonation, or misinformation content**.\n*   **Action:** If any user is found circulating falsified documents (e.g., doctored emails or contracts) or using fake accounts to spread malicious misinformation, we will initiate a **"Report Abuse"** filing under *Rule 3(2)(b)*, which mandates that intermediaries must remove content that is "patently false and untrue" or "misleads or misinforms."\n*   **Trigger:** We will only flag content that crosses the threshold into malicious defamation or breach of confidentiality/IP.\n\n---\n\n### 4. 24-Hour Monitoring Action Plan\n\n| Time Frame | Action Item | Platform/Tool |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **0-4 Hours** | Baseline sentiment analysis using Brandwatch/Sprout Social. Identify "High-Influence" accounts driving the narrative. | X, LinkedIn |\n| **4-8 Hours** | Deploy "Community Management" team to monitor comments. Do not engage with trolls; hide/block only if they violate platform TOS. | All |\n| **8-12 Hours** | Brief internal stakeholders (Legal & Corporate Comms). Prepare a "Holding Statement" for incoming media inquiries. | Internal |\n| **12-24 Hours** | Evaluate if the conversation is organic or "bot-driven." If bot activity is detected, report the cluster to X Trust & Safety. | X |\n\n**Key Performance Indicators (KPIs):**\n1.  **Sentiment Score:** Aiming to move from "Negative/Neutral" to "Neutral/Fact-based."\n2.  **Share of Voice:** Monitor if the negative conversation is being drowned out by positive corporate updates.\n3.  **Direct Message (DM) Volume:** Monitor if clients or prospective employees are reaching out for clarification; respond to these via a dedicated high-touch team.\n\n**Directives to Team:**\n*   Do not engage in arguments.\n*   Do not confirm or deny specific contractual details.\n*   Escalate any mentions from Tier-1 tech journalists to the Global PR lead immediately.'}
