2026-07-10 10:41:07 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 10:41:07 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from Finance_Risk_Agent\n**MEMORANDUM**\n\n**TO:** Procurement / Chennai Delivery Center Project Lead\n**FROM:** SVP, Finance & Risk Management, Cognizant India\n**DATE:** October 26, 2023\n**SUBJECT:** Financial Risk Assessment & Emergency Approval Protocol: Chennai Delivery Center Kickoff\n\nI have reviewed the reported payment failure of **â‚¹18,50,000** related to the Chennai Delivery Center infrastructure procurement. Given the critical nature of the kickoff timeline, I have conducted a formal risk assessment and outlined the mandatory compliance path for re-processing.\n\n### 1. Financial Risk Assessment & Tax Calculation\nThe total invoice value of â‚¹18,50,000 requires immediate reconciliation to avoid breach of contract with our hardware vendor.\n\n*   **Base Invoice Value:** â‚¹15,67,797\n*   **GST (18% on HSN 8471):** â‚¹2,82,203\n*   **Total Payment Liability:** **â‚¹18,50,000**\n*   **Risk Exposure:**\n    *   **Operational Risk:** Delay in kickoff impacts billable capacity for Q3/Q4. Every week of delay results in an estimated productivity loss of ~â‚¹45 Lakhs in potential revenue.\n    *   **Financial Risk:** Late payment penalties (as per standard vendor MSME/Corporate terms) and potential disruption to supply chain continuity.\n\n### 2. Budget Head & Cost Center\n*   **Budget Head:** Capital Expenditure (CAPEX) â€“ IT Infrastructure / Delivery Center Expansion.\n*   **Cost Center:** CHN-OPS-DC-2023 (Chennai Delivery Center Expansion).\n*   **FY Impact:** This expenditure falls within the **FY 2023-24 (Aprilâ€“March)** budget cycle. The depletion of this budget line must be reconciled against the Q3 CAPEX forecast to ensure we do not exceed the approved regional allocation.\n\n### 3. Payment Terms & Compliance Protocol\nSince the payment amount (â‚¹18,50,000) exceeds the **â‚¹10 Lakh threshold**, this transaction triggers a **CFO sign-off requirement**. \n\n*   **Standard Terms:** Net-30 days.\n*   **If Advance Payment is requested:** \n    *   A **Bank Guarantee (BG)** for the full advance amount is mandatory. \n    *   An **Exception to Policy (ETP)** form must be attached to the Ariba/Coupa requisition, citing "Project Criticality" and "Business Continuity."\n*   **Approval Workflow:**\n    *   **Level 1:** Procurement Head (Validation of HSN/GST).\n    *   **Level 2:** SVP Finance (Verification of Cost Center availability).\n    *   **Level 3:** CFO (Final authorization due to >â‚¹10 Lakhs threshold).\n\n### 4. Emergency Approval Instructions\nTo mitigate the risk of further delay, proceed with the following actions immediately:\n\n1.  **Re-submission:** Re-initiate the payment in the **Coupa/Ariba portal** under the \'Emergency/Urgent\' flag.\n2.  **Documentation:** Attach the original invoice, the Proof of Delivery (POD) or Goods Receipt Note (GRN), and the internal memo detailing the payment failure root cause.\n3.  **ETP Request:** If this payment includes any advance, upload the BG document and the signed ETP form.\n4.  **Notification:** Once submitted, provide me with the **Requisition ID**. I will fast-track the VP-level approval and escalate the request to the CFOâ€™s office for final sign-off within 4 business hours.\n\n**Warning:** Do not attempt to split the invoice into smaller tranches to bypass the â‚¹10 Lakh CFO threshold. Any such attempt constitutes a violation of Cognizantâ€™s Global Financial Integrity Policy and will be treated as a serious compliance breach.\n\nRegards,\n\n**Senior VP, Finance & Risk Management**\nCognizant India'}
