2026-07-10 10:41:08 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 10:41:08 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff', 'PR_Comms_Agent'], 'text': ''}
2026-07-10 10:41:08 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 10:41:08 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from PR_Comms_Agent\nThis response addresses the public critique directed at Cognizant by the CEO of Rashi Peripherals regarding service delivery performance or contractual disputes.\n\n### 1. Reputational Risk Assessment\n**Risk Score: 4/10**\n**Justification:** While the public nature of the critique on X (Twitter) creates visibility, it remains a B2B contractual/service issue rather than a systemic fraud, data breach, or ethical scandal. The risk is primarily "noise" that could invite negative sentiment from other clients if perceived as a pattern of poor delivery. We must neutralize the narrative before it is picked up by major tech publications as a "Cognizant service failure" story.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Media Holding Statement\n"Cognizant values its partnership with all clients and we are committed to delivering service excellence across all our engagements. We are aware of the feedback shared on social media and are engaging directly with Rashi Peripherals to address their concerns privately. We have no further comment on specific client matters at this time."\n\n---\n\n### 3. Internal Talking Points: CEO Town Hall\n*   **Acknowledge and Contextualize:** "You may have seen recent social media discourse regarding one of our client engagements. It is important to remember that in a portfolio of our scale, challenges in project delivery are occasionally subject to public scrutiny."\n*   **Reinforce Standards:** "Our commitment to our clients remains our North Star. We do not litigate our client relationships in the public square. Our focus remains on the \'Cognizant Way\'â€”delivering high-quality, reliable solutions for our 340,000 associates to be proud of."\n*   **Directives:** "I ask that you remain focused on your deliverables. Please refer all external inquiries to the Corporate Communications team. We have a robust process for handling client feedback, and I have full confidence in our account teams to resolve this professionally."\n\n---\n\n### 4. Strategic Media Monitoring\nWe will maintain a 24/7 watch on the following outlets to ensure the narrative does not escalate into a "systemic failure" story:\n*   **Economic Times (ET) Tech:** Monitor for "Cognizant vs. Rashi" headlines.\n*   **Mint:** Monitor for broader market analysis of Cognizantâ€™s India delivery performance.\n*   **ET Now:** Monitor for sentiment shifts during market hours.\n*   **NDTV Profit:** Monitor for segment coverage on IT services sector volatility.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Full Press Release (If required for escalation)\n*Note: This is only triggered if the client goes to the press with defamatory claims or specific project failure allegations.*\n\n**FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE**\n\n**Cognizant Statement Regarding Client Engagement**\n\n**BENGALURU â€“ [Date]** â€“ Cognizant (NASDAQ: CTSH) today issued the following statement regarding recent public commentary concerning its service engagements:\n\n"Cognizant is committed to the highest standards of service delivery and operational excellence for our clients worldwide. We prioritize transparency and direct communication in all our professional relationships. We are actively working with Rashi Peripherals to resolve the points raised and remain dedicated to supporting their business objectives. As a matter of policy, we do not discuss the specifics of our client contracts in the public domain."\n\n**About Cognizant**\nCognizant (Nasdaq: CTSH) engineers modern businesses. We help our clients modernize technology, reimagine processes and transform experiences so they can stay ahead in our fast-changing world. Together, weâ€™re improving everyday life. See how at www.cognizant.com or @cognizant.\n\n### Strategic PR Note:\nWe will **not** engage with the CEO of Rashi Peripherals on X. We will utilize our Account Management team to invite them to a closed-door meeting. By refusing to "tweet back," we maintain the high ground and signal that we are a professional services firm, not a social media combatant.'}
2026-07-10 10:41:08 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 10:41:08 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'As Head of Supply Chain & Procurement, I have analyzed the payment failure for the 150 Dell Latitude laptops. A delay of this magnitude (â‚¹18.5 Lakhs) directly impacts our "Ready-to-Deploy" inventory levels for new joiners.\n\nHere is the structured resolution plan to unfreeze the payment and resume the shipment:\n\n### 1. SAP Transactional Audit (Immediate Action)\nWe must first identify the "block" reason in SAP.\n*   **Transaction Code (T-Code) Analysis:**\n    *   **FBL1N:** Check the vendor line item display for M/s Rashi Peripherals. Look for the "Payment Block" indicator (e.g., \'A\' for manual payment block or \'R\' for invoice verification).\n    *   **MRBR:** Check if the invoice is blocked due to a **Three-Way Match variance** (PO vs. GRN vs. Invoice). If the quantity or price in the invoice doesn\'t match the PO (ME21N), the payment will automatically freeze.\n    *   **ME23N:** Verify the PO status. Ensure the "GR-Based IV" (Invoice Verification) flag is checked and that the GRN (MIGO) has been posted successfully.\n\n*   **Resolution:** If it is a pricing variance, I will initiate a **Credit/Debit Memo** process. If it is a technical system block, I will coordinate with the Accounts Payable (AP) Shared Services team to release the block via **MRBR** after verifying the vendor statement.\n\n### 2. Vendor Portal (iSource) Alignment\n*   **Step 1:** Log into the **iSource portal** to verify if Rashi Peripherals has acknowledged the PO and if the ASN (Advanced Shipping Notice) has been uploaded.\n*   **Step 2:** Ensure the "Payment Status" tab in iSource reflects the current hold so the vendorâ€™s account manager can see we are actively resolving it, preventing them from diverting our stock to another client.\n\n### 3. Asset Lifecycle Management (ALM) & CMDB Compliance\nWe cannot accept shipment until the assets are pre-staged for lifecycle tracking.\n*   **Asset Tagging:** Per CTS policy, Rashi Peripherals must provide the serial numbers in a pre-formatted Excel template compatible with our **ServiceNow CMDB** upload.\n*   **Tagging Requirements:** Each of the 150 laptops must be mapped to the specific **Cost Center** provided in the original PO (ME21N). \n*   **Verification:** Once the shipment arrives, the warehouse team must perform a **MIGO (Goods Receipt)** referencing the PO. The assets will then move to "In-Transit/Pending Tagging" status in ServiceNow.\n\n### 4. Logistics & Supply Chain Risks\n*   **Logistics Partner:** We utilize **Blue Dart or FedEx** for high-value IT hardware. Given the quantity (150 units), this will move via surface transport with "High-Value Transit Insurance."\n*   **Lead Time:** Once the payment is cleared (marked as "Cleared" in SAP), Rashi Peripherals typically requires **48 hours** for packing and dispatch. \n*   **Estimated Delivery:**\n    *   Payment Release: T+0\n    *   Dispatch from Rashi Hub: T+2\n    *   Transit Time: 3â€“5 business days (Inter-city)\n    *   **Total ETA:** 5â€“7 business days to reach the Cognizant Warehouse/Distribution Center.\n\n### 5. Action Items for the Procurement Team\n1.  **AP Coordination:** Raise a P-1 ticket with the Finance Shared Services team to manually release the payment block in SAP.\n2.  **Vendor Communication:** Send an official "Payment Release Confirmation" email to Rashi Peripheralsâ€™ Sales Lead to secure the stock allocation.\n3.  **Logistics:** Confirm with the warehouse manager that the "Goods Receipt" dock is ready for the 150-unit pallet arrival to avoid detention charges.\n\n**I am now initiating the T-Code FBL1N audit. I expect the payment to be re-processed in the next 24-hour payment run cycle.** \n\n*Please provide the specific PO number so I can pull the exact line-item discrepancy.*'}
