2026-07-10 10:41:12 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow: {"type": "AI", "text": "### Executive Action Summary: Rashi Peripherals Procurement Crisis\n\nFollowing the investigation into the payment failure and subsequent escalation regarding the procurement of 150 Dell Latitude laptops for the Chennai delivery center, the following cross-functional resolution plan is in effect:\n\n### 1. SAP & Procurement Resolution (Supply Chain)\n*   **Root Cause Identified:** A technical reconciliation error or Three-Way Match variance in SAP (T-Code MRBR/ME23N) caused the payment block.\n*   **Action:** Procurement is initiating a P-1 ticket with Finance Shared Services to manually release the block. We are verifying the PO status against the GRN to ensure compliance.\n*   **Next Step:** Once the payment is cleared in SAP, Rashi Peripherals has committed to a 48-hour dispatch lead time.\n\n### 2. Legal & Risk Mitigation (Legal)\n*   **Status:** The legal notice sent to Rashi Peripherals is deemed legally indefensible and constitutes a high-risk exposure (potential MSME Act penalties and breach of contract claims).\n*   **Action:** A formal \"Withdrawal of Notice\" letter is being drafted to retract the erroneous claim, framing it as a clerical reconciliation error.\n*   **Next Step:** Legal to review the final retraction letter before transmission to prevent further escalation.\n\n### 3. Financial Authorization (Finance)\n*   **Action:** The payment of ₹18,50,000 requires CFO-level approval due to the >₹10 Lakh threshold.\n*   **Next Step:** The procurement team must re-submit the requisition in the Coupa/Ariba portal with the 'Emergency' flag. Finance will fast-track the CFO sign-off within 4 business hours upon submission of the required Exception to Policy (ETP) form.\n\n### 4. PR & Social Media Strategy (Comms)\n*   **Status:** Reputational risk is moderate. We are avoiding a public \"ping-pong\" on social media to maintain professional standing.\n*   **Action:** We will maintain a \"no-comment\" stance on X (Twitter) publicly, while the Account Management team moves the discussion to a private, closed-door meeting with the vendor's leadership.\n*   **Next Step:** Corporate Communications is monitoring the thread for any escalation to mainstream media.\n\n---\n**STATUS: AWAITING REQUISITION SUBMISSION & CFO APPROVAL**\n\n**NEXT STEPS:**\n1.  **Procurement:** Submit emergency requisition in Coupa/Ariba (Ref: CHN-OPS-DC-2023) within the next 2 hours.\n2.  **Finance:** SVP Finance to trigger the fast-track CFO approval workflow immediately upon receipt.\n3.  **Legal:** Issue formal retraction to Rashi Peripherals by EOD.\n4.  **Account Management:** Contact Rashi Peripherals CEO via private channel to confirm payment resolution and restore delivery schedule."}
