d account or server identified as the source of the leak.\n*   **Revoke Credentials:** Reset credentials for all users who had access to the unencrypted files.\n*   **Validate Exposure:** Determine if the data was merely accessed or exfiltrated (check egress logs and forensic artifacts).\n\n#### Phase II: Investigation (Ongoing)\n*   **Forensic Analysis:** Engage the Cybersecurity Incident Response Team (CIRT) to determine the "patient zero" and the scope of the breach.\n*   **Encryption Audit:** Identify why these files were stored unencrypted in violation of the Data Handling Policy and remediate the storage configuration.\n\n#### Phase III: Communication (Legal/PR)\n*   **Legal Counsel:** Engage outside counsel to manage regulatory notifications and attorney-client privilege during the investigation.\n*   **Internal Disclosure:** Brief the Board of Directors and the Audit Committee regarding the potential material impact.\n*   **Stakeholder Notification:** If required by law, prepare a communication plan for shareholders, employees, and relevant regulatory bodies.\n\n#### Phase IV: Remediation & Recovery\n*   **Post-Mortem:** Conduct a root-cause analysis to address the failure of encryption controls.\n*   **Policy Enforcement:** Implement automated Data Loss Prevention (DLP) tools to scan for and block the storage of unencrypted sensitive financial documents.\n*   **Training:** Conduct mandatory refresher training for the Finance and Accounting departments on secure data handling and encryption standards.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Immediate Action Items for Management\n1.  **Freeze trading** (if applicable) for personnel with access to the leaked data to prevent insider trading allegations.\n2.  **Confirm the specific timestamp** of the breach to establish a timeline for regulators.\n3.  **Initiate a "Legal Hold"** on all communications related to the Q3 projections to preserve evidence for potential litigation or regulatory inquiries.\n\n***Disclaimer:** This document is a template for incident response. Please consult with your organization\'s Legal and Compliance departments immediately to ensure the response adheres to specific jurisdictional requirements and corporate bylaws.*'}
