2026-07-10 22:22:44 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow: {"type": "AI", "text": "### Executive Action Summary: CFO Laptop Theft (Mumbai)\n\n**Incident Status:** Critical / High Risk\n**Current Situation:** CFO's laptop stolen in Mumbai (approx. 20 mins ago). Contains unencrypted Q3 financial projections (MNPI).\n\n#### **1. Immediate Containment (In Progress)**\n*   **Access Revoked:** IT has terminated all active sessions (O365, VPN, SaaS) and locked the CFO's account.\n*   **Remote Wipe:** IT is executing remote wipe via MDM (Device ID: CFO-LAP-992).\n*   **Hardware:** Mumbai office is preparing a pre-configured \"loaner\" laptop. IT is facilitating secure handover to the CFO.\n\n#### **2. Regulatory & Legal Actions**\n*   **CERT-In (India):** Mandatory reporting within 6 hours. IT/Legal are coordinating this.\n*   **FIR (Police):** Local team is filing a First Information Report in Mumbai for legal/insurance documentation.\n*   **Materiality Assessment:** General Counsel and the Disclosure Committee are meeting to determine if an 8-K / regulatory disclosure is required due to the MNPI on the device.\n*   **Trading:** A trading blackout has been implemented for all personnel with access to the Q3 projections.\n\n#### **3. Strategic Recommendations**\n*   **Earnings Call:** CFO to use the replacement device. Finance is performing an integrity check to ensure the leaked projections were draft versions and that core systems remain secure.\n*   **Insurance:** Finance/Risk is notifying the cyber-insurance carrier.\n*   **Governance:** Post-incident, mandatory full-disk encryption and a \"Zero Trust\" policy for sensitive financial data will be strictly enforced.\n\n**Next Steps for Chief of Staff:**\n*   Monitor the 6-hour CERT-In filing deadline.\n*   Ensure the Disclosure Committee provides a recommendation on public disclosure before the earnings call.\n*   Confirm receipt of the loaner device by the CFO."}
