2026-07-10 22:25:56 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 22:25:56 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff', 'Vendor_Agent'], 'text': 'result from Sourcing_Sub_Agent\nTo check the stock availability for 25 MacBook Pro M3 Max units with Apple Enterprise India, you should follow these steps, as Apple does not provide a public real-time inventory API for enterprise-level bulk orders:\n\n### 1. Identify Your Procurement Channel\nApple Enterprise sales in India are handled through two primary channels. You should contact the one that best fits your company\'s current setup:\n\n*   **Apple Direct (Corporate/Enterprise Sales):** If your organization is a large enterprise with an existing Apple account manager, contact them directly. They have access to the "Apple Business Manager" (ABM) backend and can provide real-time lead times for bulk orders.\n*   **Apple Authorized Enterprise Resellers (AAER):** If you do not have a direct account, you must go through an authorized partner. Major partners in India include:\n    *   **Redington India** (Distributor)\n    *   **Imagine / Unicorn / Maple** (Enterprise divisions)\n    *   **Ingram Micro** (Distributor)\n\n### 2. Required Information for the Inquiry\nTo get an accurate quote and stock confirmation, provide your account manager or the reseller with the following:\n*   **Exact Configuration:** The M3 Max chip comes in different variations (14-core vs. 16-core CPU, different GPU counts, and Unified Memory options). \n*   **Timeline:** Specify your "Need-by Date."\n*   **Shipping Location:** Stock availability can vary by region (e.g., availability in Mumbai or Bengaluru may differ).\n*   **GST Details:** Provide your companyâ€™s GSTIN, as enterprise bulk orders are processed through B2B invoicing.\n\n### 3. Immediate Action Plan\nIf you need this information right now, follow these steps:\n\n1.  **Visit the [Apple India Enterprise Page](https://www.apple.com/in/business/):** Scroll to the bottom and click on "Contact Apple Enterprise Sales."\n2.  **Request a Quote:** Use the [Apple Business Quote Request form](https://www.apple.com/in/shop/browse/business/find_store).\n3.  **Call a Major Reseller:** If you need an answer within hours, call the **Enterprise Sales Desk** of a major regional partner (e.g., *Imagine* or *Unicorn* Enterprise division). They hold local inventory and can confirm if 25 units are available for immediate dispatch or if they need to be back-ordered.\n\n### Important Note on "M3 Max" Availability:\nBecause the M3 Max is a high-end configuration, it is often **"Build-to-Order" (BTO)**. If you require specific RAM (e.g., 64GB or 128GB) or Storage configurations, it is unlikely that 25 units are sitting in a local warehouse. You should expect a **2â€“4 week lead time** for BTO configurations.\n\n**Would you like me to draft an email template you can send to a reseller to expedite this request?**'}
