*   **Verdict:** **The budget is currently insufficient.** You are facing a shortfall of approximately â‚¹15 Lakhs if you include GST.\n\n### 3. Recommendations to Proceed\n1.  **Request Enterprise Pricing:** Enterprise resellers often provide volume discounts (typically 5â€“12% off MSRP). If you negotiate a 15% discount, the price might drop to ~â‚¹72 Lakhs (excl. GST) or ~â‚¹85 Lakhs (incl. GST). \n2.  **Adjust Specifications:** If the M3 Max is not strictly required for all 25 users, consider a mix of **M3 Pro** and **M3 Max** chips to bring the average unit cost down.\n3.  **Procurement Strategy:**\n    *   Contact a Tier-1 Enterprise Reseller (e.g., **Redington, Ingram Micro, or major regional partners like Imagine/iPlanet Enterprise divisions**).\n    *   Request a **"Bill of Materials" (BOM) quote** specifically mentioning "Enterprise Volume Discount."\n    *   Ensure the quote includes AppleCare+ for Enterprise, as this is standard for corporate procurement.\n\n**Next Steps:** Would you like me to draft a Request for Quotation (RFQ) template that you can send to authorized resellers to secure the volume discount?'}
