ript (Terraform/Ansible/Cloud-Init) to install the stack automatically upon launch.\n*   **Networking/VPN:** Does the cloud environment need to access internal company resources (Git repos, internal APIs)? Ensure your Site-to-Site VPN or Client VPN gateway can handle the additional 50 concurrent connections.\n\n### 3. Execution Strategy (The "Rapid" Path)\n1.  **Today (Urgent):** Identify the cloud provider. Check vCPU quotas. Create the "Golden Image" (a single virtual machine with all required dev tools installed, then captured as a template).\n2.  **Tomorrow:** Perform a "Smoke Test" by spinning up 2 instances. Verify network connectivity, login permissions, and tool functionality.\n3.  **Sunday:** Deploy the remaining 48 instances using the template.\n4.  **Monday:** Provide the connection URLs and login credentials to the 50 developers.\n\n### 4. Critical Questions to Resolve Right Now\n*   **Licensing:** Do you have the necessary Windows/Office licenses for 50 users? (Cloud providers often bake these into the hourly rate).\n*   **Hardware Dependency:** Are the developers expecting high-performance hardware (e.g., for compiling massive C++ codebases)? If so, ensure you select **GPU-optimized or high-memory instance types** (e.g., Azure D-series or AWS M-series).\n*   **Data Sovereignty:** Are there any compliance requirements (GDPR/SOC2) that dictate which geographic region the data must reside in?\n\n**Recommendation:** If you have an existing Enterprise Agreement with Microsoft or AWS, **contact your account representative immediately.** They can often fast-track quota increases and provide "Jumpstart" support teams to help with the configuration of 50+ seats over the weekend.'}
