2026-07-10 23:12:34 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 23:12:34 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff'], 'text': 'result from HR_Safety_Agent\nI have coordinated with the relevant departments to ensure that the 50 developers for Project Titan have seamless access on Monday despite the ID card delay.\n\n### **Summary of Coordination**\n\n*   **Facilities (Access Plan):**\n    *   **Contingency:** All 50 developers have been pre-registered in the Visitor Management System (VMS). They will receive Temporary Daily Visitor Badges at the lobby upon presenting a government-issued ID.\n    *   **Access:** These badges are pre-coded for the Project Titan workspace (Zone X) and will bypass standard visitor restrictions for the first 48 hours.\n    *   **Escort:** A "Buddy System" is in place, with 5 Project Titan leads assigned to meet groups in the lobby at 8:30 AM to assist with the transition.\n    *   **Communication:** A clear email will be sent to the developers by EOD Friday explaining the check-in process so there is no confusion on Monday morning.\n\n*   **Talent Acquisition & Onboarding (Preparation):**\n    *   The teams are finalizing the roster and auditing documentation (NDAs, equipment, system access) to ensure that the only hurdle is the physical badge, which is now resolved by the Facilities plan.\n    *   They will report any "Blocked" individuals by EOD Friday to ensure last-minute issues are addressed before the weekend.\n\n### **Action Items for Monday**\n1.  **7:30 AM:** Facilities will check if any permanent cards were finalized over the weekend for priority distribution.\n2.  **8:30 AM:** Titan Leads will meet their respective groups in the main lobby.\n3.  **Onboarding:** Onboarding/HR teams will monitor the check-in flow to identify and resolve any unexpected issues in real-time.\n\nAll systems are go for Monday morning. Please let me know if you need further clarification on any of these protocols.'}
