thread is often a negative sentiment trigger).\n    *   **Tone Shift:** Does the conversation move from public to DMs? (This usually indicates a de-escalation of a negative issue).\n\n---\n\n### 4. Automated Monitoring Recommendation\nIf you need to automate this for real-time alerts, I recommend the following setup:\n\n1.  **Tool:** **Zapier** or **Make.com** connected to the **Twitter API**.\n2.  **Trigger:** "New Mention" or "New Tweet" filtered by the specific handles.\n3.  **Action:** Send the text to an **AI Sentiment Analysis API** (like OpenAI’s GPT-4o or Google Cloud Natural Language API).\n4.  **Notification:** Push the result (e.g., "Sentiment: Negative, Content: [Text]") to a Slack channel or Microsoft Teams group.\n\n---\n\n**Would you like me to analyze a specific set of tweets from this thread?** \nIf you paste the text of the recent replies here, I can provide an immediate, detailed sentiment breakdown for you.'}
