ting period closed").\n\n### 4. Check Interface/IDoc Logs (If using Bank Integration/PI/PO)\nIf the payment was sent to a bank portal (e.g., HDFC, ICICI, SBI host-to-host):\n*   **Transaction:** `WE02` or `WE05` (IDoc List)\n*   **Steps:**\n    1.  Search by **Message Type** (usually `PAYEXT` or `CGI_XML_CT`).\n    2.  Check the **Status Record**. \n        *   Status **03**: Data passed to port.\n        *   Status **18/20**: Triggered error in the interface.\n        *   Status **02**: Error in processing.\n    3.  Click on the status code to see the specific error returned by the bank\'s API or middleware.\n\n### 5. Check Posting Period/Authorization Errors\n*   **Transaction:** `ST22` (ABAP Dump Analysis)\n    *   If the system crashed during the transaction, check for a "Dump" at the exact timestamp.\n*   **Transaction:** `SU53` (Display Authorization Data)\n    *   If the user reported an "Authorization Error," run this immediately after the failed attempt to see if the user lacked specific object permissions (e.g., `F_BKPF_BUK`).\n\n---\n\n**Common Root Causes for \u20b918.5 Lakhs Range Failures:**\n1.  **Amount Limit:** Does the bank account or the SAP Payment Medium Workbench (PMW) have a limit on the maximum transaction amount?\n2.  **Posting Period:** Is the period for the specific G/L account closed? (Check `OB52`).\n3.  **Vendor Master Data:** Verify if the "Payment Method" or "Bank Details" for Rashi Peripherals were modified or locked in `XK02` / `BP` just before the payment run.\n\n**Recommended Action:**\nIf you provide the **specific error code** (e.g., `F5150`, `M8081`) found in the logs, I can provide a precise resolution for that error.'}
