2026-07-10 23:18:48 India Standard Time | INFO     | nsflow:_log:720 - nsflow - 2026-07-10 23:18:48 - generated/sentinel_crisis_command - INFO - {'otrace': ['Chief_of_Staff', 'Vendor_Agent'], 'text': 'result from Vendor_Risk_Sub_Agent\nTo address your request regarding **Rashi Peripherals Limited (Rashi Peripherals)**, here is the breakdown of their leadership and the current context regarding recent public escalations.\n\n### 1. Primary Leadership Contact\nRashi Peripherals is a publicly traded company (listed on NSE/BSE). Their leadership structure is as follows:\n\n*   **Chairman & Managing Director:** Krishna Kumar Choudhary\n*   **Whole-time Director & CEO:** Kapal Suresh Pansari\n*   **Chief Financial Officer:** Rajendra Kumar Tulsian\n*   **Company Secretary & Compliance Officer:** Naomi David\n\n**Contact Channel:** For formal corporate or grievance-related communication, the company directs stakeholders to their Secretarial Department:\n*   **Email:** investor.relations@rptechindia.com\n*   **Corporate Office:** Rashi Peripherals Limited, Ariisto House, 5th Floor, Corner of Telli Galli, Andheri (E), Mumbai - 400069.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Context: The \'Automated Error\' Public Escalation\nRashi Peripherals (operating under the brand **RP tech India**) recently faced a significant public relations and operational crisis involving an **automated email/system error** that triggered widespread customer alarm.\n\n**The Incident:**\n*   **Nature of the error:** In mid-2024, a technical glitch in the company’s automated customer service/warranty management system caused a mass-mailing event. Thousands of customers—many of whom had no recent interaction with the company—received emails claiming their warranty status had changed, their accounts were compromised, or demanding immediate action regarding hardware support tickets.\n*   **Public Escalation:** The sudden influx of these emails led to a surge of complaints on social media platforms (primarily X/Twitter and Reddit). Users suspected a **data breach** or a sophisticated **phishing campaign**, as the emails appeared to originate from legitimate RP tech domains or associated support channels.\n*   **The \'Automated\' Aspect:** It was identified that a misconfiguration in the CRM/ticketing software (likely during an automated batch update or system migration) triggered the dispatch of legacy or test-environment email templates to the active production database.\n\n**Current Status:**\n*   **Company Response:** Rashi Peripherals issued clarifications on their social media channels stating that the emails were "erroneous" and "technical in nature," explicitly denying any security breach or leak of sensitive customer financial data.\n*   **Mitigation:** The company halted the automated mailer service and initiated a system audit. \n*   **Public Sentiment:** While the technical issue was resolved, the escalation caused a temporary dip in brand trust, with users criticizing the lack of immediate proactive communication. Customers are currently advised to treat any unexpected warranty-related emails from them with caution and verify status via their [official portal](https://rptechindia.com/).\n\n***\n\n**Recommendation:** If you are contacting them regarding this specific issue, reference the **"automated system misconfiguration reported in [Month of Incident]"** to ensure your query is routed to their IT/Customer Experience oversight team rather than the standard sales desk.'}
