ected parties to prioritize their resolutions. For any further assistance, please reach out to us at [Official Support Email/Portal]."\n\n---\n\n### Internal Guidelines for Implementation\n\n*   **Do not engage in the comments:** Instruct your social media team *not* to reply to individual commenters who are piling on. Every response should be directed solely at the primary grievance.\n*   **The "One-Voice" Policy:** Ensure that the Sales team (who manages the Rashi relationship) and the PR team (who manages the Twitter account) are aligned. Any information provided to Rashi in private must be consistent with the "verification phase" stance identified by the Internal Comms team.\n*   **Documentation:** Before any public follow-up, ensure that you have the internal "ledger" ready. If Rashi posts a follow-up claiming "they haven\'t heard from us," you must be prepared to post a screenshot of the email/ticket sent to them (redacting sensitive financial data) to prove you have initiated the dialogue.\n\n**Next Steps:**\nIf you need this response tailored for a specific platform (e.g., LinkedIn vs. Twitter) or if you would like me to draft a more detailed internal memo to be sent to Rashi Peripherals to accompany the public response, please let me know.'}
